table_lines.name: Image Rotation
table_lines.comment: How far to rotate the image clockwise in degrees, before any Image Horizontal Flip (0070,0041) is applied.

table_lines.name: Image Horizontal Flip
table_lines.comment: Whether or not to flip the image horizontally after any Image Rotation has been applied such that the left side of the image becomes the right side.

table_lines.name: Graphic Layer Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence of Items each of which represents a single layer in which overlays, graphics or text may be rendered.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
An Item is required for each layer referenced from the

table_lines.name: >Graphic Layer
table_lines.comment: A string that identifies the layer.

table_lines.name: >Graphic Layer Order
table_lines.comment: An integer indicating the order in which it is recommended that the layer be rendered, if the display is capable of distinguishing. Lower numbered layers are to be rendered first.

table_lines.name: >Graphic Layer Recommended Display Grayscale Value
table_lines.comment: A default single gray unsigned value in which it is recommended that the layer be rendered on a monochrome display. The units are specified in P-Values from a minimum of 0000H (black) up to a maximum of FFFFH (white).

table_lines.name: >Graphic Layer Description
table_lines.comment: A free text description of the contents of this layer.

table_lines.name: Instance Number
table_lines.comment: A number that identifies this Waveform.

table_lines.name: Content Date
table_lines.comment: The date the Waveform data was created.

table_lines.name: Content Time
table_lines.comment: The time the Waveform data was created.

table_lines.name: Acquisition DateTime
table_lines.comment: The date and time that the acquisition of data that resulted in this waveform started; the reference timestamp for the Multiplex Group Time Offset (0018,1068) for a waveform multiplex group

table_lines.name: Referenced Instance Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Composite SOP Instances that are significantly related to this Waveform.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Purpose of Reference Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Code describing the purpose of the reference to the Instance(s).
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Waveform Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items, each representing one waveform multiplex group.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Ordering of Items in this Sequence is significant for external reference to specific multiplex groups.

table_lines.name: >Multiplex Group Time Offset
table_lines.comment: Required if Acquisition Time Synchronized (0018,1800) value is Y; may be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Trigger Time Offset
table_lines.comment: Offset time in milliseconds from a synchronization trigger to the first sample of a waveform multiplex group. May be positive or negative. Required if waveform acquisition is synchronized to a trigger.

table_lines.name: >Number of Waveform Channels
table_lines.comment: Number of channels for this multiplex group.

table_lines.name: >Number of Waveform Samples
table_lines.comment: Number of samples per channel in this multiplex group.

table_lines.name: >Sampling Frequency
table_lines.comment: Frequency in Hz.

table_lines.name: >Multiplex Group Label
table_lines.comment: Label for multiplex group.

table_lines.name: >Multiplex Group UID
table_lines.comment:
Unique Identifier for the multiplex group.
Required if the same Multiplex Group is used in more than one SOP Instance. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Powerline Frequency
table_lines.comment: Frequency of the power line in Hz.

table_lines.name: >Channel Definition Sequence
table_lines.comment:
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Ordering of Items in this Sequence is significant for reference to specific channels.

table_lines.name: >>Waveform Channel Number
table_lines.comment: Equipment physical channel number used for acquisition.

table_lines.name: >>Channel Label
table_lines.comment: Text label for channel, which may be used for display purposes.

table_lines.name: >>Channel Status
table_lines.comment:
One or more values for the status of this channel within this SOP Instance.
Precise location of a change in status may be noted in an Annotation.

table_lines.name: >>Channel Source Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A coded descriptor of the waveform channel source (metric, anatomical position, function, and technique).
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
(see

table_lines.usage: Baseline CID determined by IOD specialization

table_lines.name: >>Channel Source Modifiers Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items that further qualify the Waveform Source.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Ordering of Items in this Sequence may be semantically significant.
Required if Channel Source Sequence (003A,0208) does not fully specify the semantics of the source.

table_lines.usage: Baseline CID determined by IOD specialization

table_lines.name: >>Source Waveform Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that provides reference to a DICOM waveform from which this channel was derived.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>Referenced Waveform Channels
table_lines.comment: Identifies the waveform multiplex group and channel within the referenced SOP Instance. Pair of values (M,C).

table_lines.name: >>Channel Derivation Description
table_lines.comment: Additional description of waveform channel derivation.

table_lines.name: >>Channel Sensitivity
table_lines.comment: Nominal numeric value of unit quantity of sample. Required if samples represent defined (not arbitrary) units.

table_lines.name: >>Channel Sensitivity Units Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A coded descriptor of the Units of measure for the Channel Sensitivity.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
(see
Required if Channel Sensitivity (003A,0210) is present.

table_lines.name: >>Channel Sensitivity Correction Factor
table_lines.comment: Required if Channel Sensitivity (003A,0210) is present.

table_lines.name: >>Channel Baseline
table_lines.comment:
Offset of encoded sample value 0 from actual 0 using the units defined in the Channel Sensitivity Units Sequence (003A,0211).
Required if Channel Sensitivity (003A,0210) is present.

table_lines.name: >>Channel Time Skew
table_lines.comment: Required if Channel Sample Skew is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Channel Sample Skew
table_lines.comment: Required if Channel Time Skew is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Waveform Amplifier Type
table_lines.comment: The type of amplifier used for waveform acquisition.

table_lines.name: >>Filter Low Frequency
table_lines.comment:
Nominal 3dB point of lower frequency of pass band; in Hz.
Required if Waveform Amplifier Type (003A,0317) is AC and Filter Low Frequency Characteristics Sequence (003A,0318) is not present. Shall not be present if Waveform Amplifier Type (003A,0317) is DC. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >>Filter Low Frequency Characteristics Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The properties of low frequency (high-pass) filters used for the waveform acquisition.
Required if Waveform Amplifier Type (003A,0317) is AC and Filter Low Frequency (003A,0220) is not present. May be present otherwise unless Waveform Amplifier Type (003A,0317) is DC.
At least one item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Filter High Frequency
table_lines.comment:
Nominal 3dB point of upper frequency of pass band; in Hz.
Required if Waveform Amplifier Type (003A,0317) is present and Filter High Frequency Characteristics Sequence (003A,0319) is not present. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >>Filter High Frequency Characteristics Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The properties of high frequency (low-pass) filters used for the waveform acquisition.
Required if Waveform Amplifier Type (003A,0317) is present and Filter High Frequency (003A,0221) is not present. May be present otherwise.
At least one item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Notch Filter Frequency
table_lines.comment: Center frequency of notch filter(s); in Hz.

table_lines.name: >>Notch Filter Bandwidth
table_lines.comment: Nominal 3dB bandwidth of notch filter(s); in Hz.

table_lines.name: >>Notch Filter Characteristics Sequence
table_lines.comment: The properties of notch filters used for the waveform acquisition.

table_lines.name: >>Summarized Filter Lookup Table Sequence
table_lines.comment: Filter Lookup Table providing the total effect of all filters applied.

table_lines.name: >>Channel Impedance Sequence
table_lines.comment: One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>Impedance Value
table_lines.comment: Measured value of the impedance in Ohm.

table_lines.name: >>>Impedance Measurement DateTime
table_lines.comment: Point in time the measurement took place.

table_lines.name: >>>Impedance Measurement Frequency
table_lines.comment: Frequency of the impedance measurement current in Hz.

table_lines.name: >>>Impedance Measurement Current Type
table_lines.comment: Type of current used to measure the impedance

table_lines.name: Waveform Presentation Group Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items, each Item describing a Presentation Group of one or more waveform channels to be displayed together.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Presentation Group Number
table_lines.comment: A number that identifies the Presentation Group.

table_lines.name: >Channel Display Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items, each Item describing a channel to be displayed in the Presentation Group.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Referenced Waveform Channels
table_lines.comment: Identifier of the displayed channel, specified as a pair of values (M,C) where the first value is the ordinal of the Item of Waveform Sequence (5400,0100) (i.e., the Multiplex Group Number), and the second value is the ordinal of the Item of the Channel Definition Sequence (003A,0200) Attribute (i.e., the Waveform Channel Number) within the multiplex group.

table_lines.name: >>Channel Offset
table_lines.comment: The offset in seconds from the beginning of the channel waveform data to the first sample to be used for presentation. Value may be negative.

table_lines.name: >>Display Shading Flag
table_lines.comment: Specifies display area shading between the displayed waveform channel and another line. The nature of the shading (e.g., solid, or cross-hatching) is implementation dependent.

table_lines.name: Waveform Annotation Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Annotation Items.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Unformatted Text Value
table_lines.comment:
Text Observation Value (annotation).
Mutually exclusive with Concept Name Code Sequence (0040,A043).

table_lines.name: >Concept Name Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Code representing the fully specified name of the NUMERIC measurement or CODED concept.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Mutually exclusive with Unformatted Text Value (0070,0006).

table_lines.usage: Baseline CID may be defined in IOD definition.

table_lines.name: >>Modifier Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence of Items modifying or specializing the Concept Name.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if the value of Concept Name Code Sequence (0040,A043) does not fully describe the semantics of the measurement or concept.

table_lines.usage: Baseline CID may be defined in IOD definition.

table_lines.name: >Concept Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that conveys the categorical coded nominal value.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.usage: Baseline CID may be defined in IOD definition.

table_lines.name: >>Modifier Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence of Items modifying or specializing the Concept.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if the value of Concept Code Sequence (0040,A168) does not fully describe the semantics of the concept value.

table_lines.usage: Baseline CID may be defined in IOD definition.

table_lines.name: >Numeric Value
table_lines.comment: Numeric measurement value or values.

table_lines.name: >Measurement Units Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Units of measurement.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Temporal Range Type
table_lines.comment: Required if Annotation does not apply to entire Referenced Waveform Channels; shall not be present if Annotation applies to entire temporal extent of referenced channels.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Time Offsets
table_lines.comment: Specifies temporal points for annotation by number of seconds after start of data. Required if Temporal Range Type (0040,A130) is present, and if Referenced Sample Positions (0040,A132) and Referenced DateTime (0040,A13A) are not present.

table_lines.name: >Referenced DateTime
table_lines.comment: Specifies temporal points for annotation by absolute time. Required if Temporal Range Type (0040,A130) is present, and if Referenced Sample Positions (0040,A132) and Referenced Time Offsets (0040,A138) are not present.

table_lines.name: Graphic Group Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that describes the combined graphic object.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Graphic Group ID
table_lines.comment: A unique number identifying the Graphic Group, i.e., the combined graphic object.

table_lines.name: >Graphic Group Label
table_lines.comment: Name used to identify the Graphic Group, i.e., the combined graphic object.

table_lines.name: >Graphic Group Description
table_lines.comment: Description of the group.

table_lines.name: Waveform Filter Type
table_lines.comment: The type of filter.

table_lines.name: Filter Low Frequency
table_lines.comment:
Nominal 3dB point of lower frequency of pass band in Hz. This is the cutoff frequency of a high-pass filter.
Required if the filter is a high-pass filter.
Shall be consistent with Filter Low Frequency (003A,0220) in the enclosing Dataset, if present.

table_lines.name: Filter High Frequency
table_lines.comment:
Nominal 3dB point of upper frequency of pass band in Hz. This is the cutoff frequency of a low-pass filter.
Required if the filter is a low-pass filter.
Shall be consistent with Filter High Frequency (003A,0221) in the enclosing Dataset, if present.

table_lines.name: Notch Filter Frequency
table_lines.comment:
Center frequency of the notch filter in Hz.
Required if the filter is a notch filter.

table_lines.name: Notch Filter Bandwidth
table_lines.comment:
Nominal 3dB bandwidth of the notch filter; in Hz.
Required if the filter is a notch filter.

table_lines.name: Analog Filter Characteristics Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Characteristic parameters of the analog filter.
Required if Waveform Filter Type (003A,0322) is ANALOG.
A single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Analog Filter Roll Off
table_lines.comment: The slope of the filter response between pass-band and stop-band given in dB/octave.

table_lines.name: >Analog Filter Type Code Sequence
table_lines.comment: A coded descriptor of the type of analog filter.

table_lines.name: Digital Filter Characteristics Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Characteristic parameters of the digital filter.
Required if Waveform Filter Type (003A,0322) is DIGITAL.
A single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Digital Filter Order
table_lines.comment: Filter order is the maximum delay, in samples, used in creating each output sample.

table_lines.name: >Digital Filter Type Code Sequence
table_lines.comment: A coded descriptor of the type of digital filter.

table_lines.name: Waveform Filter Description
table_lines.comment: A textual description of the filter.

table_lines.name: Filter Lookup Table Sequence
table_lines.comment: A Lookup Table defining the filter.

C.10.13-1.table_caption: Waveform Filter Lookup Table Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: Filter Lookup Table Description
table_lines.comment: A textual description of the Filter Lookup Table.

table_lines.name: Frequency Encoding Code Sequence
table_lines.comment: Encoding of frequency values in the Lookup Table Data.

table_lines.name: Magnitude Encoding Code Sequence
table_lines.comment: Encoding of filter response magnitude in the Lookup Table Data.

table_lines.name: Filter Lookup Table Data
table_lines.comment:
Lookup Table Data.
See

table_lines.name: Modality LUT Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Defines a Sequence of Modality LUTs.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Shall not be present if Rescale Intercept (0028,1052) is present.

table_lines.name: >LUT Descriptor
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the format of the LUT Data in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >LUT Explanation
table_lines.comment: Free form text explanation of the meaning of the LUT.

table_lines.name: >Modality LUT Type
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the output values of this Modality LUT.
See

table_lines.name: >LUT Data
table_lines.comment: LUT Data in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Rescale Intercept
table_lines.comment:
The value b in relationship between stored values (SV) and the output units specified in Rescale Type (0028,1054).
Output units = m*SV + b.
Required if Modality LUT Sequence (0028,3000) is not present. Shall not be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Rescale Slope
table_lines.comment:
m in the equation specified by Rescale Intercept (0028,1052).
Required if Rescale Intercept is present.

table_lines.name: Rescale Type
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the output units of Rescale Slope (0028,1053) and Rescale Intercept (0028,1052).
See
Required if Rescale Intercept is present.

table_lines.name: VOI LUT Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Defines a Sequence of VOI LUTs.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Window Center (0028,1050) is not present. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >LUT Descriptor
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the format of the LUT Data in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >LUT Explanation
table_lines.comment: Free form text explanation of the meaning of the LUT.

table_lines.name: >LUT Data
table_lines.comment: LUT Data in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Window Center
table_lines.comment:
Window Center for display.
See
Required if VOI LUT Sequence (0028,3010) is not present. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Window Width
table_lines.comment: Required if Window Center (0028,1050) is present.

table_lines.name: Window Center & Width Explanation
table_lines.comment: Free form explanation of the meaning of the Window Center and Width. Multiple values correspond to multiple Window Center and Width values.

table_lines.name: VOI LUT Function
table_lines.comment:
Describes a VOI LUT function to apply to the values of Window Center (0028,1050) and Window Width (0028,1051).
See
When this Attribute is not present, the interpretation of the values of Window Center (0028,1050) and Window Width (0028,1051) is linear as in

table_lines.name: Presentation LUT Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Defines a Sequence of Presentation LUTs.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Presentation LUT Shape (2050,0020) is absent.

table_lines.name: >LUT Descriptor
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the format of the LUT Data in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >LUT Explanation
table_lines.comment: Free form text explanation of the meaning of the LUT.

table_lines.name: >LUT Data
table_lines.comment: LUT Data in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Presentation LUT Shape
table_lines.comment:
Specifies predefined Presentation LUT transformation. Required if Presentation LUT Sequence (2050,0010) is absent.
See

table_lines.name: Overlay Activation Layer
table_lines.comment: Required if Group 60xx is present in the referenced image(s) or the Presentation State Instance containing this Module.

table_lines.name: Softcopy VOI LUT Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Defines a Sequence of VOI LUTs or Window Centers and Widths and to which images and frames they apply.
No more than one VOI LUT Sequence containing a single Item or one pair of Window Center/Width values shall be specified for each image or frame.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if the VOI LUT transformation in this Item does not apply to all the images and frames listed in the

table_lines.name: Modality
table_lines.comment:
Type of device, process or method that created the Instances in this Series.
See

table_lines.name: Presentation Creation Date
table_lines.comment: Date on which this presentation was created.

table_lines.name: Presentation Creation Time
table_lines.comment: Time at which this presentation was created.

table_lines.name: Referenced Series Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items where each Item includes the Attributes of one Series to which the Presentation applies.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Series Instance UID
table_lines.comment: Unique identifier of a Series that is part of the Study defined by the Study Instance UID (0020,000D) in the enclosing Data Set.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The set of images and frames to which the Presentation applies. These shall be of the Study defined by Study Instance UID (0020,000D) and the Series defined by Series Instance UID (0020,000E).
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
The referenced SOP Class shall be the same for all Images in any Item of this Referenced Series Sequence (0008,1115).

table_lines.name: Shutter Presentation Value
table_lines.comment:
A single grayscale unsigned value used to replace those parts of the image occluded by the shutter, when rendered on a monochrome display. The units are specified in P-Values.
Required if the

table_lines.name: Mask Subtraction Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Applicable Frame Range (0028,6102) shall not be included in the Sequence Item.
See

table_lines.name: >Mask Operation
table_lines.comment:
Type of mask operation to be performed
See

table_lines.name: >Contrast Frame Averaging
table_lines.comment:
Specified the number of contrast frames to average together before performing the mask operation.
Required if Mask Frame Numbers (0028,6110) specifies more than one frame (i.e., is multi-valued).

table_lines.name: Recommended Viewing Mode
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the recommended viewing protocol(s).
Required if Mask Subtraction Sequence (0028,6100) is present.

table_lines.name: Blending Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence of Items, one identifying and describing transformations upon a set of underlying grayscale images, and the other identifying and describing transformations upon a set of superimposed grayscale images.
Two Items shall be included in this Sequence
See

table_lines.name: >Blending Position
table_lines.comment: Whether or not the contents of the Item represent the superimposed or underlying image set.

table_lines.name: >Study Instance UID
table_lines.comment: Unique identifier for the Study that contains the images, which may differ from the Study in which the presentation state is contained.

table_lines.name: >Softcopy VOI LUT Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Defines a Sequence of VOI LUTs or Window Centers and Widths and to which images and frames they apply.
No more than one VOI LUT Sequence containing a single Item or one pair of Window Center/Width values shall be specified for each image or frame.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if a VOI LUT is to be applied to referenced image(s).

table_lines.name: >>Referenced Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items identifying images that are defined in the enclosing Item of Blending Sequence (0070,0402), to which this VOI LUT or Window Center and Width applies.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if the VOI LUT transformation in this Item does not apply to all the images and frames in the enclosing Item of Blending Sequence (0070,0402).

table_lines.name: Relative Opacity
table_lines.comment:
A value from 0.0 to 1.0 indicating the relative opacity of the pixels of the superimposed image, where 1.0 means that pixels of the superimposed image completely replace the pixels of the underlying image, and 0.0 means that the pixels of the underlying image completely replace the pixels of the superimposed image.
See

table_lines.name: Referenced Spatial Registration Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A reference to Spatial Registration Instances that may be used to register the underlying and superimposed images.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: ICC Profile
table_lines.comment: An ICC Profile encoding the transformation of device-dependent color stored pixel values into PCS-Values.

table_lines.name: Color Space
table_lines.comment:
A label that identifies the well-known color space of the image. Shall be consistent with any ICC Profile (0028,2000) that is also present.
See

table_lines.name: Presentation Creation Date
table_lines.comment: Date on which this structured display was created.

table_lines.name: Presentation Creation Time
table_lines.comment: Time at which this structured display was created.

table_lines.name: Number of Screens
table_lines.comment:
The number of screens for this Structured Display.
If SOP Class UID (0008,0016) equals 1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.131(Basic Structured Display), the value shall be 1.

table_lines.name: Nominal Screen Definition Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items that describes the set of screens for this Structured Display.
The number of Items shall equal the value of Number of Screens (0072,0100).
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Icon Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
This icon image is representative of the structured display.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Hanging Protocol Name
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the hanging protocol that was used in the creation of this structured display.
See

table_lines.name: Hanging Protocol Creator
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the creator of the Hanging Protocol.
See

C.11.17-1.table_caption: Structured Display Image Box Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Structured Display Image Box Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The image display boxes defined in the display environment, together with the reference to the image to be displayed in each Image Box.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Display Environment Spatial Position
table_lines.comment:
Exactly four dimensionless floating point values, in the range 0.0 to 1.0, indicating the rectangular coordinate position of the Image Box within the Display Environment.
See

table_lines.name: >Image Box Number
table_lines.comment: An integer that is unique across all Items of the Structured Display Image Box Sequence (0072,0422) that identifies the Image Box.

table_lines.name: >Image Box Layout Type
table_lines.comment: Type of layout of the Image Box. The types are primarily distinguished by their interaction technique.

table_lines.name: >Image Box Tile Horizontal Dimension
table_lines.comment:
Positive integer defining the horizontal Image Box tile dimension; the number of columns.
Required if the value of Image Box Layout Type (0072,0304) is TILED.

table_lines.name: >Image Box Tile Vertical Dimension
table_lines.comment:
Positive integer defining the vertical Image Box tile dimension; the number of rows.
Required if the value of Image Box Layout Type (0072,0304) is TILED.

table_lines.name: >Image Box Overlap Priority
table_lines.comment: If this Image Box overlaps in spatial position with others, this Attribute indicates the layer of this Image Box in relation to the others. The value shall be a positive integer in the range 1 to 100, where 1 = top and 100 = bottom. If this Attribute is not present, then the expected behavior is not defined.

table_lines.name: >Display Set Horizontal Justification
table_lines.comment: Indicates direction in which to horizontally justify the image within an Image Box that is not the same shape (aspect ratio) as the image.

table_lines.name: >Display Set Vertical Justification
table_lines.comment: Indicates direction in which to vertically justify the image within an Image Box that is not the same shape (aspect ratio) as the image.

table_lines.name: >Preferred Playback Sequencing
table_lines.comment:
Describes the preferred playback sequencing for the Image Box. Overrides any Preferred Playback Sequencing (0018,1244) value in the image objects being displayed.
Required if the value of Image Box Layout Type (0072,0304) is CINE.

table_lines.name: >Recommended Display Frame Rate
table_lines.comment:
Recommended rate at which the frames of a multi-frame image shall be displayed, in frames/second. Shall have a value greater than zero. Overrides any Recommended Display Frame Rate (0008,2144) value in the image objects being displayed.
Required if the value of Image Box Layout Type (0072,0304) is CINE and if Cine Relative to Real-Time (0072,0330) is not present.

table_lines.name: >Cine Relative to Real-Time
table_lines.comment:
A positive dimensionless floating point numeric factor equal to playback rate divided by acquisition rate.
Required if the value of Image Box Layout Type (0072,0304) is CINE and if Recommended Display Frame Rate (0008,2144) is not present.

table_lines.name: >Initial Cine Run State
table_lines.comment: Required if the value of Image Box Layout Type (0072,0304) is CINE.

table_lines.name: >Start Trim
table_lines.comment:
The frame number of the first frame of the multi-frame image to be displayed in a CINE Image Box.
Required if the value of Image Box Layout Type (0072,0304) is CINE.

table_lines.name: >Stop Trim
table_lines.comment:
The Frame Number of the last frame of the multi-frame image to be displayed in a CINE Image Box.
Required if the value of Image Box Layout Type (0072,0304) is CINE.

table_lines.name: >Referenced First Frame Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Reference to the initial frame in a stack to be displayed in this image box. If value is not present, the first image frame to be displayed is not defined by the Standard.
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if the value of Image Box Layout Type (0072,0304) is STACK.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Reference to the Image SOP Instances, or frames from multi-frame Image SOP Instances, to be displayed in this Image Box.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Referenced Presentation State Sequence (0008,9237), Referenced Stereometric Instance Sequence (0008,1134), and Referenced Instance Sequence (0008,114A) are not present.
See

table_lines.name: >>Referenced Presentation State Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Reference to a Softcopy Presentation State SOP Instance to be applied to the referenced image.
Only a single Item shall be permitted in this sequence.
Required if presentation controls are to be applied to the image or image frame before rendering in the Structured Display.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Presentation State Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Reference to a Softcopy Presentation State SOP Instance or a Volumetric Presentation State SOP Instance whose referenced images are to be displayed in the Image Box using the presentation controls of the referenced SOP Instance.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence. Multiple items are only permitted if the Image Box Layout Type (0072,0304) has a value of VOLUME_CINE.
Required if Referenced Image Sequence (0008,1140), Referenced Stereometric Instance Sequence (0008,1134), and Referenced Instance Sequence (0008,114A) are not present.
See

table_lines.name: >Referenced Instance Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Reference to a non-image SOP Instance (e.g., waveform, SR, encapsulated document) whose content is to be displayed in the Image Box.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Referenced Presentation State Sequence (0008,9237), Referenced Stereometric Instance Sequence (0008,1134), and Referenced Image Sequence (0008,1140) are not present.
See

table_lines.name: >Referenced Stereometric Instance Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Reference to a Stereometric SOP Instance whose referenced images are to be displayed in the Image Box.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Referenced Presentation State Sequence (0008,9237), Referenced Instance Sequence (0008,114A), and Referenced Image Sequence (0008,1140) are not present.
See

table_lines.name: Image Box Synchronization Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Description of synchronized display between two or more Image Boxes. Required if synchronized display is specified between Image Boxes.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Synchronized Image Box List
table_lines.comment:
Multi-valued list of two or more Image Box Number (0072,0302) values. Indicates that the display of multiple image frames within the specified Image Boxes are synchronized.
Referenced Image Boxes shall be of same Image Box Layout Type (0072,0304).
An Image Box Number value may appear in only one Image Box Synchronization Sequence (0072,0430) Item.

table_lines.name: >Type of Synchronization
table_lines.comment:
Type of synchronization between Image Boxes.
See

table_lines.name: Structured Display Text Box Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that describes a text annotation.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Unformatted Text Value
table_lines.comment:
The text value may contain spaces, as well as multiple lines separated by CR LF, but otherwise no format control characters (such as horizontal or vertical tab and form feed) shall be present, even if permitted by the Value Representation of ST.
The text shall be interpreted as specified by Specific Character Set (0008,0005) if present in the SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: >Display Environment Spatial Position
table_lines.comment: Exactly four dimensionless floating point values, in the range 0.0 to 1.0, indicating the rectangular coordinate position within the Display Environment of the bounding box in which Unformatted Text Value (0070,0006) is to be displayed.

table_lines.name: >Bounding Box Text Horizontal Justification
table_lines.comment: Location of the text relative to the vertical edges of the bounding box.

C.11.19-1.table_caption: XA/XRF Presentation State Mask Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Mask Subtraction Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Defines a Sequence that describes mask subtraction operations for Multi-frame Images.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A reference to a selected Image.
Required if
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Applicable Frame Range
table_lines.comment:
Each frame shall only be associated with a single Item of this Sequence.
Required if Mask Operation (0028,6101) equals REV_TID. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Mask Frame Numbers
table_lines.comment: Specifies the frame numbers of the pixel data used to generate this mask. Frames in a Multi-frame Image are specified by sequentially increasing number values beginning with 1. Required if the Mask Operation (0028,6101) is AVG_SUB.

table_lines.name: >Contrast Frame Averaging
table_lines.comment: Specifies the number of contrast frames to average together before performing the mask operation. If the Attribute is missing, no averaging is performed.

table_lines.name: >TID Offset
table_lines.comment:
If Mask Operation is TID, specifies the offset to be subtracted from the current frame number in order to locate the mask frame in TID mode.
If Mask Operation is REV_TID, specifies the initial offset to be subtracted from the first contrast frame number. See
If zero length, TID Offset defaults to 1. Required if Mask Operation (0028,6101) is TID or REV_TID.

table_lines.name: >Pixel Intensity Relationship LUT Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence of Pixel Intensity Relationship LUTs that specifies a transformation to logarithmic space.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Pixel Intensity Relationship (0028,1040) is not LOG for frames included in this Item of the Mask Subtraction Sequence (0028,6100).

table_lines.name: >>LUT Frame Range
table_lines.comment:
Each pair of numbers in this multi-valued Attribute specifies a beginning and ending frame number inclusive of a range where this LUT operation is specified.
Discontinuous ranges are represented by multiple pairs of numbers. Frames in a Multi-frame Image are specified by sequentially increasing number values beginning with 1.

table_lines.name: >>LUT Descriptor
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the format of the LUT Data in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >>LUT Data
table_lines.comment: LUT Data in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>LUT Function
table_lines.comment: The transformation function this LUT applies to the stored pixel values.

table_lines.name: >Pixel Shift Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence containing the pixel shift values for the masks of the specified frame range(s) in the specified region(s).
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Pixel Shift Frame Range
table_lines.comment:
Each pair of numbers in this multi-valued Attribute specify a beginning and ending contrast frame number inclusive of a range where this pixel shift is specified.
Discontinuous ranges are represented by multiple pairs of numbers. Frames in a Multi-frame Image are specified by sequentially increasing number values beginning with 1.
Overlapping frame ranges are not permitted.

table_lines.name: >>Region Pixel Shift Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence containing the pixel shifts for this frame(s).
Only one sub region of this frame(s) shall be specified when the pixel shift is applicable for the full size or a single region of the frame(s).
More than one sub region of this frame(s) may be specified when pixel shift is different in different regions.
The order of Items in this Sequence is significant, see
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>Mask Sub-pixel Shift
table_lines.comment:
A pair of floating point numbers specifying the fractional vertical [adjacent row spacing] and horizontal [adjacent column spacing] pixel shift applied to the mask before subtracting it from the region of the frame numbers specified by Pixel Shift Frame Range (0028,9506) of this Pixel Shift Sequence (0028,9501) Item.
The region is specified by the polygon defined by the Vertices of the Region (0028,9503) Attribute. The pixels on the line of the polygon belong to the region.
See

table_lines.name: >>>Vertices of the Region
table_lines.comment:
Multiple Values where the first set of two values are:
row of the origin vertexcolumn of the origin vertex
Two or more pairs of values follow and are the row and column coordinates of the other vertices of the polygon region. Each polygon region is implicitly closed from the last vertex to the origin vertex and all edges shall be non-intersecting except at the vertices. See
The upper left pixel of the image has the coordinate 1\1.
Required if the pixel shift does not apply to the entire set of pixels of the frames.

C.11.20-1.table_caption: XA/XRF Presentation State Shutter Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Frame Display Shutter Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of shutter specifications to be applied to groups of frames.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if shutters in this Item do not apply to all the images and frames listed in the

C.11.21-1.table_caption: XA/XRF Presentation State Presentation Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Multi-frame Presentation Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes for one or more SOP Instances the recommended playback and display preferences.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if display sequences in this Item do not apply to all the images listed in the

table_lines.name: >Preferred Playback Sequencing
table_lines.comment: Describes the preferred playback sequencing for a multi-frame image.

table_lines.name: >Frame Display Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that specifies the display frame rate of a selected set of frames. The Items are ordered in increasing frame number. The range of the frames may not overlap and the ranges shall be adjacent.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Start Trim
table_lines.comment: The Frame Number of the first frame of the set of frames to be displayed in this Item.

table_lines.name: >>Stop Trim
table_lines.comment: The Frame Number of the last frame of the set of frames to be displayed in this Item.

table_lines.name: >>Skip Frame Range Flag
table_lines.comment: A flag indicating that the range of frames in this Item may be skipped.

table_lines.name: >>Recommended Display Frame Rate in Float
table_lines.comment: Recommended rate at which the frames of this Item should be displayed in frames/second.

table_lines.name: >>Recommended Viewing Mode
table_lines.comment: Specifies the recommended viewing protocol(s).

table_lines.name: >>Display Filter Percentage
table_lines.comment: Edge enhancement filter percentage that is recommended by the pixel data creator as filter presetting for display purposes. The value of 100 corresponds to the maximum filter strength that can be applied by a specific application displaying the image.

table_lines.name: >>Mask Visibility Percentage
table_lines.comment: Required if Recommended Viewing Mode (0028,1090) equals SUB.

C.11.22-1.table_caption: Volumetric Presentation State Identification Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Presentation Creation Date
table_lines.comment: Date on which this presentation was created.

table_lines.name: Presentation Creation Time
table_lines.comment: Time at which this presentation was created.

table_lines.name: Rendered Image Reference Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A rendered representation of the view described by this Presentation State.
Only one Item shall be present in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: Presentation Display Collection UID
table_lines.comment:
Unique identifier of a collection of Presentation State Instances that are intended by the Presentation State creator to be processed or displayed together.
See

table_lines.name: Presentation Sequence Collection UID
table_lines.comment:
Unique identifier of a collection of Presentation State Instances that are sequentially related.
See
Required if Presentation Animation Style (0070,1A01) is present with a value of PRESENTATION_SEQ. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Presentation Sequence Position Index
table_lines.comment:
Ordinal position of this Presentation State within a Presentation Sequence Collection. Shall be a monotonically increasing integer, starting from 1, incrementing by 1, unique within the Instances sharing the same value of Presentation Sequence Collection UID (0070,1102).
See
Required if Presentation Sequence Collection UID (0070,1102) is present.

C.11.23-1.table_caption: Volumetric Presentation State Relationship Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Volumetric Presentation Input Set Sequence
table_lines.comment: Input sets specified for use by this Volumetric Presentation State.

table_lines.name: >Volumetric Presentation Input Set UID
table_lines.comment:
Unique identifier of this input specification.
See

table_lines.name: >Presentation Input Type
table_lines.comment:
Type of input.
See

table_lines.name: >Referenced Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The set of images comprising this input volume. One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
See
Required if Presentation Input Type (0070,1202) has a value of VOLUME.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Spatial Registration Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A reference to a Spatial Registration Instance that is used to register the referenced inputs.
Only one Item shall be included in this Sequence. All images referenced by the Referenced Image Sequence (0008,1140) of this Item of the Volumetric Presentation State Input Sequence (0070,1201) shall be referenced by the Spatial Registration Instance.
See
Required if the Frame of Reference UID (0020,0052) value of the Images referenced by the Referenced Image Sequence (0008,1140) of this Item of the Volumetric Presentation State Input Sequence (0070,1201) does not match the Frame of Reference UID (0020,0052) value of this Presentation State Instance. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Volumetric Presentation State Input Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Inputs to the Presentation State.
Each Item represents one input.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Volumetric Presentation Input Number
table_lines.comment: Identification number of the input. Values shall be ordinal numbers starting from 1 and monotonically increasing by 1 within the Volumetric Presentation State Instance.

table_lines.name: >Volumetric Presentation Input Set UID
table_lines.comment:
Unique identifier of this input in Volumetric Presentation Input Set Sequence (0070,120A).
The UID may be shared among multiple Volumetric Presentation State Input Sequence (0070,1201) Items.
See

table_lines.name: >Input Sequence Position Index
table_lines.comment:
Position of this input data within a set of sequential inputs. Multiple inputs may share the same value.
Distinct values shall be ordinal numbers starting from 1 and monotonically increasing by 1 within the Volumetric Presentation State Instance.
See
Required if Presentation Animation Style (0070,1A01) is present with a value of INPUT_SEQ.

table_lines.name: >Crop
table_lines.comment:
Specifies whether to apply per-input cropping to this input.
See

table_lines.name: >Cropping Specification Index
table_lines.comment:
Values of Cropping Specification Number (0070,1309) of the Item in the Volume Cropping Sequence (0070,1301) specifying the cropping methods to be applied to this input.
Required if Crop (0070,1204) has a value of YES.

table_lines.name: >Rendering Method
table_lines.comment:
The rendering method for this input.
Required if MPR Thickness Type (0070,1502) is present with a value of SLAB.

table_lines.name: Global Crop
table_lines.comment:
Specifies whether to apply the cropping specified by Global Cropping Specification Index (0070,120C) to every input of the Volumetric Presentation State.
See

table_lines.name: Global Cropping Specification Index
table_lines.comment:
Values of Cropping Specification Number (0070,1309) of one or more Items in the Volume Cropping Sequence (0070,1301) specifying the cropping methods to be applied to every input.
Volume Cropping Method (0070,1302) shall include only BOUNDING_BOX or OBLIQUE_PLANE values.
Required if Global Crop (0070,120B) has a value of YES.

table_lines.name: Volume Cropping Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Regions cropped from volumetric presentation inputs.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Cropping Specification Number
table_lines.comment: Identification number of the cropping specification, as an ordinal number starting from 1 and monotonically increasing by 1 within the Volumetric Presentation State Instance.

table_lines.name: >Volume Cropping Method
table_lines.comment:
Method of volume cropping applied.
See

table_lines.name: >Bounding Box Crop
table_lines.comment:
A cuboid containing the source volume data to be included. The axes of the cuboid are aligned to the axes of encoded source volume. The bounding box is defined by the (x,y,z) coordinates in mm of two opposite corners in the Volumetric Presentation State Reference Coordinate System.
Required if Volume Cropping Method (0070,1302) has a value of BOUNDING_BOX.

table_lines.name: >Oblique Cropping Plane Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Oblique cropping planes that contain the source volume data to be included.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Volume Cropping Method (0070,1302) has a value of OBLIQUE.

table_lines.name: >>Plane
table_lines.comment: A plane described by a four-tuple (A,B,C,D) describing coordinates in mm of the plane equation Ax+By+Cz+D=0 relative to the Volumetric Presentation State Reference Coordinate System.

table_lines.name: >>Plane Normal
table_lines.comment: Vector of the normal to the plane pointing outside of the volume to be included, encoded as x, y and z values of a unit vector (direction cosine) in the Volumetric Presentation State Reference Coordinate System.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Instances of the Segmentation Storage SOP Class (1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.66.4) containing segments specifying the included or excluded source volume data.
Each referenced Segmentation Instance shall have Segmentation Type (0062,0001) value of BINARY and shall share a Frame of Reference with one or more Input Volumes.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Volume Cropping Method (0070,1302) has a value of INCLUDE_SEG or EXCLUDE_SEG.

table_lines.name: View Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes this view of the patient anatomy.
No more than one Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >View Modifier Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
View modifier.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Image Laterality
table_lines.comment:
Laterality of (possibly paired) body part (as described in Anatomic Region Sequence (0008,2218) ) examined.
Shall be consistent with any laterality information contained in Primary Anatomic Structure Modifier Sequence (0008,2230), if present.

table_lines.name: Multi-Planar Reconstruction Style
table_lines.comment: Style of the MPR view.

table_lines.name: MPR Thickness Type
table_lines.comment:
Specifies whether the Multi-Planar Reconstruction surface has thickness.
See

table_lines.name: MPR Slab Thickness
table_lines.comment:
Thickness of the Multi-Planar Reconstruction slab as a value greater than zero, in mm.
See
Required if MPR Thickness Type (0070,1502) has a value of SLAB.

table_lines.name: MPR View Width Direction
table_lines.comment:
Direction cosine (x,y,z) indicating the direction within the VPS RCS of the top row of the MPR view.
See
Required if Multi Planar Reconstruction Style (0070,1501) is PLANAR.

table_lines.name: MPR View Width
table_lines.comment:
Width of the MPR view, in mm.
See
Required if Multi Planar Reconstruction Style (0070,1501) is PLANAR.

table_lines.name: MPR View Height Direction
table_lines.comment:
Direction cosine (x,y,z) indicating the direction within the VPS RCS of the leftmost column of the MPR view.
See
Required if Multi Planar Reconstruction Style (0070,1501) is PLANAR.

table_lines.name: MPR View Height
table_lines.comment:
Height of the MPR view, in mm.
See
Required if Multi Planar Reconstruction Style (0070,1501) is PLANAR.

table_lines.name: MPR Top Left Hand Corner
table_lines.comment:
The 3D location in the Volumetric Presentation State - Reference Coordinate System of the upper left hand corner of the MPR View rectangle, in mm.
See
Required if Multi-Planar Reconstruction Style (0070,1501) has a value of PLANAR.

C.11.27-1.table_caption: MPR Volumetric Presentation State Display Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Pixel Presentation
table_lines.comment: Grayscale or color space of the Presentation State output.

table_lines.name: Presentation State Classification Component Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of classification components in which the order of Items is significant. Each classification component converts one or two processed inputs into a single RGB output.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
See
Required if Pixel Presentation (0008,9205) has a value of TRUE_COLOR.

table_lines.name: >Component Type
table_lines.comment:
Type of component.
See

table_lines.name: >Component Input Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Description of the input or inputs to this component.
One Item shall be present in this Sequence if Component Type (0070,1802) has a value of ONE_TO_RGBA.
Two Items shall be present in this Sequence if Component Type (0070,1802) has a value of TWO_TO_RGBA.

table_lines.name: >>Volumetric Presentation Input Index
table_lines.comment: Value of Volumetric Presentation Input Number (0070,1207) for this input in the Volumetric Presentation State Input Sequence (0070,1201).

table_lines.name: >>Bits Mapped to Color Lookup Table
table_lines.comment:
The number of most significant bits of each value of Pixel Data (7FE0,0010) from this frame contributing to the Palette Color Lookup Table input.
If absent, Bits Stored (0028,0101) bits of each value of Pixel Data (7FE0,0010) from this frame contributes to the Palette Color Lookup Table input.
See

table_lines.name: >RGB LUT Transfer Function
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the mapping that takes place between the input value and RGB output.
See

table_lines.name: >Alpha LUT Transfer Function
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the transformation that is used to create the Alpha input a compositor component.
Required if the number of Items in Presentation State Classification Component Sequence (0070,1801) is greater than 1.

table_lines.name: >Red Palette Color Lookup Table Descriptor
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the format of the Red Palette Color Lookup Table Data (0028,1201).
The second value (first stored pixel value mapped) shall be zero.
See
Required if RGB LUT Transfer Function (0028,140F) has a value of TABLE.

table_lines.name: >Green Palette Color Lookup Table Descriptor
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the format of the Green Palette Color Lookup Table Data (0028,1202).
The second value (first stored pixel value mapped) shall be zero.
See
Required if RGB LUT Transfer Function (0028,140F) has a value of TABLE.

table_lines.name: >Blue Palette Color Lookup Table Descriptor
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the format of the Blue Palette Color Lookup Table Data (0028,1203).
The second value (first stored pixel value mapped) shall be zero.
See
Required if RGB LUT Transfer Function (0028,140F) has a value of TABLE.

table_lines.name: >Alpha Palette Color Lookup Table Descriptor
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the format of the Alpha Palette Color Lookup Table Data.
The second value (first stored pixel value mapped) shall be zero.
See
Required if Alpha LUT Transfer Function (0028,1410) has a value of TABLE.

table_lines.name: >Palette Color Lookup Table UID
table_lines.comment:
Palette Color Lookup Table UID.
See

table_lines.name: >Red Palette Color Lookup Table Data
table_lines.comment:
Red Palette Color Lookup Table Data.
See
Required if RGB LUT Transfer Function (0028,140F) has a value of TABLE and Segmented Red Palette Color Lookup Table Data (0028,1221) is not present.

table_lines.name: >Green Palette Color Lookup Table Data
table_lines.comment:
Green Palette Color Lookup Table Data.
See
Required if Red Palette Color Lookup Table Data (0028,1201) is present.

table_lines.name: >Blue Palette Color Lookup Table Data
table_lines.comment:
Blue Palette Color Lookup Table Data.
See
Required if Red Palette Color Lookup Table Data (0028,1201) is present.

table_lines.name: >Alpha Palette Color Lookup Table Data
table_lines.comment:
Alpha LUT contains the blending values for the data frames.
See
Required if Alpha LUT Transfer Function (0028,1410) has a value of TABLE and Segmented Alpha Palette Color Lookup Table Data (0028,1224) is not present.

table_lines.name: >Segmented Red Palette Color Lookup Table Data
table_lines.comment:
Segmented Red Palette Color Lookup Table Data.
See
Required if RGB LUT Transfer Function (0028,140F) has a value of TABLE and Red Palette Color Lookup Table Data (0028,1201) is not present.

table_lines.name: >Segmented Green Palette Color Lookup Table Data
table_lines.comment:
Segmented Green Palette Color Lookup Table Data.
See
Required if Segmented Red Palette Color Lookup Table Data (0028,1221) is present.

table_lines.name: >Segmented Blue Palette Color Lookup Table Data
table_lines.comment:
Segmented Blue Palette Color Lookup Table Data.
See
Required if Segmented Red Palette Color Lookup Table Data (0028,1221) is present.

table_lines.name: >Segmented Alpha Palette Color Lookup Table Data
table_lines.comment:
Segmented Alpha Palette Color Lookup Table Data.
See
Required if Alpha LUT Transfer Function (0028,1410) has a value of TABLE and Alpha Palette Color Lookup Table Data (0028,1204) is not present.

table_lines.name: Presentation State Compositor Component Sequence
table_lines.comment:
RGB Compositor components. Each RGB Compositor component combines pairs of RGB values to produce a single RGB value.
The order of Items is significant. If there is more than one compositor component, the components are chained such that the output of one compositor component is an input to the next compositor component.
The number of Items in this Sequence shall be one less than the number of Items in Presentation State Classification Component Sequence (0070,1801).
See
Required if Pixel Presentation (0008,9205) has a value of TRUE_COLOR.

table_lines.name: >Weighting Transfer Function Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Transfer functions used to derive the weighting factors for each of the two RGB inputs from both input Alphas. Each function is represented by the formula
f(Alpha

The function is specified in the form of a table.
Two Items shall be included in this Sequence.
The order is significant. The first Item specifies the weighting factor for RGB1 and the second Item specifies the weighting factor for RGB2.
See

table_lines.name: >>LUT Descriptor
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the format of the LUT Data (0028,3006) in this Sequence.
The first value (number of entries in the LUT) shall be an even power of two or zero indicating 2
The third value (number of bits in the LUT Data) shall be 8.
See

table_lines.name: >>LUT Data
table_lines.comment: LUT Data.

table_lines.name: Presentation LUT Shape
table_lines.comment:
Presentation LUT transformation.
See
Required if Pixel Presentation (0008,9205) has a value of MONOCHROME.

table_lines.name: ICC Profile
table_lines.comment:
An ICC Profile encoding the transformation of device-dependent color stored pixel values into PCS-Values.
When present, defines the color space of the output of the Volumetric Presentation State.
See
Required if Pixel Presentation (0008,9205) has a value of TRUE_COLOR.

table_lines.name: Color Space
table_lines.comment:
A label that identifies the well-known color space of the view.
Shall be consistent with the ICC Profile (0028,2000) that is present.
Required if Pixel Presentation (0008,9205) has a value of TRUE_COLOR and a standard color space described by one of the Enumerated Values in

table_lines.name: Volumetric Annotation Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Graphic annotations described by coordinates in the Volumetric Presentation State Reference Coordinate System.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Volumetric Presentation Input Annotation Sequence (0070,1905) is not present. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Graphic Data
table_lines.comment:
An ordered set of (x,y,z) triplets (in mm and may be negative) that define a region of interest in the Volumetric Presentation State Reference Coordinate System defined by Frame of Reference UID (0020,0052).
See

table_lines.name: >Graphic Layer
table_lines.comment: sect_C.10.7

table_lines.name: >Annotation Clipping
table_lines.comment:
Specifies whether the volumetric annotation should be displayed only when it intersects with the presentation view.
See

table_lines.name: >Text Object Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that describes a text annotation.
One Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Unformatted Text Value
table_lines.comment:
Displayed text associated with the input Instance.
See

table_lines.name: >>Bounding Box Top Left Hand Corner
table_lines.comment: Recommended location of the Top Left Hand Corner (TLHC) of the bounding box in which Unformatted Text Value (0070,0006) is to be placed within a Volumetric Presentation View, specified as fractions of the view width and view height. Each value shall be within the range 0.0 to 1.0.

table_lines.name: >>Bounding Box Bottom Right Hand Corner
table_lines.comment:
Recommended location of the Bottom Right Hand Corner (BRHC) of the bounding box in which Unformatted Text Value (0070,0006) is to be placed within a Volumetric Presentation View, specified as fractions of the view width and view height. Each value shall be within the range 0.0 to 1.0.
Required if Bounding Box Top Left Hand Corner (0070,0010) is present.

table_lines.name: >>Bounding Box Text Horizontal Justification
table_lines.comment:
Location of the Unformatted Test Value (0070,0006) relative to the vertical edges of the bounding box.
Required if Bounding Box Top Left Hand Corner (0070,0010) is present.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Structured Context Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Reference to a node in a Structured Report Instance providing context for this annotation.
Only one Item shall be present in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >>Referenced Content Item
table_lines.comment: Reference to a Content Item in the referenced Structured Report specified as the Observation UID (0040,A171) of the Content Item.

table_lines.name: Volumetric Presentation Input Annotation Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Annotations of inputs in Volumetric Presentation State Input Sequence (0070,1201).
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Volumetric Annotation Sequence (0070,1901) is not present. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: > Volumetric Presentation Input Index
table_lines.comment: Value of Volumetric Presentation Input Number (0070,1207) for this input in the Volumetric Presentation State Input Sequence (0070,1201).

table_lines.name: >Graphic Layer
table_lines.comment: sect_C.10.7

table_lines.name: >Text Object Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that describes a text annotation.
One Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Unformatted Text Value
table_lines.comment:
Displayed text associated with the input.
See

table_lines.name: >>Bounding Box Top Left Hand Corner
table_lines.comment:
Recommended location of the Top Left Hand Corner (TLHC) of the bounding box in which Unformatted Text Value (0070,0006) is to be displayed, as fractions of the specified presentation view width and height. Each value shall be within the range 0.0 to 1.0.
See

table_lines.name: >>Bounding Box Bottom Right Hand Corner
table_lines.comment:
Recommended location of the Bottom Right Hand Corner (BRHC) of the bounding box in which Unformatted Text Value (0070,0006) is to be displayed, as fractions of the specified presentation view width and height. Each value shall be within the range 0.0 to 1.0.
See
Required if Bounding Box Top Left Hand Corner (0070,0010) is present.

table_lines.name: >>Bounding Box Text Horizontal Justification
table_lines.comment:
Location of the Unformatted Test Value (0070,0006) relative to the vertical edges of the bounding box.
See
Required if Bounding Box Top Left Hand Corner (0070,0010) is present.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Structured Context Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Reference to a node in a Structured Report Instance providing context for this annotation.
Only one Item shall be present in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >>Referenced Content Item
table_lines.comment: Reference to a Content Item in the referenced Structured Report specified as the Observation UID (0040,A171) of the Content Item.

table_lines.name: Presentation Animation Style
table_lines.comment:
Animation style intended by the source.
See

table_lines.name: Recommended Animation Rate
table_lines.comment:
Recommended rate at which the inputs shall be displayed. Shall have a value greater than zero.
See

table_lines.name: Animation Curve Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Curve describing the trajectory of a fly-through animation.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Presentation Animation Style (0070,1A01) has a value of CROSSCURVE or FLYTHROUGH.

table_lines.name: >Number of Volumetric Curve Points
table_lines.comment: Number of (x,y,z) points in Volumetric Curve Points (0070,150D).

table_lines.name: >Volumetric Curve Points
table_lines.comment:
Coordinates of points on the curve in the Volumetric Presentation State Reference Coordinate System, in mm. One triplet (x,y,z) shall be present for each point in the curve.
See

table_lines.name: >Volumetric Curve Up Directions
table_lines.comment:
Direction cosines (x
See
Required if Presentation Animation Style (0070,1A01) has a value of FLYTHROUGH.

table_lines.name: Animation Step Size
table_lines.comment:
Distance in mm along the curve the display moves in one step.
Required if Presentation Animation Style (0070,1A01) has a value of CROSSCURVE or FLYTHROUGH.

table_lines.name: Swivel Range
table_lines.comment:
Range in which a volume rotates back-and-forth around the swivel axis, in degrees. The initial position is at the midpoint of the swivel range.
See
Required if Presentation Animation Style (0070,1A01) is SWIVEL.

table_lines.name: Render Projection
table_lines.comment: Projection style.

table_lines.name: Viewpoint Position
table_lines.comment:
Position of the viewpoint in volume space.
A point (x,y,z) in the Volumetric Presentation State Reference Coordinate System.

table_lines.name: Viewpoint LookAt Point
table_lines.comment:
Point the viewpoint is looking at.
A point (x,y,z) in the Volumetric Presentation State Reference Coordinate System.

table_lines.name: Viewpoint Up Direction
table_lines.comment:
Vertical orientation of the view.
A vector (x,y,z) in the Volumetric Presentation State Reference Coordinate System.

table_lines.name: Render Field of View
table_lines.comment:
The field of view specified as a 6-tuple of values (X
See

table_lines.name: Rendering Method
table_lines.comment: The rendering method used during the ray casting compositing operation.

table_lines.name: Sampling Step Size
table_lines.comment:
Spacing in mm between samples along each ray in the original volume rendering operation.
See

table_lines.name: Shading Style
table_lines.comment:
The style of shading.
See

table_lines.name: Ambient Reflection Intensity
table_lines.comment: Intensity of the ambient reflection in the relative range 0.0 to 1.0, inclusive.

table_lines.name: Light Direction
table_lines.comment:
The direction light is traveling from a single white light source at infinity. Represented as a unit vector encoded as three coordinates (x,y,z) in the VPS-RCS.
Required if Diffuse Reflection Intensity (0070,1704) or Specular Reflection Intensity (0070,1705) is present.

table_lines.name: Diffuse Reflection Intensity
table_lines.comment:
Intensity of the diffuse reflection in the relative range 0.0 to 1.0, inclusive.
If absent, a value of zero is assumed.

table_lines.name: Specular Reflection Intensity
table_lines.comment:
Intensity of the specular reflection in the relative range 0.0 to 1.0, inclusive.
If absent, a value of zero is assumed.

table_lines.name: Shininess
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the roughness of the rendered surfaces, in the relative range 0.0 to 1.0, inclusive. A value of 0.0 represents a rough surface and a value of 1.0 represents the smoothest surface which can be generated by the implementation.
If absent, the shininess is an implementation decision.

table_lines.name: Pixel Presentation
table_lines.comment: Grayscale or color space of the Presentation State output.

table_lines.name: Volume Stream Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Volumetric source input streams combined through Volume Blending.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Volumetric Presentation Input Set UID
table_lines.comment:
Unique identifier of the input set processed in this volume stream. Corresponds to the Item in Volume Presentation Input Set Sequence (0070,120A) with this UID.
See

table_lines.name: >Presentation State Classification Component Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Classification components in which the order of Items is significant. Each classification component converts one or two processed inputs into a single RGB output.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >>RGBA Transfer Function Description
table_lines.comment: Label describing the clinical significance of the RGBA transfer function.

table_lines.name: >>Component Type
table_lines.comment:
Type of component.
See

table_lines.name: >>Component Input Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Specification of the input or inputs to this component.
One Item shall be present in this Sequence if Component Type (0070,1802) has a value of ONE_TO_RGBA.
Two Items shall be present in this Sequence if Component Type (0070,1802) has a value of TWO_TO_RGBA.

table_lines.name: >>> Volumetric Presentation Input Index
table_lines.comment: Volumetric Presentation Input Number (0070,1207) for this input in the Volumetric Presentation State Input Sequence (0070,1201).

table_lines.name: >>>Bits Mapped to Color Lookup Table
table_lines.comment:
The number of most significant bits of each value of Pixel Data (7FE0,0010) from this frame contributing to the Palette Color Lookup Table input.
If absent, Bits Stored (0028,0101) bits of each value of Pixel Data (7FE0,0010) from this frame contributes to the Palette Color Lookup Table input.
See

table_lines.name: >>RGB LUT Transfer Function
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the mapping that takes place between the input value and RGB output.
See

table_lines.name: >>Alpha LUT Transfer Function
table_lines.comment: Specifies the transformation that is used to create the Alpha input to a compositor component (if present) and the opacity value for use in the Volume Rendering compositor.

table_lines.name: >>Red Palette Color Lookup Table Descriptor
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the format of the Red Palette Color Lookup Table Data (0028,1201).
The second value (first stored pixel value mapped) shall be zero.
See
Required if RGB LUT Transfer Function (0028,140F) has a value of TABLE.

table_lines.name: >>Green Palette Color Lookup Table Descriptor
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the format of the Green Palette Color Lookup Table Data (0028,1202).
The second value (first stored pixel value mapped) shall be zero.
See
Required if RGB LUT Transfer Function (0028,140F) has a value of TABLE.

table_lines.name: >>Blue Palette Color Lookup Table Descriptor
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the format of the Blue Palette Color Lookup Table Data (0028,1203).
The second value (first stored pixel value mapped) shall be zero.
See
Required if RGB LUT Transfer Function (0028,140F) has a value of TABLE.

table_lines.name: >>Alpha Palette Color Lookup Table Descriptor
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the format of the Alpha Palette Color Lookup Table Data.
The second value (first stored pixel value mapped) shall be zero.
See
Required if Alpha LUT Transfer Function (0028,1410) has a value of TABLE.

table_lines.name: >>Palette Color Lookup Table UID
table_lines.comment:
Palette Color Lookup Table UID.
See

table_lines.name: >>Red Palette Color Lookup Table Data
table_lines.comment:
Red Palette Color Lookup Table Data.
See
Required if RGB LUT Transfer Function (0028,140F) has a value of TABLE and Segmented Red Palette Color Lookup Table Data (0028,1221) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Green Palette Color Lookup Table Data
table_lines.comment:
Green Palette Color Lookup Table Data.
See
Required if Red Palette Color Lookup Table Data (0028,1201) is present.

table_lines.name: >>Blue Palette Color Lookup Table Data
table_lines.comment:
Blue Palette Color Lookup Table Data.
See
Required if Red Palette Color Lookup Table Data (0028,1201) is present.

table_lines.name: >>Alpha Palette Color Lookup Table Data
table_lines.comment:
Alpha Palette Color Lookup Table Data.
See
Required if Alpha LUT Transfer Function (0028,1410) has a value of TABLE and Segmented Alpha Palette Color Lookup Table Data (0028,1224) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Segmented Red Palette Color Lookup Table Data
table_lines.comment:
Segmented Red Palette Color Lookup Table Data.
See
Required if RGB LUT Transfer Function (0028,140F) has a value of TABLE and Red Palette Color Lookup Table Data (0028,1201) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Segmented Green Palette Color Lookup Table Data
table_lines.comment:
Segmented Green Palette Color Lookup Table Data.
See
Required if Segmented Red Palette Color Lookup Table Data (0028,1221) is present.

table_lines.name: >>Segmented Blue Palette Color Lookup Table Data
table_lines.comment:
Segmented Blue Palette Color Lookup Table Data.
See
Required if Segmented Red Palette Color Lookup Table Data (0028,1221) is present.

table_lines.name: >>Segmented Alpha Palette Color Lookup Table Data
table_lines.comment:
Segmented Alpha Palette Color Lookup Table Data.
See
Required if Alpha LUT Transfer Function (0028,1410) has a value of TABLE and Alpha Palette Color Lookup Table Data (0028,1204) is not present.

table_lines.name: Presentation State Compositor Component Sequence
table_lines.comment:
RGBA Compositor components. Each RGBA Compositor component combines pairs of RGBA values to produce a single RGBA value.
The order of Items is significant. If there are more than one compositor component, the components are chained such that the output of one compositor component is an input to the next compositor component.
The number of Items in this Sequence shall be the one less than the number of Items in Volume Stream Sequence (0070,1A08).
See

table_lines.name: >Weighting Transfer Function Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Transfer functions used to derive the weighting factors for each of the two RGB inputs from both input Alphas.
Each function is represented by the formula
f(Alpha

The function is specified in the form of a table.
Two Items shall be included in this Sequence.
The order is significant. The first Item specifies the weighting factor for RGB1 and the second Item specifies the weighting factor for RGB2.
See

table_lines.name: >>LUT Descriptor
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the format of the LUT Data (0028,3006) in this Sequence.
The first value (number of entries in the LUT) shall be an even power of two or zero indicating 2
The third value (number of bits in the LUT Data) shall be 8.
See

table_lines.name: >>LUT Data
table_lines.comment: LUT Data.

table_lines.name: ICC Profile
table_lines.comment:
An ICC Profile encoding the transformation of device-dependent color stored pixel values into PCS-Values.
When present, defines the color space of the output of the Volumetric Presentation State.
See
Required if Pixel Presentation (0008,9205) has a value of TRUE_COLOR.

table_lines.name: Color Space
table_lines.comment:
A label that identifies the well-known color space of the view.
Shall be consistent with the ICC Profile (0028,2000) that is present.
Required if Pixel Presentation (0008,9205) has a value of TRUE_COLOR and a standard color space described by one of the Enumerated Values in

C.11.33-1.table_caption: Advanced Blending Presentation State Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Advanced Blending Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence of Items identifying the inputs and describing transformations of them.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >Blending Input Number
table_lines.comment: Identification number of the input. Values shall be ordinal numbers starting from 1 and monotonically increasing by 1 within the Advanced Blending Presentation State Instance.

table_lines.name: >Study Instance UID
table_lines.comment: Unique identifier for the Study.

table_lines.name: >Series Instance UID
table_lines.comment: Unique identifier of a Series that is part of the Study defined by the Study Instance UID (0020,000D).

table_lines.name: >Referenced Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The set of images comprising this input. One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if the input is not the entire set of Instances in the Series.

table_lines.name: >>Referenced Optical Path Identifier
table_lines.comment:
A single value that identifies the optical path that is the input.
Refers to the value in Optical Path Identifier (0048,0106) within the Optical Path Sequence (0048,0105) in the images to which this Presentation State applies.
Required if more than one Optical Path is present in the images to which this Presentation State applies.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Spatial Registration Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A reference to a Spatial Registration Instance that is used to register the referenced inputs.
Only one Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if the Frame of Reference UID (0020,0052) value of the Images referenced by the Referenced Image Sequence (0008,1140) of this Item does not match the Frame of Reference UID (0020,0052) value of this Presentation State Instance. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Softcopy VOI LUT Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Defines a Sequence of VOI LUTs or Window Centers and Widths and to which images and frames they apply.
No more than one VOI LUT Sequence containing a single Item or one pair of Window Center/Width values shall be specified for each image or frame.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if a VOI LUT is to be applied to referenced image(s) and the Threshold Sequence (0070,1B11) is not present. May be present otherwise if the referenced image(s) are grayscale.

table_lines.name: >>Referenced Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items identifying images and optical paths that are defined in the enclosing Item of Advanced Blending Sequence (0070,1B01), to which this VOI LUT or Window Center and Width applies.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if the VOI LUT transformation in this Item does not apply to all the images and frames and optical paths listed in the enclosing Item.

table_lines.name: >>>Referenced Optical Path Identifier
table_lines.comment:
A single value that identifies the optical path that is the input.
Refers to the value in Optical Path Identifier (0048,0106) within the Optical Path Sequence (0048,0105) in the images to which this Presentation State applies.
Required if there is more than one Optical Path in the images to which the this reference applies.

table_lines.name: >Palette Color Lookup Table Sequence
table_lines.comment:
For grayscale input images, provides a transform of the pixel values into an RGB color representation.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.
