Required if the input is a grayscale image and a palette color transformation is to be applied rather than the default transformation to equal RGB values. See

table_lines.name: >Time Series Blending
table_lines.comment:
Whether this Series is a time series and every time point in this Series will be blended with the single volumes in the other Series specified in the Advanced Blending Sequence (0070,1B01).
Only a single Item in the Sequence may have the value TRUE
Required if the input is a Time Series and all time points need to be blended with the other Series. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Geometry for Display
table_lines.comment:
Whether the geometry of this Series is used as the geometry for the blending operation.
See
Only a single Item in the Sequence may have the value TRUE
Required if the geometry of this input is to be used as the geometry for the blending operation. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Threshold Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Threshold specification for the image
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Threshold needs to be applied and the Softcopy VOI LUT Sequence (0028,3110) is not present. May be present otherwise if Threshold needs to be applied.

table_lines.name: >Threshold Type
table_lines.comment:
Type of threshold comparison used to determine the presence of a pixel value in the output.
See

table_lines.name: >Threshold Value Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Values for thresholding.
If the Threshold Type (0070,1B13) is GREATER_OR_EQUAL, LESS_OR_EQUAL, GREATER_THAN or LESS_THAN only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
If the Threshold Type (0070,1B13) is RANGE_INCL or RANGE_EXCL, exactly two Items shall be included in this Sequence, the first of which is less than or equal to the second.

table_lines.name: >>Threshold Value
table_lines.comment:
Value for the threshold.
See

C.11.34.1-1.table_caption: Advanced Blending Presentation State Display Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Pixel Presentation
table_lines.comment: Grayscale or color space of the Presentation State output.

table_lines.name: Blending Display Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The blending operations and the input series to be used. Each Item results in a single RGB output that may be reused in a following step.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Blending Display Input Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Each Item is an input series that will be used in the blending operation.
The order of Items is significant
Two Items shall be included if the blending mode is FOREGROUND.
One or more Items shall be included if the blending mode is EQUAL.

table_lines.name: >>Blending Input Number
table_lines.comment: Identification number of the input series to which the Blending information must be applied.

table_lines.name: >Relative Opacity
table_lines.comment:
Specifies Relative Opacity for the visible pixels of the set referenced by the first Blending Input Number (0070,1B02)
Required if Blending Mode (0070,1B06) is equal to FOREGROUND.

table_lines.name: >Blending Mode
table_lines.comment:
Describes the method for weighting the different input images during the blending operation:
See

table_lines.name: >Blending Input Number
table_lines.comment:
Identification of the result as input for a subsequent blending operation.
Required if the result is used for further Blending.

table_lines.name: Variable Modality LUT Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Modality LUTs or Rescale Slopes and Intercepts for specific images and frames.
Any given image or frame shall not be referenced in more than one item of this Sequence.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Image Sequence
table_lines.comment: One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Specific Character Set
table_lines.comment:
Character Set that expands or replaces the Basic Graphic Set.
Required if an expanded or replacement character set is used.
See

table_lines.name: Instance Creation Date
table_lines.comment:
Date the SOP Instance was created.
This is the date that the SOP Instance UID was assigned, and does not change during subsequent coercion of the Instance.

table_lines.name: Instance Creation Time
table_lines.comment:
Time the SOP Instance was created.
This is the time that the SOP Instance UID was assigned, and does not change during subsequent coercion of the Instance.

table_lines.name: Instance Coercion DateTime
table_lines.comment: Date and time that the SOP Instance was last coerced, corrected or converted by a Storage SCP (see

table_lines.name: Instance Creator UID
table_lines.comment: Uniquely identifies device that created the SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: Related General SOP Class UID
table_lines.comment: Uniquely identifies a Related General SOP Class for the SOP Class of this Instance. See

table_lines.name: Original Specialized SOP Class UID
table_lines.comment: The SOP Class in which the Instance was originally encoded that has been replaced during a fall-back conversion to the current Related General SOP Class. See

table_lines.name: Coding Scheme Identification Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items that map values of Coding Scheme Designator (0008,0102) to an external coding system registration, or to a private or local coding scheme.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Coding Scheme Designator
table_lines.comment: The value of a Coding Scheme Designator, used in this SOP Instance, which is being mapped.

table_lines.name: >Coding Scheme Registry
table_lines.comment: The name of the external registry where further definition of the identified coding scheme may be obtained. Required if coding scheme is registered.

table_lines.name: >Coding Scheme UID
table_lines.comment: The coding scheme UID identifier. Required if coding scheme is identified by an ISO 8824 object identifier compatible with the UI VR.

table_lines.name: >Coding Scheme External ID
table_lines.comment: The coding scheme identifier as defined in an external registry. Required if coding scheme is registered and Coding Scheme UID (0008,010C) is not present.

table_lines.name: >Coding Scheme Name
table_lines.comment: The coding scheme full common name.

table_lines.name: >Coding Scheme Version
table_lines.comment: The coding scheme version associated with the Coding Scheme Designator (0008,0102).

table_lines.name: >Coding Scheme Responsible Organization
table_lines.comment: Name of the organization responsible for the Coding Scheme. May include organizational contact information.

table_lines.name: >Coding Scheme Resources Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Resources related to the coding scheme.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Coding Scheme URL Type
table_lines.comment: The type of the resource related to the coding scheme at the Coding Scheme URL (0008,010E).

table_lines.name: >>Coding Scheme URL
table_lines.comment: A resource related to the coding scheme.

table_lines.name: Context Group Identification Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items that map values of Context Identifier (0008,010F) to an external, private or local Context Group.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Context Identifier
table_lines.comment:
The identifier of the Context Group.
See

table_lines.name: >Context UID
table_lines.comment:
The unique identifier of the Context Group.
See

table_lines.name: >Mapping Resource
table_lines.comment:
The identifier of the Mapping Resource that defines the Context Group.
See

table_lines.name: >Context Group Version
table_lines.comment:
The identifier of the version of the Context Group.
See

table_lines.name: Mapping Resource Identification Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items that map values of Mapping Resource (0008,0105) to an external, private or local Mapping Resource.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Mapping Resource
table_lines.comment:
The identifier of the Mapping Resource.
See

table_lines.name: >Mapping Resource UID
table_lines.comment: The unique identifier of the Mapping Resource.

table_lines.name: >Mapping Resource Name
table_lines.comment:
The name of the Mapping Resource.
See

table_lines.name: Timezone Offset From UTC
table_lines.comment:
Contains the offset from UTC to the timezone for all DA and TM Attributes present in this SOP Instance, and for all DT Attributes present in this SOP Instance that do not contain an explicitly encoded timezone offset.
See
The local timezone offset is undefined if this Attribute is absent.

table_lines.name: Contributing Equipment Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items containing descriptive Attributes of related equipment that has contributed to the acquisition, creation or modification of the Composite Instance.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >Purpose of Reference Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes the purpose for which the related equipment is being referenced.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >Manufacturer
table_lines.comment: Manufacturer of the equipment that contributed to the Composite Instance.

table_lines.name: >Institution Name
table_lines.comment: Institution where the equipment that contributed to the Composite Instance is located.

table_lines.name: >Institution Address
table_lines.comment: Address of the institution where the equipment that contributed to the Composite Instance is located.

table_lines.name: >Station Name
table_lines.comment: User defined name identifying the machine that contributed to the Composite Instance.

table_lines.name: >Institutional Department Name
table_lines.comment: Department in the institution where the equipment that contributed to the Composite Instance is located.

table_lines.name: >Institutional Department Type Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A coded description of the type of Department or Service within the healthcare facility.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Operators' Name
table_lines.comment: Name(s) of the operator(s) of the contributing equipment.

table_lines.name: >Operator Identification Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identification of the operator(s) of the contributing equipment.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.
The number and order of Items shall correspond to the number and order of values of Operators' Name (0008,1070), if present.

table_lines.name: >Manufacturer's Model Name
table_lines.comment: Manufacturer's model name of the equipment that contributed to the Composite Instance.

table_lines.name: >Device Serial Number
table_lines.comment: Manufacturer's serial number of the equipment that contributed to the Composite Instance.

table_lines.name: >Date of Manufacture
table_lines.comment: The date the equipment that contributed to the Composite Instance was originally manufactured or re-manufactured (as opposed to refurbished).

table_lines.name: >Date of Installation
table_lines.comment: The date the equipment that contributed to the Composite Instance was installed in its current location. The equipment may or may not have been used prior to installation in its current location.

table_lines.name: >Device UID
table_lines.comment: Unique identifier of the contributing equipment.

table_lines.name: >UDI Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Unique Device Identifier (UDI) of the contributing equipment.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Spatial Resolution
table_lines.comment: The inherent limiting resolution in mm of the acquisition equipment for high contrast objects for the data gathering and reconstruction technique chosen. If variable across the images of the Series, the value at the image center.

table_lines.name: >Contribution DateTime
table_lines.comment: The Date & Time when the equipment contributed to the Composite Instance.

table_lines.name: >Contribution Description
table_lines.comment: Description of the contribution the equipment made to the Composite Instance.

table_lines.name: Instance Number
table_lines.comment: A number that identifies this Composite Instance.

table_lines.name: SOP Instance Status
table_lines.comment: A flag that indicates the storage status of the SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: SOP Authorization DateTime
table_lines.comment: The date and time when the SOP Instance Status (0100,0410) was set to AO.

table_lines.name: SOP Authorization Comment
table_lines.comment: Any comments associated with the setting of the SOP Instance Status (0100,0410) to AO.

table_lines.name: Authorization Equipment Certification Number
table_lines.comment: The certification number issued to the Application Entity that set the SOP Instance Status (0100,0410) to AO.

table_lines.name: Encrypted Attributes Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items containing encrypted DICOM data.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if application level confidentiality is needed and certain recipients are allowed to decrypt all or portions of the Encrypted Attributes Data Set. See

table_lines.name: >Encrypted Content Transfer Syntax UID
table_lines.comment: Transfer Syntax used to encode the encrypted content. Only Transfer Syntaxes that explicitly include the VR and use Little Endian encoding shall be used.

table_lines.name: HL7 Structured Document Reference Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items defining mapping between HL7 Instance Identifiers of unencapsulated HL7 Structured Documents referenced from the current SOP Instance as if they were DICOM Composite SOP Instances defined by SOP Class and Instance UID pairs. May also define a means of accessing the Documents.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
See
Required if unencapsulated HL7 Structured Documents are referenced within the Instance. Every such document so referenced is required to have a corresponding Item in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >HL7 Instance Identifier
table_lines.comment: Instance Identifier of the referenced HL7 Structured Document, encoded as a UID (OID or UUID), concatenated with a caret ("^") and Extension value (if Extension is present in Instance Identifier).

table_lines.name: >Retrieve URI
table_lines.comment: biblio_RFC_3986

table_lines.name: Longitudinal Temporal Information Modified
table_lines.comment:
Indicates whether or not the date and time Attributes in the Instance have been modified during de-identification.
See

table_lines.name: Query/Retrieve View
table_lines.comment:
The view requested during the C-MOVE operation that resulted in the transfer of this Instance.
Required if the Instance has ever been converted from its source form as the result of a C-MOVE operation with a specific view.

table_lines.name: Conversion Source Attributes Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The set of images or other composite SOP Instances that were converted to this Instance.
If this Instance was converted from a specific frame in the source Instance, the reference shall include the Frame Number.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if this Instance was created by conversion from a DICOM source, and Conversion Source Attributes Sequence (0020,9172) is not present in an Item of Shared Functional Groups Sequence (5200,9229) or Per-Frame Functional Groups Sequence (5200,9230).

table_lines.name: Content Qualification
table_lines.comment:
Content Qualification Indicator
See

table_lines.name: Private Data Element Characteristics Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Characteristics of Private Data Elements within or referenced in the current SOP Instance.
See
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Private Group Reference
table_lines.comment: Odd group number within which the Private Data Element block is reserved.

table_lines.name: >Private Creator Reference
table_lines.comment: The value of the Private Creator Data Element value used to reserve the block of Private Data Elements whose characteristics are described in this Item.

table_lines.name: >Private Data Element Definition Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Description of individual Private Data Elements.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Private Data Element
table_lines.comment:
Element Number used to identify the Data Element within the reserved block.
The value of this Attribute represents the last two digits of the Data Element Tag; i.e., the value of xx in (gggg,00xx) where gggg is the Private Group Reference (0008,0301).

table_lines.name: >>Private Data Element Value Multiplicity
table_lines.comment:
Value Multiplicity (VM) of the Data Element.
See

table_lines.name: >>Private Data Element Value Representation
table_lines.comment: Value Representation (VR) of the Data Element.

table_lines.name: >>Private Data Element Number of Items
table_lines.comment:
Number of Items allowed in a Sequence Data Element.
Required if the value of Private Data Element Value Representation (0008,030A) is SQ.
See

table_lines.name: >>Private Data Element Keyword
table_lines.comment: Keyword for the Data Element (in the sense of the keywords provided in

table_lines.name: >>Private Data Element Name
table_lines.comment: Name for referring to the Data Element.

table_lines.name: >>Private Data Element Description
table_lines.comment: Description of the purpose and/or proper usage of the Data Element.

table_lines.name: >>Private Data Element Encoding
table_lines.comment: Description of how the Data Element value contents are encoded.

table_lines.name: >>Retrieve URI
table_lines.comment:
Retrieval access path to associated documentation.
Includes fully specified scheme, authority, path, and query in accordance with

table_lines.name: >Block Identifying Information Status
table_lines.comment: Specifies whether some or all of the Private Data Elements in the block are safe from identity leakage as defined by

table_lines.name: >Nonidentifying Private Elements
table_lines.comment:
List of Private Data Elements in block that do not contain identifying information (are safe from identity leakage).
Elements are identified by the lowest 8-bits of the Date Element Tag (i.e., with a value from 0000H to 00FFH) within the block, stored as an unsigned short integer. Multiple values shall be in increasing order and a given value shall be listed at most once.
Required if Block Identifying Information Status (0008,0303) equals MIXED.

table_lines.name: >Deidentification Action Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Actions to be performed on element within the block that are not safe from identify leakage.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Identifying Private Elements
table_lines.comment:
List of Private Data Elements in block that may contain identifying information (are unsafe from identity leakage).
Elements are identified by the lowest 8-bits of the Data Element Tag (i.e., with a value from 0000H to 00FFH) within the block, stored as an unsigned short integer. Multiple values shall be in increasing order and a given value shall be listed at most once.

table_lines.name: >>Deidentification Action
table_lines.comment: Recommended action to be performed during de-identification on elements listed in Identifying Private Elements (0008,0306) within this Item.

table_lines.name: Instance Origin Status
table_lines.comment: Categorizes the locality of the entity from whence the Instance originated.

table_lines.name: Barcode Value
table_lines.comment: Barcode interpreted from a scanned label.

table_lines.name: MAC Parameters Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence of Items that describe the parameters used to calculate a MAC for use in Digital Signatures.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >MAC ID Number
table_lines.comment: A number, unique within this SOP Instance, used to identify this MAC Parameters Sequence (4FFE,0001) Item from an Item of the Digital Signatures Sequence (FFFA,FFFA).

table_lines.name: >MAC Calculation Transfer Syntax UID
table_lines.comment: The Transfer Syntax UID used to encode the values of the Data Elements included in the MAC calculation. Only Transfer Syntaxes that explicitly include the VR and use Little Endian encoding shall be used.

table_lines.name: >MAC Algorithm
table_lines.comment:
The algorithm used in generating the MAC to be encrypted to form the Digital Signature.
For Defined Terms, see

table_lines.name: Digital Signatures Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence holding Digital Signatures.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >MAC ID Number
table_lines.comment: A number used to identify which MAC Parameters Sequence Item was used in the calculation of this Digital Signature.

table_lines.name: >Digital Signature UID
table_lines.comment: A UID that can be used to uniquely reference this signature.

table_lines.name: >Digital Signature DateTime
table_lines.comment: The date and time the Digital Signature was created. The time shall include an offset (i.e., time zone indication) from Coordinated Universal Time.

table_lines.name: >Certificate Type
table_lines.comment: The type of certificate used in (0400,0115).

table_lines.name: >Certificate of Signer
table_lines.comment: A certificate that holds the identity of the entity producing this Digital Signature, that entity's public key or key identifier, and the algorithm and associated parameters with which that public key is to be used. Algorithms allowed are specified in Digital Signature Security Profiles (see

table_lines.name: >Certified Timestamp Type
table_lines.comment: The type of certified timestamp used in Certified Timestamp (0400,0310). Required if Certified Timestamp (0400,0310) is present.

table_lines.name: >Digital Signature Purpose Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The purpose of this Digital Signature.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Modified Attributes Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items containing all Attributes that were removed or replaced by "dummy values" in the top level Data Set during de-identification of the SOP Instance. Upon reversal of the de-identification process, the Attributes are copied back into the top level Data Set, replacing any dummy values that might have been created.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: > Any Attribute from the top level Data Set that was modified or removed during the de-identification process.
Original Attributes Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items containing all Attributes that were added, removed or replaced by other values in the top level Data Set.
See
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Source of Previous Values
table_lines.comment: The source that provided the SOP Instance prior to the removal or replacement of the values. For example, this might be the Institution from which imported SOP Instances were received.

table_lines.name: >Attribute Modification DateTime
table_lines.comment: Date and time the Attributes were replaced, added or removed.

table_lines.name: >Modifying System
table_lines.comment: Identification of the system that replaced, added or removed the Attributes.

table_lines.name: >Reason for the Attribute Modification
table_lines.comment: Reason for the Attribute modification.

table_lines.name: >Modified Attributes Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that contains all the Attributes, with their previous values, that were modified or removed from the top level Data Set.
See
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Any Attribute from the top level Data Set that was modified or removed.
table_lines.comment: May include Sequence Attributes and their Items.

table_lines.name: >Nonconforming Modified Attributes Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Attributes that were replaced or removed from the Data Set because the values were not conformant to the Attribute's Value Representation or Value Multiplicity.
See
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence, one Item for each nonconforming Attribute.

table_lines.usage: Pointer to Attribute in Modified Attributes Sequence (0400,0550) that had a nonconforming value.

table_lines.name: >>Nonconforming Data Element Value
table_lines.comment: The original Value of the nonconforming Attribute.

table_lines.name: Referenced Series Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items each of which includes the Attributes of one Series.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if this Instance references Instances in this Study.

table_lines.name: >Series Instance UID
table_lines.comment: Unique identifier of the Series containing the referenced Instances.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Instance Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items each providing a reference to an Instance that is part of the Series defined by Series Instance UID (0020,000E) in the enclosing Item.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Studies Containing Other Referenced Instances Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items each identifying a Study other than the Study of which this Instance is a part, which Studies contain Instances that are referenced elsewhere in this Instance.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if this Instance references Instances in other Studies.

table_lines.name: >Study Instance UID
table_lines.comment: Unique identifier of the Study containing the referenced Instances.

table_lines.name: Frame Extraction Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence containing details of how this SOP Instance was extracted from a source multi-frame SOP Instance.
If this Instance was created from an Instance that contains a Frame Extraction Sequence, then this Sequence shall contain all of the Items from the parent's Frame Extraction Sequence and a new Item that describes this extraction.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Multi-frame Source SOP Instance UID
table_lines.comment: SOP Instance from which the frames of this Instance are extracted.

table_lines.name: >Simple Frame List
table_lines.comment:
A list of Frames that were extracted in the form of a simple list.
Required if object extraction is based on a Frame Level Retrieve using the Simple Frame List (0008,1161) Attribute.
See

table_lines.name: >Calculated Frame List
table_lines.comment:
A list of Frames that were extracted in the form of one or more triplets
Required if object extraction is based on a Frame Level Retrieve using the Calculated Frame List (0008,1162) Attribute.
See

table_lines.name: >Time Range
table_lines.comment:
The start and end times of the frames that were extracted.
Required if object extraction is based on a Frame Level Retrieve using Time Range (0008,1163).
See

table_lines.name: Referenced Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Other images significantly related to this image (e.g., post-localizer CT image, Mammographic biopsy or partial view images, or slide images containing control material).
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Purpose of Reference Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes the purpose for which the reference is made.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Referenced Instance Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Non-image composite SOP Instances that are significantly related to this Image, including waveforms that may or may not be temporally synchronized with this image.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Purpose of Reference Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Code describing the purpose of the reference to the Instance(s).
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Derivation Code Sequence
table_lines.comment: One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence. More than one Item indicates that successive derivation steps have been applied.

table_lines.name: Source Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The set of Image SOP Class/Instance pairs of the Images that were used to derive this Image.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >Purpose of Reference Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes the purpose for which the reference is made, that is what role the source image or frame(s) played in the derivation of this image.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Spatial Locations Preserved
table_lines.comment: The extent to which the spatial locations of all pixels are preserved during the processing of the source image that resulted in the current image

table_lines.name: >Patient Orientation
table_lines.comment:
The Patient Orientation values of the source image.
Required if the value of Spatial Locations Preserved (0028,135A) is REORIENTED_ONLY.

table_lines.name: Source Instance Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The set of non-image composite SOP Instances that were used to derive this Instance.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >Purpose of Reference Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes the purpose for which the reference is made, that is what role the source Instance(s) played in the derivation of this Instance.
Only a single Item single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Timezone Offset From UTC
table_lines.comment:
Contains the offset from UTC to the timezone for all DA and TM Attributes present in this SOP Instance, and for all DT Attributes present in this SOP Instance that do not contain an explicitly encoded timezone offset.
See

Attributes that may be used to identify and describe the Patient, Study and Series that are the subject of this Film Session.

C.13-3.table_caption: Basic Film Box Presentation Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Image Display Format
table_lines.comment: Type of image display format.

table_lines.name: Annotation Display Format ID
table_lines.comment: Identification of annotation display format. The definition of the annotation display formats and the annotation box position Sequence are defined in the Conformance Statement.

table_lines.name: Film Orientation
table_lines.comment: Film orientation.

table_lines.name: Film Size ID
table_lines.comment: Film size identification.

table_lines.name: Magnification Type
table_lines.comment: Interpolation type by which the printer magnifies or decimates the image in order to fit the image in the image box on film.

table_lines.name: Smoothing Type
table_lines.comment: Further specifies the type of the interpolation function. Values are defined in Conformance Statement. Only valid for Magnification Type (2010,0060) = CUBIC.

table_lines.name: Border Density
table_lines.comment:
Density of the film areas surrounding and between images on the film.
i where i represents the desired density in hundredths of OD (e.g., 150 corresponds with 1.5 OD).

table_lines.name: Empty Image Density
table_lines.comment:
Density of the image box area on the film that contains no image.
i where i represents the desired density in hundredths of OD (e.g., 150 corresponds with 1.5 OD).

table_lines.name: Min Density
table_lines.comment: Minimum density of the images on the film, expressed in hundredths of OD. If Min Density is lower than minimum printer density than Min Density is set to minimum printer density.

table_lines.name: Max Density
table_lines.comment: Maximum density of the images on the film, expressed in hundredths of OD. If Max Density is higher than maximum printer density than Max Density is set to maximum printer density.

table_lines.name: Trim
table_lines.comment: Specifies whether a trim box shall be printed surrounding each image on the film.

table_lines.name: Configuration Information
table_lines.comment: Character string that contains either the ID of the printer configuration table that contains a set of values for implementation specific print parameters (e.g., perception LUT related parameters) or one or more configuration data values, encoded as characters. If there are multiple configuration data values encoded in the string, they shall be separated by backslashes. The definition of values shall be contained in the SCP's Conformance Statement.

table_lines.name: Illumination
table_lines.comment: Luminance of lightbox illuminating a piece of transmissive film, or for the case of reflective media, luminance obtainable from diffuse reflection of the illumination present. Expressed as L0, in candelas per square meter (cd/m

table_lines.name: Reflected Ambient Light
table_lines.comment: For transmissive film, luminance contribution due to reflected ambient light. Expressed as La, in candelas per square meter (cd/m

table_lines.name: Requested Resolution ID
table_lines.comment: Specifies the resolution at which images in this Film Box are to be printed.

table_lines.name: ICC Profile
table_lines.comment: sect_C.11.15

table_lines.name: Polarity
table_lines.comment:
Specifies whether minimum pixel values (after VOI LUT transformation) are to printed black or white.
If Polarity (2020,0020) is not specified by the SCU, the SCP shall print with NORMAL polarity.

table_lines.name: Magnification Type
table_lines.comment: table_C.13-3

table_lines.comment: table_C.13-3

table_lines.comment: table_C.13-3

table_lines.name: Requested Image Size
table_lines.comment: Width (x-dimension) in mm of the image to be printed. This value overrides the size that corresponds with optimal filling of the Image Box.

table_lines.name: Requested Decimate/Crop Behavior
table_lines.comment:
Specifies whether image pixels are to be decimated or cropped if the image rows or columns is greater than the available printable pixels in an Image Box.
Decimation means that a magnification factor <1 is applied to the image. The method of decimation shall be that specified by Magnification Type (2010,0060) or the SCP default if not specified
Cropping means that some image rows and/or columns are deleted before printing

table_lines.name: Printer Status

table_lines.name: Printer Status Info

Additional information about Printer Status (2110,0010).
See

table_lines.name: Printer Name
table_lines.comment: User defined name identifying the printer.

table_lines.name: Manufacturer
table_lines.comment: Manufacturer of the printer.

table_lines.name: Manufacturer Model Name
table_lines.comment: Manufacturer's model number of the printer.

table_lines.name: Device Serial Number
table_lines.comment: Manufacturer's serial number of the printer.

table_lines.name: Software Versions
table_lines.comment: Manufacturer's designation of software version of the printer.

table_lines.name: Date of Manufacture
table_lines.comment: The date the printer was originally manufactured or re-manufactured (as opposed to refurbished).

table_lines.name: Date of Installation
table_lines.comment: The date the printer was installed in its current location. The printer may or may not have been used prior to installation in its current location.

table_lines.name: Date Of Last Calibration
table_lines.comment: Date when the printer was last calibrated.

table_lines.name: Time Of Last Calibration
table_lines.comment: Time when the printer was last calibrated.

table_lines.name: Printer Configuration Sequence
table_lines.comment: Contains printer configuration information for a single Application Entity title. See Print Management Service Class Structure in

table_lines.name: >SOP Classes Supported
table_lines.comment: The Meta-SOP Class and a list of optional SOP Classes supported. It shall contain one Meta SOP Class UID and 0-n optional SOP Class UIDs.

table_lines.name: >Maximum Memory Allocation
table_lines.comment: Maximum number of kilobytes of memory that can be allocated for a Film Session. The value shall be 0 if Memory Allocation (2000,0060) is not supported.

table_lines.name: >Memory Bit Depth
table_lines.comment: The maximum number of bits for each pixel that can be stored in printer memory.

table_lines.name: >Printing Bit Depth
table_lines.comment: The number of bits used by the print engine for internal LUT calculation and printing of each pixel.

table_lines.name: >Media Installed Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies the combinations of Medium Type and Film Size IDs available in the printer at this time and the Min and Max Densities supported by these media.

table_lines.name: Graphic Data
table_lines.comment:
An ordered set of (column,row) pairs that denote positions in an image specified with sub-pixel resolution such that the origin at the TLHC of the TLHC pixel is 0.0\0.0, the BRHC of the TLHC pixel is 1.0\1.0, and the BRHC of the BRHC pixel is Columns\Rows. The values must be within the range 0\0 to Columns\Rows. The maximum values are those contained in the referenced image in Attributes Columns (0028,0011) and Rows (0028,0010), or in the case of spatial coordinates with Pixel Origin Interpretation (0048,0301) value VOLUME, in Attributes Total Pixel Matrix Columns (0048,0006) and Total Pixel Matrix Rows (0048,0007).
See

table_lines.name: Pixel Origin Interpretation
table_lines.comment:
Required if the instance referenced by Referenced Image Sequence (0008,1140) is tiled (i.e., contains Total Pixel Matrix Columns (0048,0006) and Total Pixel Matrix Rows (0048,0007)). May be present otherwise.
If not present, Graphic Data values are defined relative to the frame pixel origin.

table_lines.name: Fiducial UID
table_lines.comment: The globally unique identifier for this fiducial Item.

table_lines.name: Referenced Sample Positions
table_lines.comment:
List of samples within a multiplex group specifying temporal points of the referenced data. Position of first sample is 1.
Required if the Referenced SOP Instance is a Waveform and Referenced Time Offsets (0040,A138) and Referenced DateTime (0040,A13A) are not present.
Shall only be used when Referenced Channels (0040,A0B0) refers to channels within a single multiplex group.

table_lines.name: Referenced Time Offsets
table_lines.comment:
Specifies temporal points for reference by number of seconds after start of data.
Required if Referenced Sample Positions (0040,A132) and Referenced DateTime (0040,A13A) are not present.

table_lines.name: Referenced DateTime
table_lines.comment:
Specifies temporal points for reference by absolute time.
Required if Referenced Sample Positions (0040,A132) and Referenced Time Offsets (0040,A138) are not present.

table_lines.name: Continuity of Content
table_lines.comment:
This flag specifies for a CONTAINER whether or not its contained Content Items are logically linked in a continuous textual flow, or are separate Items.
See

table_lines.name: Content Template Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Template that describes the content of this Content Item and its subsidiary Content Items.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if a template defined and known to the implementation at the time of encoding was used to define the content of this Item, and the template consists of a single CONTAINER with nested content, and it is the outermost invocation of a set of nested templates that start with the same CONTAINER (see

table_lines.name: >Mapping Resource
table_lines.comment: sect_8.4

table_lines.name: >Mapping Resource UID
table_lines.comment: Uniquely identifies the Mapping Resource that defines the template.

table_lines.name: >Template Identifier
table_lines.comment: Template identifier.

table_lines.name: Referenced Frame of Reference UID
table_lines.comment: Uniquely identifies the Frame of Reference within which the coordinates are defined.

table_lines.name: Graphic Data
table_lines.comment: glossentry_ReferenceCoordinateSystemsect_C.18.9.1.1

table_lines.name: Fiducial UID
table_lines.comment: The globally unique identifier for this fiducial Item.

table_lines.name: Tabulated Values Sequence
table_lines.comment:
This is the table that represents the value of the Content Item.
Shall consist of a single Item whose Attributes convey the cell value(s), which represent rows and columns consisting of text, codes, integers, real numbers or DateTimes.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Number of Table Rows
table_lines.comment: The number of rows in this table.

table_lines.name: >Number of Table Columns
table_lines.comment: The number of columns in this table.

table_lines.name: >Table Row Definition Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The concepts that define the meaning of the rows of the table.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.
If a single Item is present, then the concept applies to all the rows.
Not all rows need to be described.
Items of this Sequence shall be sorted by Table Row Number.
See

table_lines.name: >>Table Row Number
table_lines.comment:
The row, numbered from 1, of the table that this concept describes.
Required if the concept does not apply to all rows.

table_lines.name: >>Concept Name Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The concept that describes the meaning of the row(s).
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Measurement Units Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Units of measurement that apply to all the numeric values in this row.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if all the columns in this row are numeric values (Selector Attribute VR is DS, FD, FL, IS, SL, SS, UL, or US), have units (are not dimensionless), and have the same units.

table_lines.name: >Table Column Definition Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The concepts that define the meaning of the columns of the table.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.
Not all columns need to be described.
If a single Item is present, then the concept applies to all the columns.
Items of this Sequence shall be sorted by Table Column Number.
See

table_lines.name: >>Table Column Number
table_lines.comment:
The column, numbered from 1, of the table that this concept describes.
Required if the concept does not apply to all columns.

table_lines.name: >>Concept Name Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The concept that describes the meaning of the column(s).
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Measurement Units Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Units of measurement that apply to all the numeric values in this column.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if all the rows in this column are numeric values (Selector Attribute VR is DS, FD, FL, IS, SL, SS, UL, or US), have units (are not dimensionless), and have the same units.

table_lines.name: >Cell Values Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The values of each populated cell in the table, identified by row and column.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
The table may be sparse (i.e., not every cell is required to be populated).
Entire rows may be specified in a single Item if all the columns have the same VR.
Entire columns may be specified in a single Item if all the rows have the same VR.
Items of this Sequence shall be in row-major order, then sorted by column.
See

table_lines.name: >>Table Row Number
table_lines.comment:
The row, numbered from 1, of the table.
Required if Table Column Number is absent, or all the rows for the column specified in Table Column Number are not encoded in a single Attribute (containing multiple values) in this Item (i.e., with a single VR).

table_lines.name: >>Table Column Number
table_lines.comment:
The column, numbered from 1, of the table.
Required if Table Row Number is absent, or all the columns for the row specified in Table Row Number are not encoded in a single Attribute (containing multiple values) in this Item (i.e., with a single VR).

table_lines.name: >>Referenced Content Item Identifier
table_lines.comment:
An ordered set of one or more integers that uniquely identifies the Content Item that is the value for this cell.
See
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Selector Attribute VR
table_lines.comment:
Value Representation of the value(s) of the cell(s) in this Item.
Required if Referenced Content Item Identifier (0040,DB73) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Selector DS Value
table_lines.comment:
The numeric value(s) of the cell(s) in this Item.
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is DS, and Numeric Value Qualifier Code Sequence (0040,A301) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Selector DT Value
table_lines.comment:
The DateTime value(s) of the cell(s) in this Item.
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is DT.

table_lines.name: >>Selector FD Value
table_lines.comment:
The numeric value(s) of the cell(s) in this Item.
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is FD, and Numeric Value Qualifier Code Sequence (0040,A301) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Selector FL Value
table_lines.comment:
The numeric value(s) of the cell(s) in this Item.
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is FL, and Numeric Value Qualifier Code Sequence (0040,A301) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Selector IS Value
table_lines.comment:
The numeric value(s) of the cell(s) in this Item.
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is IS, and Numeric Value Qualifier Code Sequence (0040,A301) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Selector SL Value
table_lines.comment:
The numeric value(s) of the cell(s) in this Item.
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is SL, and Numeric Value Qualifier Code Sequence (0040,A301) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Selector SS Value
table_lines.comment:
The numeric value(s) of the cell(s) in this Item.
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is SS, and Numeric Value Qualifier Code Sequence (0040,A301) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Selector SV Value
table_lines.comment:
The numeric value(s) of the cell(s) in this Item.
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is SV, and Numeric Value Qualifier Code Sequence (0040,A301) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Selector UC Value
table_lines.comment:
The text value(s) of the cell(s) in this Item.
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is UC.

table_lines.name: >>Selector UL Value
table_lines.comment:
The numeric value(s) of the cell(s) in this Item.
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is UL, and Numeric Value Qualifier Code Sequence (0040,A301) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Selector US Value
table_lines.comment:
The numeric value(s) of the cell(s) in this Item.
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is US, and Numeric Value Qualifier Code Sequence (0040,A301) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Selector UV Value
table_lines.comment:
The numeric value(s) of the cell(s) in this Item.
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is UV, and Numeric Value Qualifier Code Sequence (0040,A301) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Concept Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The coded value(s) of the cell(s) in this Item.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is SQ.

table_lines.name: >>Measurement Units Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Units of measurement that apply to all the numeric value in this cell.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if this cell is a numeric value (Selector Attribute VR is DS, FD, FL, IS, SL, SS, SV, UL, US or UV) has a unit (is not dimensionless), and the unit is not specified within the Table Row Definition Sequence for this row or Table Column Definition Sequence for this column.

table_lines.name: >>Numeric Value Qualifier Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The reason for the absence of the numeric value.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.
Required if this cell is a numeric value (Selector Attribute VR is DS, FD, FL, IS, SL, SS, SV, UL, US or UV), and the numeric value cannot be provided.

table_lines.name: Instance Number
table_lines.comment: A number that identifies this raw data. The value shall be unique within a Series.

table_lines.name: Content Date
table_lines.comment: The date the raw data creation was started.

table_lines.name: Content Time
table_lines.comment: The time the raw data creation was started.

table_lines.name: Acquisition DateTime
table_lines.comment: The date and time that the acquisition of data started.

table_lines.name: Content Label
table_lines.comment: A label that is used to identify this SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: Content Description
table_lines.comment: A description of the content of the SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: Concept Name Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A coded description of the content of the SOP Instance.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Image Laterality
table_lines.comment: Laterality of (possibly paired) body part examined.

table_lines.name: Creator-Version UID
table_lines.comment: Unique identification of the equipment and version of the software that has created the Raw Data information. The UID allows one to avoid attempting to interpret raw data with an unknown format.

table_lines.name: Referenced Instance Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Other Instances significantly related to this Instance.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Purpose of Reference Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes the purpose for which the reference is made.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.prefix: Include any Private Attributes that contain Raw Data information. See

table_lines.name: Modality
table_lines.comment: Type of device, process or method that created the Instances in this Series.

table_lines.name: Content Date
table_lines.comment: The date the content creation started.

table_lines.name: Content Time
table_lines.comment: The time the content creation started.

table_lines.name: Registration Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence of registration Items. Each Item defines a spatial registration of the images referenced in that Item to the Registered RCS established by this SOP Instance. All referenced images are in the same spatial Frame of Reference or atlas.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Frame of Reference UID
table_lines.comment: Required if Referenced Image Sequence (0008,1140) is absent. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the set of images of the referenced data, registered in this Item.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Frame of Reference UID (0020,0052) is absent. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Matrix Registration Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies one spatial registration.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Frame of Reference Transformation Comment
table_lines.comment: User description or comments about the registration.

table_lines.name: >>Registration Type Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes the information input into the registration process.
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Matrix Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Specifies one transformation, that registers the Source RCS/images to the Registered RCS. It is expressible as multiple matrices, each in a separate Item of the Sequence.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
The Item order is significant and corresponds to matrix multiplication order. See

table_lines.name: >>>Frame of Reference Transformation Matrix Type
table_lines.comment:
Type of Frame of Reference Transformation Matrix (3006,00C6).
See

table_lines.name: >Used Fiducials Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The fiducials used to determine the Frame of Reference Transformation Matrix.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.usage: Reference to the Spatial Fiducial SOP Instance identifying the used Fiducial(s).

table_lines.name: >>Fiducial UID
table_lines.comment: The UID that identifies the fiducial used as registration input.

table_lines.name: >Used Segments Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The segments used to determine the Frame of Reference Transformation Matrix.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.usage: Reference to the Segmentation or Surface Segmentation SOP Instance identifying the used Segments.

table_lines.name: >>Referenced Segment Number
table_lines.comment: Uniquely identifies the segment described in Segment Sequence (0062,0002) by reference to Segment Number (0062,0004). Referenced Segment Number (0062,000B) shall not be multi-valued.

table_lines.name: >Used RT Structure Set ROI Sequence Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The ROIs defined in an RT Structure Set Instance used to determine the Frame of Reference Transformation Matrix.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.usage: Reference to the RT Structure Set SOP Instance identifying the used ROIs.

table_lines.name: >>Referenced ROI Number
table_lines.comment: Uniquely identifies the ROI described in the Structure Set ROI Sequence (3006,0020) by reference to ROI Number (3006,0022).

table_lines.name: Content Date
table_lines.comment: The date the vector grid data creation started.

table_lines.name: Content Time
table_lines.comment: The time the vector grid data creation started.

table_lines.name: Deformable Registration Sequence
table_lines.comment: One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the set of images registered in this Item.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if the registration applies to a subset of images within the specified Source Frame of Reference UID (0064,0003). All referenced images shall be in the same spatial Frame of Reference.

table_lines.name: >Frame of Reference Transformation Comment
table_lines.comment: User description or comments about the registration.

table_lines.name: >Registration Type Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes the method used for the registration process.
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Pre Deformation Matrix Registration Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies one spatial registration to be applied prior to the deformation.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if a matrix transformation is to be applied prior to deformation.

table_lines.name: >>Frame of Reference Transformation Matrix Type
table_lines.comment:
Type of Frame of Reference Transformation Matrix (3006,00C6).
See

table_lines.name: >Post Deformation Matrix Registration Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies one spatial registration to be applied after the application of the deformation.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if matrix transformation is to be performed after application of the deformation.

table_lines.name: >>Frame of Reference Transformation Matrix Type
table_lines.comment:
Type of Frame of Reference Transformation Matrix (3006,00C6).
See

table_lines.name: >Deformable Registration Grid Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes the deformation grid used to sample into the Source RCS.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if deformation is performed. See

table_lines.name: >>Grid Dimensions
table_lines.comment: The dimensions of the grid, in voxels. A triple representing the number of voxels along the X, Y, and Z axes.

table_lines.name: >>Grid Resolution
table_lines.comment: The resolution of the grid voxels. A triple representing the size of a deformation voxel in along the X, Y, and Z dimension, in mm.

table_lines.name: >Used Fiducials Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The fiducials used to determine the registration.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.usage: Reference to the Spatial Fiducial SOP Instance identifying the used Fiducial(s).

table_lines.name: >>Fiducial UID
table_lines.comment: The UID that identifies the fiducial used as registration input.

table_lines.name: Modality
table_lines.comment: Type of device, process or method that created the Instances in this Series.

table_lines.name: Content Date
table_lines.comment: The date the content creation started.

table_lines.name: Content Time
table_lines.comment: The time the content creation started.

table_lines.name: Fiducial Set Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence of Items, each of which is a fiducial set.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the set of images in which the fiducials are located.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Frame of Reference UID (0020,0052) is absent. May be present otherwise.
All referenced images shall have the same Frame of Reference UID if present in the images.

table_lines.name: >Fiducial Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies fiducials, one Item per fiducial.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Fiducial Identifier
table_lines.comment: A fiducial assignment identifier that is unique within this Fiducial Sequence (0070,031E) Item but may match the fiducial identifier of an equivalent feature in another Item.

table_lines.name: >>Fiducials Property Category Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence defining the general category of the property the fiducial represents.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Fiducial Identifier Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Code Sequence for a term that identifies a well-known fiducial type (potentially including methodology, anatomy, tools, etc.).
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Identifier (0070,0310) is absent. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >>Fiducial UID
table_lines.comment: Globally unique identifier for the fiducial instance of this fiducial assignment.

table_lines.name: >>Fiducial Description
table_lines.comment: User description or comments about the fiducial.

table_lines.name: >>Number of Contour Points
table_lines.comment:
Number of points (triplets) in Contour Data (3006,0050).
Required if Contour Data is present.

table_lines.name: >>Graphic Coordinates Data Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The image pixel locations of the fiducial's points.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
More than one Item shall be present only if a fiducial spans more than one image.
Required if Contour Data is not present. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >>>Graphic Data
table_lines.comment:
Graphic point coordinates of the fiducial points in the image of the Referenced Image Sequence. If Fiducial's Contour Data (3006,0050) is present, these points correlate to the points in the Contour Data, one row-column pair for each point and in the same order.
See

table_lines.name: >>>Referenced Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that specifies the image containing the fiducial's graphic coordinates.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Shall be an image within the set of the images in the Referenced Image Sequence (0008,1140) of the encapsulating Fiducial Set Sequence (0070,031C) Item.

table_lines.name: >>Definition Source Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Instances containing the source of the ROI Contour information.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>Referenced ROI Number
table_lines.comment:
The value of ROI Number (3006,0022) in the referenced SOP Instance that identifies the ROI that is the origin of the Spatial Fiducial information.
Required if Referenced SOP Class UID (0008,1150) is RT Structure Set Storage ("1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.481.3").

table_lines.name: Hanging Protocol Name
table_lines.comment: Short descriptor that identifies the Hanging Protocol.

table_lines.name: Hanging Protocol Description
table_lines.comment: Explanation of the objective or intent of the Hanging Protocol.

table_lines.name: Hanging Protocol Level
table_lines.comment: Identifies the level at which this Hanging Protocol is defined, and the intended use.

table_lines.name: Hanging Protocol Creator
table_lines.comment: Identifies the creator of the Hanging Protocol.

table_lines.name: Hanging Protocol Creation DateTime
table_lines.comment: Date and time on which the Hanging Protocol was created.

table_lines.name: Hanging Protocol Definition Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that defines the type of imaging Studies to which this Hanging Protocol applies.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >Modality
table_lines.comment: Required if Anatomic Region Sequence (0008,2218) is not present. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Anatomic Region Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that identifies the anatomic region of interest to which this Hanging Protocol applies.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Modality (0008,0060) is not present. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Laterality
table_lines.comment:
Laterality of the body part to which this Hanging Protocol applies.
Zero length means not applicable.
Required if Anatomic Region Sequence (0008,2218) is present.

table_lines.name: >Procedure Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that identifies a procedure to which this Hanging Protocol applies.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Reason for Requested Procedure Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that identifies a reason for procedure to which this Hanging Protocol applies.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Number of Priors Referenced
table_lines.comment: Identifies the number of prior image sets used in this Hanging Protocol.

table_lines.name: Image Sets Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence describing one or more types of Image Sets to which the Hanging Protocol applies.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >Image Set Selector Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence containing Image Set selection Attributes and values that are used to identify one type of image or object set for the Hanging Protocol.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >>Image Set Selector Usage Flag
table_lines.comment: Indicates the behavior of matching against an image object when Selector Attribute (0072,0026) is not available in the image object.

table_lines.name: >>Selector Attribute
table_lines.comment: Data Element Tag of an Attribute from an Image or other IOD to use for Image Set selection.

table_lines.name: >>Selector Attribute VR
table_lines.comment: The Value Representation of Selector Attribute (0072,0026). See

table_lines.name: >>Selector Value Number
table_lines.comment: Positive integer identifying which value of a multi-valued Attribute identified by Selector Attribute (0072,0026) is to be used for Image Set selection. The value 1 identifies the first value. The value zero identifies any value.

table_lines.name: >Time Based Image Sets Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence containing time based Image Set selection categories and values that are used to identify one type of image set for the Hanging Protocol per Sequence Item.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
The Image Set Selector Sequence (0072,0022) shall be applied to each Sequence Item to define an image set. See

table_lines.name: >>Image Set Number
table_lines.comment: A monotonically increasing integer, starting from 1, incrementing by 1, unique within the Hanging Protocol Instance.

table_lines.name: >>Image Set Selector Category
table_lines.comment: Category of the Time Based Image Set selector.

table_lines.name: >>Relative Time
table_lines.comment:
Exactly two numeric values, indicating the start and end values of a prior range of Instance acquisition times relative to the date and time of a current image set. The units shall be specified in Relative Time Units (0072,003A).
The value pair 0\0 shall indicate a current image set. The value pair n\n shall indicate "prior from the Instance acquisition time of a current image set by n units".
Required if the value of Image Set Selector Category (0072,0034) is RELATIVE_TIME.

table_lines.name: >>Relative Time Units
table_lines.comment:
Units of time for Relative Time (0072,0038).
Required if Relative Time (0072,0038) is present.

table_lines.name: >>Abstract Prior Value
table_lines.comment:
Identifies a prior image set in abstract terms.
Exactly two integer values, indicating the range of prior Studies to include. Each value shall be greater than zero, where 1 indicates the most recent prior and higher values indicate successively older priors. The special value -1 shall indicate the oldest prior.
Required if Image Set Selector Category (0072,0034) is ABSTRACT_PRIOR and Abstract Prior Code Sequence (0072,003E) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Abstract Prior Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identifies a prior image set using coded terminology.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Image Set Selector Category (0072,0034) is ABSTRACT_PRIOR and Abstract Prior Value (0072,003C) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Image Set Label
table_lines.comment: Description of the objective of the image set defined by this Sequence Item.

table_lines.name: Hanging Protocol User Identification Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that provides a coded identifier for the person, group, or site for which this Hanging Protocol was defined.
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Hanging Protocol User Group Name
table_lines.comment: Group or site for which this Hanging Protocol was defined.

table_lines.name: Source Hanging Protocol Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that identifies the Hanging Protocol from which this Hanging Protocol was derived, or on which it is based.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Number of Screens
table_lines.comment: Positive integer indicating the number of screens for which this Hanging Protocol is intended.

table_lines.name: Nominal Screen Definition Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that describes the set of screens for which this Hanging Protocol is intended.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Number of Vertical Pixels
table_lines.comment: Positive integer indicating the intended number of rows of the addressable area of the screen in pixels.

table_lines.name: Number of Horizontal Pixels
table_lines.comment: Positive integer indicating the intended number of columns of the addressable area of the screen in pixels.

table_lines.name: Screen Minimum Grayscale Bit Depth
table_lines.comment:
Positive integer indicating the desired minimum number of grayscale bits per pixel of the screen.
Required if Screen Minimum Color Bit Depth (0072,010C) is not present.

table_lines.name: Screen Minimum Color Bit Depth
table_lines.comment:
Positive integer indicating the desired minimum total number of bits per color channel used to present a pixel.
Required if Screen Minimum Grayscale Bit Depth (0072,010A) is not present.

table_lines.name: Application Maximum Repaint Time
table_lines.comment: Positive integer indicating the desired maximum time in milliseconds required by the application to repaint the full screen once (i.e., recalculate all pixels and paint them to the screen).

table_lines.name: Display Sets Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that describes one or more display sets used to present the Image Sets defined in the Image Sets Sequence (0072,0020).
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >Display Set Number
table_lines.comment: A monotonically increasing integer, starting from 1, incrementing by 1, unique within the Hanging Protocol Instance. It shall be used to identify linked display sets in the Display Set Scrolling Group (0072,0212).

table_lines.name: >Display Set Label
table_lines.comment: Description of the objective of the display set defined by this Sequence Item.

table_lines.name: >Display Set Presentation Group
table_lines.comment: Positive integer value that designates this Display Set as part of a specific presentation group. All Display Sets with the same Display Set Presentation Group (0072,0204) value shall be displayed at the same time. The value 1 shall indicate that this Display Set is part of the initial presentation group. Subsequent values incrementing by 1 shall imply successive temporal ordering of display.

table_lines.name: >Image Set Number
table_lines.comment: Image Set Number (0072,0032) value from a Time Based Image Sets Sequence (0072,0030) Item within the Image Sets Sequence (0072,0020) Item that is selected for display by this Display Set.

table_lines.name: >Image Boxes Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that defines the image boxes for this Display Set.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence unless Image Box Layout Type (0072,0304) is TILED, in which case one or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Image Box Number
table_lines.comment: A monotonically increasing integer that identifies the order of image boxes for scrolling, starting from 1, incrementing by 1, unique within a Display Sets Sequence (0072,0200) Item.

table_lines.name: >>Image Box Layout Type
table_lines.comment:
Type of layout of the image box.
All types except for TILED are single rectangles containing a single frame of image pixel data. The types are primarily distinguished by their interaction technique.

table_lines.name: >>Image Box Tile Horizontal Dimension
table_lines.comment:
Positive integer defining the horizontal Image Box tile dimension; the number of columns.
Required if the value of Image Box Layout Type (0072,0304) is TILED.

table_lines.name: >>Image Box Tile Vertical Dimension
table_lines.comment:
Positive integer defining the vertical Image Box tile dimension; the number of rows.
Required if the value of Image Box Layout Type (0072,0304) is TILED.

table_lines.name: >>Image Box Scroll Direction
table_lines.comment: Required if the value of Image Box Layout Type (0072,0304) is TILED, and the value of Image Box Tile Horizontal Dimension (0072,0306) or Image Box Tile Vertical Dimension (0072,0308) is greater than 1.

table_lines.name: >>Image Box Small Scroll Type
table_lines.comment:
Defines the type of small increment scrolling to be applied to this Image Box.
Required if the value of Image Box Layout Type (0072,0304) is TILED, and the value of Image Box Tile Horizontal Dimension (0072,0306) or Image Box Tile Vertical Dimension (0072,0308) is greater than 1. Scrolling is not specified if zero length.

table_lines.name: >>Image Box Small Scroll Amount
table_lines.comment:
Defines the positive integer number of pages, rows, columns, or images per small increment scroll, based on the values of Image Box Small Scroll Type (0072,0312) and Image Box Scroll Direction (0072,0310). The value applies to both forward and backward scrolling.
Required if Image Box Small Scroll Type (0072,0312) is present with a value.

table_lines.name: >>Image Box Large Scroll Type
table_lines.comment:
Defines the type of large increment scrolling to be applied to this Image Box.
Required if the value of Image Box Layout Type (0072,0304) is TILED, and the value of Image Box Tile Horizontal Dimension (0072,0306) or Image Box Tile Vertical Dimension (0072,0308) is greater than 1.

table_lines.name: >>Image Box Large Scroll Amount
table_lines.comment:
Defines the positive integer number of pages, rows, columns, or images per large increment scroll, based on the values of Image Box Large Scroll Type (0072,0316) and Image Box Scroll Direction (0072,0310). The value applies to both forward and backward scrolling.
Required if Image Box Large Scroll Type (0072,0316) is present with a value.

table_lines.name: >>Image Box Overlap Priority
table_lines.comment:
If this Image Box overlaps in spatial position with others, this Attribute indicates the layer of this Image Box in relation to the others. The value shall be a positive integer in the range 1 to 100, where 1 = top and 100 = bottom.
If this Attribute is not present, then the expected behavior is not defined.

table_lines.name: >>Preferred Playback Sequencing
table_lines.comment:
Describes the preferred playback sequencing for the Image Box. Overrides any Preferred Playback Sequencing (0018,1244) value in the image objects being displayed.
Required if the value of Image Box Layout Type (0072,0304) is CINE.

table_lines.name: >>Recommended Display Frame Rate
table_lines.comment:
Recommended rate at which the frames of a multi-frame image shall be displayed, in frames/second. Shall have a value greater than zero. Overrides any Recommended Display Frame Rate (0008,2144) value in the image objects being displayed.
Required if the value of Image Box Layout Type (0072,0304) is CINE and if Cine Relative to Real-Time (0072,0330) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Cine Relative to Real-Time
table_lines.comment:
A positive unitless floating point numeric factor equal to playback rate divided by acquisition rate.
Required if the value of Image Box Layout Type (0072,0304) is CINE and if Recommended Display Frame Rate (0008,2144) is not present.

table_lines.name: >Filter Operations Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that defines filter criteria to be applied to the image set identified by Image Set Number (0072,0032).
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >>Filter-by Category
table_lines.comment: Required if Selector Attribute (0072,0026) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Filter-by Attribute Presence
table_lines.comment:
Operation to be applied based on the presence or absence of the Attribute represented by Selector Attribute (0072,0026) in each image of the Image Set.
Required if Selector Attribute (0072,0026) is present and Filter-by Operator (0072,0406) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Selector Attribute
table_lines.comment: Required if Filter-by Category (0072,0402) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Selector Attribute VR
table_lines.comment:
The Value Representation of Selector Attribute (0072,0026).
Required if Selector Attribute (0072,0026) or Filter-by Category (0072,0402), and Filter-by Operator (0072,0406) are present.

table_lines.name: >>Selector Value Number
table_lines.comment:
Positive integer identifying which value of the Attribute identified by Selector Attribute (0072,0026) is to be used for filtering. The value 1 identifies the first value. The value zero identifies any value.
Required if Selector Attribute (0072,0026) and Filter-by Operator (0072,0406) are present.

table_lines.name: >>Filter-by Operator
table_lines.comment: Required if Filter-by Category (0072,0402) is present, or if Selector Attribute (0072,0026) is present and Filter-by Attribute Presence (0072,0404) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Image Set Selector Usage Flag
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the behavior of the Filter-by Operator (0072,0406) when Selector Attribute (0072,0026) is not available in the image or does not contain a value specified by Selector Value Number (0072,0028).
If this Attribute is not present in this Sequence Item, MATCH shall be assumed.
Shall be ignored if Filter-by Operator (0072,0406) is not present.

table_lines.name: >Sorting Operations Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that defines sorting criteria to be applied to the result of filter and reformat operations, to define the order in which to present the images in the Image Boxes.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >>Selector Attribute
table_lines.comment: Required if Sort-by Category (0072,0602) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Selector Value Number
table_lines.comment:
Positive integer identifying which value of the Attribute identified by Selector Attribute (0072,0026) is to be used for sorting. The value of 1 identifies the first value. Shall not be zero.
Required if Selector Attribute (0072,0026) is present.

table_lines.name: >>Sort-by Category
table_lines.comment: Required if Selector Attribute (0072,0026) is not present.

table_lines.name: >>Sorting Direction
table_lines.comment: Sorting direction to be applied to the value(s) in the image set of the Attribute identified by Selector Attribute (0072,0026) or Sort-by Category (0072,0602).

table_lines.name: >Reformatting Operation Type
table_lines.comment: Reformatting operation to be applied to the Image Set.

table_lines.name: >Reformatting Thickness
table_lines.comment:
The desired thickness of the reformatted images in millimeters.
Required if value of Reformatting Operation Type (0072,0510) is SLAB or MPR. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Reformatting Interval
table_lines.comment:
The desired spacing of the reformatted images in millimeters. The spacing is measured from the center-to-center of each reconstructed image.
Required if value of Reformatting Operation Type (0072,0510) is SLAB or MPR. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Reformatting Operation Initial View Direction
table_lines.comment:
Initial view of the reformatted images.
Required if the value of Reformatting Operation Type (0072,0510) is MPR or 3D_RENDERING. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >3D Rendering Type
table_lines.comment:
Describes the intended 3D rendering type. One or more values shall be present. The first value shall not be zero length. Required if the value of Reformatting Operation Type (0072,0510) is 3D_RENDERING:
Additional values may be used to identify implementation specific sub-types.

table_lines.name: >Display Set Horizontal Justification
table_lines.comment: Indicates direction in which to horizontally justify the image within a viewport that is not the same shape (aspect ratio) as the image.

table_lines.name: >Display Set Vertical Justification
table_lines.comment: Indicates direction in which to vertically justify the image within a viewport that is not the same shape (aspect ratio) as the image.

table_lines.name: >VOI Type
table_lines.comment: Expected value of interest transformation for display (e.g., Window Center and Window Width or VOI LUT).

table_lines.name: >Pseudo-Color Type
table_lines.comment:
A category of pseudo-color palette choice to be applied after application of the VOI LUT. If this Attribute is not present, a pseudo-color palette shall not be applied.
Defined Terms are the values of Content Label (0070,0080) in the list of standard color palettes defined in

table_lines.name: >Pseudo-Color Palette Instance Reference Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Reference to a Color Palette Storage Instance to be applied after application of the VOI LUT.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
The Referenced SOP Class UID (0008,1150) shall be "1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.39.1".
