If the value of Pseudo-Color Type (0072,0704) is a reference to the Content Label (0070,0080) of a standard palette, the Referenced SOP Instance UID (0008,1155) shall be the corresponding Well-known SOP Instance UID defined in
Required if Pseudo-Color Type (0072,0704) is a reference to a standard palette. May be present otherwise if Pseudo-Color Type (0072,0704) is present.

table_lines.name: >Show Image True Size Flag
table_lines.comment: Indicates whether or not to display images with the physical size of the rendered image pixel the same on the screen as specified in the image Attributes, unless overridden by a Presentation State Instance.

table_lines.name: >Show Graphic Annotation Flag
table_lines.comment: sect_C.9.2

table_lines.name: >Show Patient Demographics Flag
table_lines.comment: Indicates whether or not to display patient and Study identification information.

table_lines.name: >Show Acquisition Techniques Flag
table_lines.comment: Indicates whether or not to display image acquisition technique information.

table_lines.name: >Display Set Presentation Group Description
table_lines.comment: Description of the intent of the Display Set Presentation Group (0072,0204). If present, shall have the same value in all Sequence Items assigned the same value for Display Set Presentation Group (0072,0204).

table_lines.name: Partial Data Display Handling
table_lines.comment:
If one or more Image Sets identified by Image Set Number (0072,0032) in the Display Sets Sequence (0072,0200) Items is not available, indicate whether or not to maintain the expected layout in the absence of complete Image Sets.
If this Attribute is zero length, then the expected behavior is not defined.

table_lines.name: Synchronized Scrolling Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Each Item of this Attribute identifies a group of Display Sets to which synchronized scrolling is to be applied.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.
The dimensions along which the synchronization occurs shall be those specified in the Sorting Operations Sequence (0072,0600).

table_lines.name: >Display Set Scrolling Group
table_lines.comment: Multi-valued list of two or more Display Set Number (0072,0202) values. Indicates that the images within the specified Display Sets are scrolled in parallel, to maintain the established synchronization.

table_lines.name: Navigation Indicator Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes a geometric relationship between Display Sets for the purpose of static or interactive localization or navigation.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Navigation Display Set
table_lines.comment:
Display Set Number (0072,0202) of the Display Set where the geometric relationship to the Reference Display Sets (0072,0218) is graphically depicted.
Required if there is a one-way interaction such that the location of the Reference Display Sets is indicated on or controlled by the Navigation Display Set.

table_lines.name: >Reference Display Sets
table_lines.comment:
One or more Display Set Number (0072,0202) values.
If Navigation Display Set is present, shall list those Display Sets that are controlled by or indicated on the Navigation Display Set.
If Navigation Display Set is absent, shall indicate that all of the Reference Display Sets cross-reference each other.

C.23.4-1.table_caption: Hanging Protocol Selector Attribute Context Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: Selector Sequence Pointer
table_lines.comment:
Contains the Data Element Tag of the Sequence that contains the Attribute that is identified by Selector Attribute (0072,0026).
Required if Selector Attribute (0072,0026) is nested in a Sequence. Shall not be used to identify Code Sequence Attributes. See Selector Code Sequence Value (0072,0080).

table_lines.name: Functional Group Pointer
table_lines.comment:
Contains the Data Element Tag of the Functional Group Sequence that contains the Attribute that is identified by Selector Attribute (0072,0026).
Required if the value of Selector Attribute (0072,0026) is the Data Element Tag of an Attribute that is contained within a Functional Group Sequence.

table_lines.name: Selector Sequence Pointer Private Creator
table_lines.comment: Identification of the creator of a group of Private Data Elements. Required if the Selector Sequence Pointer (0072,0052) value is the Data Element Tag of a Private Attribute.

table_lines.name: Functional Group Private Creator
table_lines.comment: Identification of the creator of a group of Private Data Elements. Required if the Functional Group Pointer (0020,9167) value is the Data Element Tag of a Private Attribute.

table_lines.name: Selector Attribute Private Creator
table_lines.comment: Identification of the creator of a group of Private Data Elements. Required if the Selector Attribute (0072,0026) value is the Data Element Tag of a Private Attribute.

C.23.4-2.table_caption: Hanging Protocol Selector Attribute Value Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: Selector AT Value
table_lines.comment:
The value(s) of the Attribute identified by Selector Attribute (0072,0026).
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is AT.

table_lines.name: Selector CS Value
table_lines.comment:
The value(s) of the Attribute identified by Selector Attribute (0072,0026).
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is CS.

table_lines.name: Selector IS Value
table_lines.comment:
The value(s) of the Attribute identified by Selector Attribute (0072,0026).
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is IS. Some leniency in precision and format (including padding with spaces and leading zeros, e.g., "001" = " 1 " = "1") will be required.

table_lines.name: Selector LO Value
table_lines.comment:
The value(s) of the Attribute identified by Selector Attribute (0072,0026).
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is LO.

table_lines.name: Selector LT Value
table_lines.comment:
The value of the Attribute identified by Selector Attribute (0072,0026).
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is LT.

table_lines.name: Selector PN Value
table_lines.comment:
The value(s) of the Attribute identified by Selector Attribute (0072,0026).
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is PN.

table_lines.name: Selector SH Value
table_lines.comment:
The value(s) of the Attribute identified by Selector Attribute (0072,0026).
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is SH.

table_lines.name: Selector ST Value
table_lines.comment:
The value of the Attribute identified by Selector Attribute (0072,0026).
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is ST.

table_lines.name: Selector UT Value
table_lines.comment:
The value of the Attribute identified by Selector Attribute (0072,0026).
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is UT.

table_lines.name: Selector DS Value
table_lines.comment:
The value(s) of the Attribute identified by Selector Attribute (0072,0026).
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is DS. Some leniency in precision and format (including padding and scientific notation) will be required.

table_lines.name: Selector FD Value
table_lines.comment:
The value(s) of the Attribute identified by Selector Attribute (0072,0026).
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is FD.

table_lines.name: Selector FL Value
table_lines.comment:
The value(s) of the Attribute identified by Selector Attribute (0072,0026).
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is FL.

table_lines.name: Selector UL Value
table_lines.comment:
The value(s) of the Attribute identified by Selector Attribute (0072,0026).
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is UL.

table_lines.name: Selector US Value
table_lines.comment:
The value(s) of the Attribute identified by Selector Attribute (0072,0026).
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is US.

table_lines.name: Selector SL Value
table_lines.comment:
The value(s) of the Attribute identified by Selector Attribute (0072,0026).
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is SL.

table_lines.name: Selector SS Value
table_lines.comment:
The value(s) of the Attribute identified by Selector Attribute (0072,0026).
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is SS.

table_lines.name: Selector Code Sequence Value
table_lines.comment: Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is SQ, and Selector Attribute (0072,0026) is a Code Sequence.

table_lines.name: Selector UI Value
table_lines.comment:
The value of the Attribute identified by Selector Attribute (0072,0026).
Required if Selector Attribute VR (0072,0050) is present and the value is UI.

table_lines.name: Modality
table_lines.comment:
Type of device, process or method that created the Instances in this Series.
This Type definition shall override the definition in the
See

table_lines.name: Series Instance UID
table_lines.comment: Unique identifier of the Series.

table_lines.name: Series Number
table_lines.comment: A number that identifies the Series.

table_lines.name: Series Date
table_lines.comment: Date the Series started.

table_lines.name: Series Time
table_lines.comment: Time the Series started.

table_lines.name: Referenced Performed Procedure Step Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Uniquely identifies the Performed Procedure Step SOP Instance for which the Series is created.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Protocol Name
table_lines.comment: Description of the conditions under which the Series was performed.

table_lines.name: Series Description
table_lines.comment: Description of the Series.

table_lines.name: Series Description Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A coded description of the Series.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Request Attributes Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that contains Attributes from the Imaging Service Request.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Treatment Session UID
table_lines.comment: A unique identifier of the RT Treatment Session to which Instances in this Series belong.

table_lines.name: Instance Number
table_lines.comment: A number that identifies this SOP Instance. The value shall be unique within a Series.

table_lines.name: Content Date
table_lines.comment: The date the document content creation was started.

table_lines.name: Content Time
table_lines.comment: The time the document content creation was started.

table_lines.name: Acquisition DateTime
table_lines.comment: The date and time that the original generation of the data in the document started.

table_lines.name: Image Laterality
table_lines.comment:
Laterality of the (possibly paired) body part that is the subject of the encapsulated document.
If Modality (0008,0060) is M3D, then values for this Attribute shall refer to the intended placement of the created object regardless of how it was generated (see also

table_lines.name: Burned In Annotation
table_lines.comment:
Indicates whether or not the encapsulated document contains sufficient burned in annotation to identify the patient and date the data was acquired.
Identification of patient and date as text in an encapsulated document (e.g., in an XML attribute or element) is equivalent to "burned in annotation". A de-identified document may use the value NO.
If Modality (0008,0060) is M3D, the presence of identifying information embossed or engraved on any part of the model shall be indicated by a value of YES.

table_lines.name: Recognizable Visual Features
table_lines.comment:
Indicates whether or not the Instance contains sufficiently recognizable visual features to allow the Instance or a reconstruction from a set of Instances to identify the patient.
If this Attribute is absent, then the Instance may or may not contain recognizable visual features.

table_lines.name: Source Instance Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence that identifies the set of Instances that were used to derive the encapsulated document.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if derived from one or more DICOM Instances. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Purpose of Reference Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes the purpose for which the reference is made, that is what role the source Instances played in the derivation of this encapsulated document
Only a single Item single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Referenced Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The set of Image Instances referenced in the encapsulated document.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Relative URI Reference Within Encapsulated Document
table_lines.comment:
The relative URI reference used in the encapsulated document to reference the Image Instance in this Item.
This may be used to maintain referential integrity between a set of related encapsulated documents.
Required if the Encapsulated Document (0042,0011) contains a reference to the Image Instance in this Item.
See

table_lines.name: Referenced Instance Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The set of non-image SOP Instances referenced in the encapsulated document.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Relative URI Reference Within Encapsulated Document
table_lines.comment:
The relative URI reference used in the encapsulated document to reference the SOP Instance in this Item.
This may be used to maintain referential integrity between a set of related encapsulated documents.
Required if the Encapsulated Document (0042,0011) contains a reference to the SOP Instance in this Item.
See

table_lines.name: Document Title
table_lines.comment: The title of the document.

table_lines.name: Concept Name Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A coded representation of the document title.
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.usage:
For documents with Modality (0008,0060) equal to M3D, B

For all other encapsulated documents, B

table_lines.name: Document Class Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Additional classifications of the document, beyond the title represented in Concept Name Code Sequence (0040,A043). May be equivalent to HL7 v2.x TXA-2.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Verification Flag
table_lines.comment: Indicates whether the encapsulated document is Verified.

table_lines.name: HL7 Instance Identifier
table_lines.comment:
Instance Identifier of the encapsulated HL7 Structured Document, encoded as a UID (OID or UUID), concatenated with a caret ("^") and Extension value (if Extension is present in Instance Identifier).
Required if encapsulated document is a CDA document.

table_lines.name: Predecessor Documents Sequence
table_lines.comment:
References to SOP Instances whose content has been wholly or partially included in this document with or without modification.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.usage: Purpose of Reference Code Sequence in the Hierarchical SOP Instance Reference Macro D

table_lines.name: Identical Documents Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Duplicates of this document, stored with different SOP Instance UIDs.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: MIME Type of Encapsulated Document
table_lines.comment: The type of the encapsulated document stream described using the MIME Media Type (see RFC 2046).

table_lines.name: List of MIME Types
table_lines.comment:
MIME Types of subcomponents of the encapsulated document.
Required if the encapsulated document incorporates subcomponents with MIME types different than the primary MIME Type of the encapsulated document.

table_lines.name: Encapsulated Document
table_lines.comment: Encapsulated Document stream, containing a document encoded according to the MIME Type.

table_lines.name: Encapsulated Document Length
table_lines.comment:
The length of the Encapsulated Document stream, not including any trailing padding added for encapsulation as a DICOM object.
If present, shall be equal to the Value Length if even, or one less than the Value Length if odd.

table_lines.name: Value Type
table_lines.comment:
The type of the value encoded in this Content Item.
Required if Content Sequence (0040,A730) is present.

table_lines.name: Content Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A potentially recursively nested Sequence of Items that conveys structured content.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >Relationship Type
table_lines.comment:
The type of relationship between the (enclosing) Source Content Item and the Target Content Item.
IODs specify additional constraints on Relationships (including lists of Enumerated Values).
See

table_lines.name: Continuity of Content
table_lines.comment:
This flag specifies for a CONTAINER whether or not its contained Content Items are logically linked in a continuous textual flow, or are separate Items.
See
Required if Content Sequence (0040,A730) is present.

table_lines.name: Content Template Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Template that describes the content of this Content Item and its subsidiary Content Items.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Content Sequence (0040,A730) is present and if a Template defined and known to the implementation at the time of encoding was used to define the content of this Item, and the Template consists of a single CONTAINER with nested content, and it is the outermost invocation of a set of nested Templates that start with the same CONTAINER (see

table_lines.name: >Mapping Resource
table_lines.comment: sect_8.4

table_lines.name: >Mapping Resource UID
table_lines.comment: Uniquely identifies the Mapping Resource that defines the Template.

table_lines.name: >Template Identifier
table_lines.comment: Template identifier.

C.25.1-1.table_caption: Real World Value Mapping Series Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Modality
table_lines.comment: Type of device, process or method that created the Instances in this Series.

C.25.2-1.table_caption: Real World Value Mapping Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Content Date
table_lines.comment: The date the content creation started.

table_lines.name: Content Time
table_lines.comment: The time the content creation started.

table_lines.name: Referenced Image Real World Value Mapping Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence of Real World Value mapping Items. Each Item defines a single mapping and a list of images to which the mapping applies.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Sequence listing the images to which the mapping applies.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Product Package Identifier
table_lines.comment: Identifier of the contrast agent, drug, or device being characterized, typically from a package bar code, RFID, or other materials management ID. This ID might not be globally unique and might conflict with other IDs used within the scope of the institution.

table_lines.name: Manufacturer
table_lines.comment: Manufacturer of product.

table_lines.name: Product Type Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Coded type of product.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.usage:
For drugs, a coded terminology in the US is RxNorm.

For devices, a coded terminology in the US is the FDA CDRH Product Code Classification.

table_lines.name: Product Name
table_lines.comment: Trade or generic name of product.

table_lines.name: Product Description
table_lines.comment: Further description in free form text describing the drug or device.

table_lines.name: Product Lot Identifier
table_lines.comment: Identifier of the manufacturing batch of which this product is part.

table_lines.name: Product Expiration DateTime
table_lines.comment: The date and time after which the manufacturer no longer ensures the safety, quality, and/or proper functioning of the material.

table_lines.name: Product Parameter Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Parameters of the product.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.usage:
For drugs or contrast agents, for Concept Name Code Sequence, B

For devices, for Concept Name Code Sequence, B

table_lines.name: Pertinent Documents Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Reference to a Product Label document for the product.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Referenced SOP Class UID
table_lines.comment: Unique identifier for the class of an HL7 Structured Product Label document.

table_lines.name: >HL7 Instance Identifier
table_lines.comment: Instance Identifier of the referenced HL7 Structured Document, encoded as a UID (OID or UUID), concatenated with a caret ("^") and Extension value (if Extension is present in Instance Identifier).

table_lines.name: >Retrieve URI
table_lines.comment: biblio_RFC_3986

table_lines.name: Substance Administration Approval
table_lines.comment: Status of request for substance administration.

table_lines.name: Approval Status Further Description
table_lines.comment: Description of warning or contra-indication, or notes on approval.

table_lines.name: Approval Status DateTime
table_lines.comment: Timestamp for the Substance Administration Approval response.

table_lines.name: Administration Route Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Route of administration for drug or contrast.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Patient's Name
table_lines.comment: Patient's full name.

table_lines.name: Patient ID
table_lines.comment: Primary identification number or code for the patient.

table_lines.name: Admission ID
table_lines.comment: Identification number of the Visit as assigned by the healthcare provider.

table_lines.name: Issuer of Admission ID Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identifier of the Assigning Authority that issued the Admission ID.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Product Package Identifier
table_lines.comment: Identifier of the contrast agent, drug, or device administered, typically from a package bar code, RFID, or other materials management ID. This ID might not be globally unique and might conflict with other IDs used within the scope of the institution.

table_lines.name: Product Name
table_lines.comment: Trade or generic name of product.

table_lines.name: Product Description
table_lines.comment: Text description of the contrast agent, drug, or device administered.

table_lines.name: Substance Administration DateTime
table_lines.comment: Date and Time of Substance Administration.

table_lines.name: Substance Administration Notes
table_lines.comment: Comments provided by the operator responsible for the substance administration.

table_lines.name: Substance Administration Device ID
table_lines.comment: Identifier for a device that controls substance administration, e.g., injector, infusion pump, etc.

table_lines.name: Administration Route Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Route of administration for drug or contrast.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Substance Administration Parameter Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Parameters of the substance as administered to the patient, e.g., volume, quantity.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.usage: For administration of drugs or contrast agents, Concept Name Code Sequence B

table_lines.name: Operator Identification Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Person administering the substance to the patient, or legally responsible for the administration, and authorized to add an entry to the Medication Administration Record.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Person Identification Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Coded identifier of the person administering the contrast agent, drug, or device.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.usage:
No Baseline CID is defined.

The Coding Scheme Designator Attribute may indicate a local coding scheme (e.g., with value "L") when it is implicitly that of the institution's employee identifier system.

The Code Meaning Attribute, though it is encoded with a VR of LO, may be encoded according to the rules of the PN VR (see

table_lines.name: Number of Surfaces
table_lines.comment: Number of surfaces contained in the Instance. Shall be 1 or more. Shall be the same as the number of Items in Surface Sequence (0066,0002).

table_lines.name: Surface Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The surfaces that are described within the data.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
There shall be Number of Surfaces (0066,0001) Items in the Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >Surface Number
table_lines.comment: Identification number of the surface. Uniquely identifies a surface within this SOP Instance. Shall start at a value of 1, and increase monotonically by 1.

table_lines.name: >Surface Comments
table_lines.comment: User-defined comments describing the surface.

table_lines.name: >Segmented Property Category Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence defining the general category of the property the surface represents.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Segmented Property Type Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence defining the specific property the surface represents.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Surface Processing
table_lines.comment:
Specifies whether the surface has been modified subsequent to the original generation of the surface.
See

table_lines.name: >Surface Processing Ratio
table_lines.comment: The Ratio of Remaining points to Original points after processing. Required if Surface Processing (0066,0009) is YES.

table_lines.name: >Surface Processing Description
table_lines.comment: A textual description of the surface processing performed.

table_lines.name: >Surface Processing Algorithm Identification Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes the processing method.
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Surface Processing (0066,0009) is YES.

table_lines.name: >Recommended Display Grayscale Value
table_lines.comment: A default single gray unsigned value in which it is recommended that the maximum pixel value in this surface be rendered on a monochrome display. The units are specified in P-Values from a minimum of 0000H (black) up to a maximum of FFFFH (white).

table_lines.name: >Recommended Display CIELab Value
table_lines.comment:
A default triplet value in which it is recommended that the surface be rendered on a color display. The units are specified in PCS-Values, and the value is encoded as CIELab.
See

table_lines.name: >Recommended Presentation Opacity
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the opacity in which it is recommended that the surface be rendered.
See

table_lines.name: >Recommended Presentation Type
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the presentation type in which it is recommended that the surface be rendered.
See

table_lines.name: >Recommended Point Radius
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the radius of the vertex points defined in the Long Vertex Point Index List (0066,0043) with which it is recommended that the point be rendered.
The units shall be the same as the units of the coordinate system in which the point coordinates are specified.

table_lines.name: >Recommended Line Thickness
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the thickness of each edge or line defined in the Long Edge Point Index List (0066,0042) or Line Sequence (0066,0028) with which it is recommended that the line be rendered.
The units shall be the same as the units of the coordinate system in which the point coordinates are specified.

table_lines.name: >Finite Volume
table_lines.comment:
Indicates, whether the surface represents a solid ("waterproof") object with an outside and an inside.
See

table_lines.name: >Manifold
table_lines.comment:
Indicates whether the surface is describing an n-1 dimensional manifold in the underlying n-dimensional vector space.
See

table_lines.name: >Surface Points Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The point positions representing vertices of the surface.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Surface Points Normals Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The normals on the surface for each point.
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.usage:
Number of Vectors (0066,001E) shall equal Number of Surface Points (0066,0015) in this Surface Sequence (0066,0002) Item.

Vector Dimensionality (0066,001F) shall be 3.

If Finite Volume (0066,000E) is YES, the normals of the vertices shall point toward the outside of the object. If Finite Volume (0066,000E) is not YES, the direction of the normals shall be consistent where possible.

table_lines.name: >Surface Mesh Primitives Sequence
table_lines.comment: Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.usage: The primitives' indices shall not exceed Number of Surface Points (0066,0015) in this Surface Sequence (0066,0002) Item.

table_lines.name: Point Position Accuracy
table_lines.comment: A single standard deviation of the error for all the points' spatial positions. The units shall be the same as the units of the coordinate system in which the point coordinates are specified.

table_lines.name: Mean Point Distance
table_lines.comment:
The mean point distance of the point set.
It is given by the mean of the distances to the nearest neighbor over all points. The units shall be the same as the units of the coordinate system in which the point coordinates are specified.

table_lines.name: Maximum Point Distance
table_lines.comment: The maximum distance of one point to its nearest neighbor. The units shall be the same as the units of the coordinate system in which the point coordinates are specified.

table_lines.name: Points Bounding Box Coordinates
table_lines.comment: Two 3D locations defining the cuboid bounding box, parallel to the coordinate system axes, encompassing the point set.

table_lines.name: Axis of Rotation
table_lines.comment: A 3D location that combined with Center of Rotation (0066,001C) specifies the preferred axis of rotation of this object.

table_lines.name: Center of Rotation
table_lines.comment: A 3D location defining the preferred center of rotation for this point set. Required if Axis of Rotation (0066,001B) is present. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Long Vertex Point Index List
table_lines.comment:
A list of point indices. Contains n point indices describing Vertices.
See

table_lines.name: Long Edge Point Index List
table_lines.comment:
A list of point indices. Contains 2n point indices describing unconnected Edges.
See

table_lines.name: Long Triangle Point Index List
table_lines.comment:
A list of point indices. Contains 3n point indices describing unconnected Triangles.
See

table_lines.name: Triangle Strip Sequence
table_lines.comment:
All Triangle Strips in this Surface.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Triangle Fan Sequence
table_lines.comment:
All Triangle Fans in this Surface.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Line Sequence
table_lines.comment:
All Lines in this Surface.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Facet Sequence
table_lines.comment:
All Facets in this Surface. Each Item describes one facet.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Surface Points Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The point positions representing vertices of the surface.
Only one Item shall be included in the Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Segmented Property Category Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence defining the general category of the property the surface point set represents.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Segmented Property Type Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence defining the specific property the surface point set represents.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Surface Point Presentation Value Data
table_lines.comment:
Contains a vector of P-Values to assign a gray value to each point.
The number of values shall be equal to the value of Number Of Surface Points (0066,0015) in the
Each value shall correspond to the respective point in the Point Coordinates Data (0066,0016).

table_lines.name: Surface Point Color CIELab Value Data
table_lines.comment:
Contains a vector of color triplets to assign colors to each point.
The number of triplets shall be equal to the value of Number Of Surface Points (0066,0015) in the
The units are PCS-Values, and the value is encoded as CIELab. See
Each triplet shall correspond to the respective point in the Point Coordinates Data (0066,0016).

table_lines.name: UV Mapping Sequence
table_lines.comment: One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Surface Number
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the Surface Number (0066,0003) of the Item in Surface Sequence (0066,0002) to which this UV Mapping applies.
Required when Surface Sequence (0066,0002) is present and contains more than one Item.

table_lines.name: >Texture Label
table_lines.comment: Contains a label that uniquely identifies this UV map to distinguish it from other Items in the Sequence.

table_lines.name: >U Value Data
table_lines.comment:
Contains a vector of column offsets. Each value is normalized to the range of 0.0 to 1.0 pointing in the pixel data of the referenced textures Sequence image. Each value shall correspond to the respective point in the Point Coordinates Data (0066,0016).
The number of values must be equal to the number of points of the Point Cloud or the Surface Mesh.

table_lines.name: >V Value Data
table_lines.comment:
Contains a vector of row offsets. Each value is normalized to the range of 0.0 to 1.0 pointing in the pixel data of the referenced textures Sequence image. Each value shall correspond to the respective point in the Point Coordinates Data (0066,0016).
The number of values must be equal to the number of points of the Point Cloud or the Surface Mesh.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Texture Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The image that is being mapped to the point cloud or the surface mesh.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

C.29.1.1-1.table_caption: Generic Implant Template Description Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Manufacturer
table_lines.comment: Name of the manufacturer that produces the implant.

table_lines.name: Frame of Reference UID
table_lines.comment: Defines a 3D Frame of Reference for this component.

table_lines.name: Implant Name
table_lines.comment: The (product) name of the implant.

table_lines.name: Implant Size
table_lines.comment:
The size descriptor of the component.
Required if the component exists in different sizes and the size number is not part of the name or identifier.
May be present otherwise.
See

table_lines.name: Implant Part Number
table_lines.comment: The (product) identifier of the implant.

table_lines.name: Implant Template Version
table_lines.comment:
The version code of the implant template.
If Implant Type (0068,6223) is DERIVED, this shall have the same value as the Implant Template Version (0068,6221) of the manufacturer's implant template from which this Instance was derived.

table_lines.name: Replaced Implant Template Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Reference to the Implant Template that is replaced by this template.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if this Instance replaces another Instance.

table_lines.name: Implant Type
table_lines.comment: Indicates whether the Implant Template is derived from another Implant Template.

table_lines.name: Original Implant Template Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Reference to the Implant Template Instance with Implant Type (0068,6223) ORIGINAL from which this Instance was ultimately derived.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Implant Type (0068,6223) is DERIVED.

table_lines.name: Derivation Implant Template Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Reference to Implant Template Instance from which this Instance was directly derived.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Implant Type (0068,6223) is DERIVED.

table_lines.name: Effective DateTime
table_lines.comment: Date and time from which this Instance is or will be valid.

table_lines.name: Implant Target Anatomy Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that identifies the anatomical region the implant is to be implanted to.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Anatomic Region Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that identifies the anatomic region of interest in this Instance (i.e., external anatomy, surface anatomy, or general region of the body).
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Notification From Manufacturer Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Information from the manufacturer concerning a critical notification, recall, or discontinuation of the implant or implant template.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if such information has been issued.

table_lines.name: >Information Issue DateTime
table_lines.comment: Date and Time the information was issued.

table_lines.name: >Information Summary
table_lines.comment: Summary of the information.

table_lines.name: >Encapsulated Document
table_lines.comment:
The complete manufacturer notification describing the template.
Encapsulated Document stream, containing a document encoded according to the MIME Type.

table_lines.name: >MIME Type of Encapsulated Document
table_lines.comment:
The type of the encapsulated document stream described using the MIME Media Type (see RFC 2046).
Required if Encapsulated Document (0042,0011) is present in this Sequence Item.

table_lines.name: Information From Manufacturer Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Information from Manufacturer other than described in Notification From Manufacturer Sequence (0068,6265).
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Information Issue DateTime
table_lines.comment: Date and Time the information was issued.

table_lines.name: >Information Summary
table_lines.comment: Summary of the information.

table_lines.name: >Encapsulated Document
table_lines.comment:
Encapsulated Document stream, containing a document encoded according to the MIME Type.
The complete manufacturer information.

table_lines.name: >MIME Type of Encapsulated Document
table_lines.comment:
The type of the encapsulated document stream described using the MIME Media Type (see RFC 2046).
Required if Encapsulated Document (0042,0011) is present in this Sequence Item.

table_lines.name: Implant Regulatory Disapproval Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence containing countries and regions in which the implant is not approved for usage.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if the implant has been disapproved in a country or a region.

table_lines.name: Overall Template Spatial Tolerance
table_lines.comment: Tolerance in mm applying to all distance measurements and spatial locations in this Implant Template.

table_lines.name: Materials Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Code Sequence specifying the materials the implant was built from.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Coating Materials Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A Code Sequence specifying the materials the implant is coated with.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if the implant is coated.

table_lines.name: Implant Type Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence containing a coded description of the type of implant the template reflects.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Fixation Method Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The method that will be used to fixate the implant in the body.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

C.29.1.2-1.table_caption: Generic Implant Template 2D Drawings Module Attributes

table_lines.name: HPGL Document Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The 2D template representations of this implant.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >HPGL Document ID
table_lines.comment:
Identification number of the HPGL Document. Uniquely identifies an HPGL Document within this SOP Instance.
The value shall start at 1, and increase monotonically by 1.

table_lines.name: >HPGL Document Label
table_lines.comment: Label describing the document.

table_lines.name: >View Orientation Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Coded description of the direction of view represented by this 2D template.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >View Orientation Modifier Code Sequence
table_lines.comment: View Orientation Modifier.

table_lines.name: >HPGL Contour Pen Number
table_lines.comment: Numeric ID of the pen used in the encapsulated HPGL document for outlines.

table_lines.name: >HPGL Pen Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Labels for each pen used in the encapsulated HPGL Document.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Shall contain one Item per pen used in the HPGL document.

table_lines.name: >>HPGL Pen Number
table_lines.comment: Numeric ID of the pen in the HPGL document.

table_lines.name: >>HPGL Pen Label
table_lines.comment: Label of the pen.

table_lines.name: >>HPGL Pen Description
table_lines.comment: Description of the kind of information drawn with the pen.

table_lines.name: >Recommended Rotation Point
table_lines.comment: Point around which the 2D template is rotated in manual planning, in HPGL coordinates.

table_lines.name: >Bounding Rectangle
table_lines.comment: HPGL coordinates of the smallest rectangle parallel to the paper axes that contains the whole drawing.

C.29.1.3-1.table_caption: Generic Implant Template 3D Models Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Implant Template 3D Model Surface Number
table_lines.comment: Surface Number (0066,0003) of the surface that represents the shape of the entire implant.

table_lines.name: Surface Model Description Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The description of the Surface Model.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Shall contain one Item per Item in Surface Sequence (0066,0002).

table_lines.name: >Referenced Surface Number
table_lines.comment: Reference to a Surface Number (0066,0003) present in Surface Sequence (0066,0002).

table_lines.name: >Surface Model Label
table_lines.comment: Label for this surface.

table_lines.name: Surface Model Scaling Factor
table_lines.comment:
Scaling factor (mm/Surface unit)
See

C.29.1.4-1.table_caption: Generic Implant Template Mating Features Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Mating Feature Sets Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Mating feature sets used to combine the implant with other implants.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Mating Feature Set ID
table_lines.comment:
Identification number of the set. Uniquely identifies a mating feature set within this SOP Instance.
The value shall start at 1, and increase monotonically by 1 for each Item.

table_lines.name: >Mating Feature Set Label
table_lines.comment: Label of the set.

table_lines.name: >Mating Feature Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The mating features of the set.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Mating Feature ID
table_lines.comment: Numeric ID of the mating feature. Uniquely identifies a mating feature within this Sequence Item.

table_lines.name: >>3D Mating Point
table_lines.comment:
Origin of the contact system.
Required if 2D Mating Feature Coordinates Sequence (0068,6430) is not present and Implant Template 3D Model Surface Number (0068,6350) is present.
May be present if 2D Mating Feature Coordinates Sequence (0068,6430) is present and Implant Template 3D Model Surface Number (0068,6350) is present.
See

table_lines.name: >>3D Mating Axes
table_lines.comment:
The Axes of contact described as direction cosines in the 3D coordinate system defined by the Frame of Reference UID.
Required if 3D Mating Point (0068,64C0) is present.
See

table_lines.name: >>2D Mating Feature Coordinates Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Coordinates of the mating feature in the HPGL documents.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if 3D Mating Point (0068,64C0) is not present and HPGL Document Sequence (0068,62C0) is present.
May be present if 3D Mating Point (0068,64C0) is present and HPGL Document Sequence (0068,62C0) is present.

table_lines.name: >>>Referenced HPGL Document ID
table_lines.comment:
Value of the HPGL Document ID (0068,62D0) present in the HPGL Document Sequence (0068,62C0) that contains the 2D Drawing including the Mating Feature.
Shall be unique within the Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>2D Mating Point
table_lines.comment:
Origin of the contact system, in HPGL coordinates.
See

table_lines.name: >>>2D Mating Axes
table_lines.comment:
Direction cosines of the contact system.
See

table_lines.name: >>Mating Feature Degree of Freedom Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Degrees of freedom in this mating feature.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >>>Degree of Freedom ID
table_lines.comment: Numeric ID of the degree of freedom. Uniquely identifies a degree of freedom within this Sequence Item. The value shall start at 1, and increase monotonically by 1 for each Item.

table_lines.name: >>>Degree of Freedom Type
table_lines.comment:
Indicates the type of the degree of freedom.
See

table_lines.name: >>>2D Degree of Freedom Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Geometric specifications of the degrees of freedom for this HPGL Document.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if 2D Mating Feature Coordinates Sequence (0068,6430) is present.
See

table_lines.name: >>>>Referenced HPGL Document ID
table_lines.comment:
Value of the HPGL Document ID (0068,62D0) present in the HPGL Document Sequence (0068,62C0) that contains the 2D Drawing including the Mating Feature.
See
Shall be unique within the Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>>2D Degree Of Freedom Axis
table_lines.comment:
Direction cosines of the axis of the degree of freedom.
See

table_lines.name: >>>>Range of Freedom
table_lines.comment:
Interval of freedom for this degree of freedom.
See

table_lines.name: >>>3D Degree Of Freedom Axis
table_lines.comment:
Direction cosines of the axis of the degree of freedom in the Frame of Reference of the template.
See
Required if 3D Mating Point (0068,64C0) is present.

table_lines.name: >>>Range of Freedom
table_lines.comment:
Two floating point numbers defining a value range for this degree of freedom.
See
Required if 3D Mating Point (0068,64C0) is present.

table_lines.name: >Planning Landmark Identification Code Sequence

Plane landmarks for planning.

table_lines.name: >Planning Landmark ID
table_lines.comment:
Numeric ID of the planning landmark. Uniquely identifies the planning landmark within the SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: >Planning Landmark Description
table_lines.comment: Purpose or intended use of the landmark.

table_lines.name: >Planning Landmark Identification Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Coded Description of the real-world plane that is represented by this landmark.

2D coordinates of the point in the HPGL documents.

table_lines.comment: Indicates that only one component of this Component Type shall be used in an assembly.

table_lines.name: >Mandatory Component Type

table_lines.comment:

The ID selects the Mating Feature of the Mating Feature Set of the first component of the connection.

table_lines.name: >Component 2 Referenced ID
table_lines.comment:
Value of Component ID (0076,0055) present in Component Sequence (0076,0040) that contains the assembly implant components.
The ID selects the second component of the connection.

table_lines.name: >Component 2 Referenced Mating Feature Set ID
table_lines.comment:
Value of the Mating Feature Set ID (0068,63C0) present in the Mating Feature Set Sequence (0068,63B0) that contains the Mating Feature Sets.

table_lines.name: >Component 2 Referenced Mating Feature ID
table_lines.comment:
Value of the Mating Feature ID (0068,63F0) present in the Mating Feature Sequence (0068,63E0) that contains the Mating Features.

Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Operator Identification Sequence
table_lines.comment: Identification of the operator who authorized override. Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Override Reason
table_lines.comment: User-defined description of reason for override of overridden parameter.

table_lines.name: General Machine Verification Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence containing general machine verification parameters.
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Specified Primary Meterset
table_lines.comment: Desired machine setting of primary Meterset. The units shall match those specified by Primary Dosimeter Unit (300A,00B3) in the plan specified in the Referenced RT Plan Sequence (300C,0002).

table_lines.name: >Specified Secondary Meterset
table_lines.comment: Desired machine setting of secondary Meterset. The units shall match those specified for Specified Secondary Meterset (3008,0033) in the plan specified in the Referenced RT Plan Sequence (300C,0002).

table_lines.name: >Specified Treatment Time
table_lines.comment: Treatment Time set in seconds.

table_lines.name: >Beam Limiting Device Leaf Pairs Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Beam limiting device (collimator) jaw or leaf (element) leaf pair values.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>RT Beam Limiting Device Type
table_lines.comment: Type of beam limiting device (collimator).

table_lines.name: >>Number of Leaf/Jaw Pairs
table_lines.comment: Number of leaf (element) or jaw pairs (equal to 1 for standard beam limiting device jaws).

table_lines.name: >Recorded Wedge Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Treatment wedges present during delivered Beam.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Wedge Number
table_lines.comment: Identification number of the Wedge. The value of Wedge Number (300A,00D2) shall be unique within the Wedge Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Wedge ID
table_lines.comment: User-supplied identifier for wedge.

table_lines.name: >>Wedge Angle
table_lines.comment: Nominal wedge angle delivered in degrees.

table_lines.name: >>Wedge Orientation
table_lines.comment: Orientation of wedge, i.e., orientation of the IEC WEDGE FILTER coordinate system with respect to the IEC BEAM LIMITING DEVICE coordinate system, in degrees.

table_lines.name: >>Accessory Code
table_lines.comment: An identifier for the accessory intended to be read by a device such as a bar-code reader.

table_lines.name: >Recorded Compensator Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Treatment compensators associated with current Beam.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Compensator ID
table_lines.comment: User-supplied identifier for compensator.

table_lines.name: >>Accessory Code
table_lines.comment: An identifier for the accessory intended to be read by a device such as a bar-code reader.

table_lines.name: >>Compensator Tray ID
table_lines.comment: User-supplied identifier for compensator tray.

table_lines.name: >>Referenced Compensator Number
table_lines.comment: Uniquely identifies compensator specified by Compensator Number (300A,00E4) within Beam referenced by Referenced Beam Number (300C,0006).

table_lines.name: >Recorded Block Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Blocks associated with current Beam.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Block Tray ID
table_lines.comment: User-supplied identifier for block tray or Electron Insert.

table_lines.name: >>Accessory Code
table_lines.comment: An identifier for the Block to be read by a device such as a bar-code reader.

table_lines.name: >>Referenced Block Number
table_lines.comment: Uniquely identifies block specified by Block Number (300A,00FC) within Beam referenced by Referenced Beam Number (300C,0006).

table_lines.name: >Beam Name
table_lines.comment: User-defined name for Beam.

table_lines.name: >Radiation Type
table_lines.comment: Particle type of Beam.

table_lines.name: >Number of Wedges
table_lines.comment: Number of wedges associated with current Beam.

table_lines.name: >Number of Compensators
table_lines.comment: Number of compensators associated with current Beam.

table_lines.name: >Number of Boli
table_lines.comment: Number of boli used with current Beam.

table_lines.name: >Number of Blocks
table_lines.comment: Number of shielding blocks or Electron Inserts associated with Beam.

table_lines.name: >Applicator Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Applicators associated with Beam.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Accessory Code
table_lines.comment: An identifier for the accessory intended to be read by a device such as a bar-code reader.

table_lines.name: >>Applicator ID
table_lines.comment: User or machine supplied identifier for Applicator.

table_lines.name: >>Applicator Type
table_lines.comment: Type of Applicator.

table_lines.name: >Number of Control Points
table_lines.comment: Number of control points in Beam.

table_lines.name: >Patient Setup Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Patient setup data for current plan.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Patient Setup Number
table_lines.comment: Identification number of the Patient Setup.

table_lines.name: >>Fixation Device Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Fixation Devices used in Patient Setup.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>Accessory Code
table_lines.comment: An identifier for the accessory intended to be read by a device such as a bar-code reader.

table_lines.name: >>>Fixation Device Type
table_lines.comment: Type of Fixation Device used during Patient Setup.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Bolus Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Boli associated with Beam.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Referenced ROI Number
table_lines.comment: sect_C.8.8.5sect_C.8.8.9

table_lines.name: >>Accessory Code
table_lines.comment: An accessory identifier to be read by a device such as a bar code reader.

C.31-2.table_caption: RT Conventional Machine Verification Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Conventional Machine Verification Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence containing conventional machine verification parameters.
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Conventional Control Point Verification Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Beam control points for current treatment beam.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Nominal Beam Energy
table_lines.comment: Nominal Beam Energy at control point.

table_lines.name: >>Dose Rate Set
table_lines.comment: Dose Rate to be set on treatment machine for segment beginning at current control point (e.g., MU/min).

table_lines.name: >>Wedge Position Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Wedge Positions for the current control point.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >>>Wedge Position
table_lines.comment: Position of Wedge at current Control Point.

table_lines.name: >>>Referenced Wedge Number
table_lines.comment: Uniquely references Wedge described by Wedge Number (300A,00D2) in Wedge Sequence (300A,00D1).

table_lines.name: >>Beam Limiting Device Position Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Beam limiting device (collimator) jaw or leaf (element) positions.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>RT Beam Limiting Device Type
table_lines.comment: Type of beam limiting device (collimator). The value of this Attribute shall correspond to RT Beam Limiting Device Type (300A,00B8) defined in an Item of Beam Limiting Device Sequence (300A,00B6)

table_lines.name: >>>Leaf/Jaw Positions
table_lines.comment: Positions of beam limiting device (collimator) leaf (element) or jaw pairs in mm in the IEC BEAM LIMITING DEVICE coordinate axis appropriate to RT Beam Limiting Device Type (300A,00B8), e.g., X-axis for MLCX, Y-axis for MLCY. Contains 2N values, where N is the Number of Leaf/Jaw Pairs (300A,00BC) in Beam Limiting Device Sequence (300A,00B6). Values shall be listed in the IEC leaf (element) subscript order 101, 102, … 1N, 201, 202, … 2N.

table_lines.name: >>Gantry Angle
table_lines.comment: Gantry angle in degrees of radiation source, i.e., orientation of the IEC GANTRY coordinate system with respect to the IEC FIXED REFERENCE coordinate system.

table_lines.name: >>Beam Limiting Device Angle
table_lines.comment: Beam Limiting Device angle in degrees, i.e., orientation of the IEC BEAM LIMITING DEVICE coordinate system with respect to the IEC GANTRY coordinate system.

table_lines.name: >>Patient Support Angle
table_lines.comment: Patient Support angle in degrees, i.e., orientation of the IEC PATIENT SUPPORT (turntable) coordinate system with respect to the IEC FIXED REFERENCE coordinate system.

table_lines.name: >>Table Top Eccentric Axis Distance
table_lines.comment: Distance (positive) in mm from the IEC PATIENT SUPPORT vertical axis to the IEC TABLE TOP ECCENTRIC vertical axis.

table_lines.name: >>Table Top Eccentric Angle
table_lines.comment: Table Top (non-isocentric) angle, i.e., orientation of the IEC TABLE TOP ECCENTRIC coordinate system with respect to the IEC PATIENT SUPPORT coordinate system, in degrees.

table_lines.name: >>Referenced Control Point Index
table_lines.comment: Uniquely identifies Control Point specified by Control Point Index (300A,0112) within the Beam referenced by Referenced Beam Number (300C,0006).

C.31-3.table_caption: RT Ion Machine Verification Module Attributes

table_lines.name: Ion Machine Verification Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence containing ion machine verification parameters.
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Ion Control Point Verification Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Beam control points for current ion treatment beam.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Meterset Rate Set
table_lines.comment: The specified speed of delivery of the specified dose in units specified by Primary Dosimeter Unit (300A,00B3) in referenced RT Plan per minute.

table_lines.name: >>Nominal Beam Energy
table_lines.comment: Nominal Beam Energy at control point.

table_lines.name: >>Beam Limiting Device Position Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Beam limiting device (collimator) jaw or leaf (element) positions.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>RT Beam Limiting Device Type
table_lines.comment: Type of beam limiting device (collimator). The value of this Attribute shall correspond to RT Beam Limiting Device Type (300A,00B8) defined in an Item of Beam Limiting Device Sequence (300A,00B6)

table_lines.name: >>>Leaf/Jaw Positions
table_lines.comment: Positions of beam limiting device (collimator) leaf (element) or jaw pairs in mm in the IEC BEAM LIMITING DEVICE coordinate axis appropriate to RT Beam Limiting Device Type (300A,00B8), e.g., X-axis for MLCX, Y-axis for MLCY. Contains 2N values, where N is the Number of Leaf/Jaw Pairs (300A,00BC) in Beam Limiting Device Sequence (300A,00B6). Values shall be listed in the IEC leaf (element) subscript order 101, 102, … 1N, 201, 202, … 2N.

table_lines.name: >>Gantry Angle
table_lines.comment: Gantry angle of radiation source in degrees, i.e., orientation of the IEC GANTRY coordinate system with respect to the IEC FIXED REFERENCE coordinate system.

table_lines.name: >>Beam Limiting Device Angle
table_lines.comment: Beam Limiting Device angle in degrees, i.e., orientation of the IEC BEAM LIMITING DEVICE coordinate system with respect to the IEC GANTRY coordinate system.

table_lines.name: >>Patient Support Angle
table_lines.comment: Patient Support angle in degrees, i.e., orientation of the IEC PATIENT SUPPORT (turntable) coordinate system with respect to the IEC FIXED REFERENCE coordinate system.

table_lines.name: >>Snout Position
table_lines.comment: Axial position in mm of the snout, measured from isocenter to the downstream side of the snout (without consideration of variable length elements such as blocks, MLC and/or compensators).

table_lines.name: >>Range Shifter Settings Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Range Shifter settings for the current control point.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>Referenced Range Shifter Number
table_lines.comment: Uniquely references Range Shifter described by Range Shifter Number (300A,0316) in Range Shifter Sequence (300A,0314).

table_lines.name: >>Lateral Spreading Device Settings Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Lateral Spreading Device settings for the current control point.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>Referenced Lateral Spreading Device Number
table_lines.comment: Uniquely references Lateral Spreading Device described by Lateral Spreading Device Number (300A,0334) in Lateral Spreading Device Sequence (300A,0332).

table_lines.name: >>Range Modulator Settings Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Range Modulator Settings for current control point.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>Range Modulator Gating Start Value
table_lines.comment: Start position, defining the range modulator position at which the beam is switched on.

table_lines.name: >>>Range Modulator Gating Stop Value
table_lines.comment: Stop position, defining the range modulator position at which the beam is switched off.

table_lines.name: >>>Referenced Range Modulator Number
table_lines.comment: Uniquely references Range Modulator described by Range Modulator Number (300A,0344) in Range Modulator Sequence (300A,0342).

table_lines.name: >>Ion Wedge Position Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Wedge positions for current control point.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>Wedge Position
table_lines.comment: Position of Wedge at current Control Point.

table_lines.name: >>Referenced Control Point Index
table_lines.comment: Uniquely identifies Control Point specified by Control Point Index (300A,0112 within the Beam referenced by Referenced Beam Number (300C,0006).

table_lines.name: >Recorded Snout Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Snouts associated with Beam.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Accessory Code
table_lines.comment: An accessory identifier to be read by a device such as a bar code reader.

table_lines.name: >>Snout ID
table_lines.comment: User or machine supplied identifier for Snout.

table_lines.name: >Recorded Range Shifter Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Range shifters recorded with Beam.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Accessory Code
table_lines.comment: An accessory identifier to be read by a device such as a bar code reader.

table_lines.name: >>Range Shifter ID
table_lines.comment: User or machine supplied identifier for Range Modulator.

table_lines.name: >>Referenced Range Shifter Number
table_lines.comment: Uniquely identifies range shifter specified by Range Shifter Number (300A,0316) within Beam referenced by Referenced Beam Number (300C,0006).

table_lines.name: >Recorded Lateral Spreading Device Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Lateral spreading devices associated with Beam.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Accessory Code
table_lines.comment: An accessory identifier to be read by a device such as a bar code reader.

table_lines.name: >>Lateral Spreading Device ID
table_lines.comment: User or machine supplied identifier for Lateral Spreading Device.

table_lines.name: >>Referenced Lateral Spreading Device Number
table_lines.comment: Uniquely identifies lateral spreading device specified by Lateral Spreading Device Number (300A,0334) within Beam referenced by Referenced Beam Number (300C,0006).

table_lines.name: >Recorded Range Modulator Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Range modulators associated with Beam.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Accessory Code
table_lines.comment: An accessory identifier to be read by a device such as a bar code reader.

table_lines.name: >>Range Modulator ID
table_lines.comment: User or machine supplied identifier for Range Modulator.

table_lines.name: >>Range Modulator Type
table_lines.comment:
Type of Range Modulator.
See

table_lines.name: >>Beam Current Modulation ID
table_lines.comment: User-supplied identifier for the beam current modulation pattern.

table_lines.name: >>Referenced Range Modulator Number
table_lines.comment: Uniquely references Range Modulator described by Range Modulator Number (300A,0344) in Range Modulator Sequence (300A,0342).

table_lines.name: >Radiation Mass Number
table_lines.comment: Mass number of radiation.

table_lines.name: >Radiation Atomic Number
table_lines.comment: Atomic number of radiation.

table_lines.name: >Radiation Charge State
table_lines.comment: Charge state of radiation.

table_lines.name: >Scan Mode
table_lines.comment: The method of beam scanning to be used during treatment.

table_lines.name: >Number of Range Shifters
table_lines.comment: Number of range shifters associated with current beam.

table_lines.name: >Number of Lateral Spreading Devices
table_lines.comment: Number of lateral spreading devices associated with current beam.

table_lines.name: >Number of Range Modulators
table_lines.comment: Number of range modulators associated with current beam.

table_lines.name: >Patient Support ID
table_lines.comment: User-specified identifier for manufacturer specific patient support devices.

table_lines.name: >Patient Support Accessory Code
table_lines.comment: A Patient Support accessory identifier to be read by a device such as a bar code reader.

table_lines.name: Manufacturer
table_lines.comment: Manufacturer of the Display System.

table_lines.name: Institution Name
table_lines.comment: Institution where the Display System is located.

table_lines.name: Institution Address
table_lines.comment: Mailing address of institution where the Display System is located.

table_lines.name: Device Serial Number
table_lines.comment: Manufacturer's serial number of the Display System.

table_lines.name: Station Name
table_lines.comment: User defined name identifying the Display System.

table_lines.name: Institutional Department Name
table_lines.comment: Department name in the institution where the Display System is located.

table_lines.name: Institutional Department Type Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A coded description of the type of Department or Service within the healthcare facility.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Manufacturer's Model Name
table_lines.comment: Manufacturer's model name of the Display System.

table_lines.name: Date of Manufacture
table_lines.comment: The date the Display System was originally manufactured or re-manufactured (as opposed to refurbished).

table_lines.name: Date of Installation
table_lines.comment: The date the Display System was installed in its current location. The printer may or may not have been used prior to installation in its current location.

table_lines.name: Equipment Administrator Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Point of contact for problems with the equipment.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Person Name
table_lines.comment: Name of the person or role that is administrating the equipment.

table_lines.name: Number of Display Subsystems
table_lines.comment: Number of Display Subsystems in the Display System.

table_lines.name: Display Subsystem Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Description of each Display Subsystem.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Display Subsystem ID
table_lines.comment:
Number that identifies a specific display subsystem within a Display System.
The value shall be unique within the Display Subsystem Sequence (0028,7023).

table_lines.name: >Display Subsystem Name
table_lines.comment: User-defined name for the Display Subsystem.

table_lines.name: >Display Subsystem Description
table_lines.comment: A free text description of the Display Subsystem.

table_lines.name: >Display Device Type Code Sequence
table_lines.comment: Type of technology used in the Display Device.

table_lines.name: >Manufacturer
table_lines.comment:
Manufacturer of the Display Device in the Display Subsystem.
If the Display Subsystem is provided integrated into the Display System (e.g., for a tablet) and the Manufacturer is not otherwise known, the Manufacturer of the Display System may be recorded here.

table_lines.name: >Device Serial Number
table_lines.comment:
Manufacturer's serial number of the Display Device (i.e., monitor device) in the Display Subsystem.
If the Display Subsystem is provided integrated into the Display System (e.g., for a tablet) and the Device Serial Number is not otherwise known, the Device Serial Number of the Display System may be recorded here.

table_lines.name: >Manufacturer's Model Name
table_lines.comment:
Manufacturer's model name of the Display Device in the Display Subsystem.
If the Display Subsystem is provided integrated into the Display System (e.g., for a tablet) and the Model Name is not otherwise known, the Model Name of the Display System may be recorded here.

table_lines.name: >Date of Manufacture
table_lines.comment: The date the Display Device in the Display Subsystem was originally manufactured or re-manufactured (as opposed to refurbished).

table_lines.name: >Date of Installation
table_lines.comment: The date the Display Device in the Display Subsystem was installed in its current location. The printer may or may not have been used prior to installation in its current location.

table_lines.name: >System Status
table_lines.comment:
Current overall status of the Display Subsystem.
See

table_lines.name: >System Status Comment
table_lines.comment: A free text comment about the status of the Display Subsystem.

table_lines.name: >Display Subsystem Configuration Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Available Display Subsystem Configurations.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Configuration ID
table_lines.comment:
Number that identifies a specific display subsystem configuration within the Display Subsystem Configuration Sequence (0028,700A).
The value shall be unique within the Display Subsystem Configuration Sequence (0028,700A).

table_lines.name: >>Configuration Name
table_lines.comment: User-defined name for the Display Subsystem Configuration.

table_lines.name: >>Configuration Description
table_lines.comment: A free text description of the Display Subsystem Configuration.

table_lines.name: >>Referenced Target Luminance Characteristics ID
table_lines.comment:
References the intended luminance characteristics for this Configuration of this Display Subsystem.
The value is the Luminance Characteristics ID (0028,7009) within the Target Luminance Characteristics Sequence (0028,7008) of the

table_lines.name: >Current Configuration ID
table_lines.comment:
References the current configuration of the Display Subsystem.
The value is the Configuration ID (0028,700B) of the Item in the Display Subsystem Configuration Sequence (0028,700A).

table_lines.name: >Measurement Equipment Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes measurement equipment (if any) built into the Display Subsystem.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Measurement Functions
table_lines.comment:
Measurement functions of the measurement equipment.
This multi-valued Attribute shall contain at most one of each enumerated value. When multiple values are present, the equipment is capable of performing multiple functions.

table_lines.name: >>Measured Characteristics
table_lines.comment:
Characteristic(s) which are measured by the measurement equipment.
This multi-valued Attribute shall contain at most one of each enumerated value. When multiple values are present, the equipment is capable of measuring multiple characteristics.

table_lines.name: >>Measurement Equipment Type
table_lines.comment:
Type of measurement equipment.
See

table_lines.name: >>Manufacturer
table_lines.comment: Manufacturer of the measurement equipment.

table_lines.name: >>Manufacturer's Model Name
table_lines.comment: Manufacturer's model name of the measurement equipment.

table_lines.name: >>Device Serial Number
table_lines.comment: The measurement equipment serial number.

table_lines.name: >>Date of Manufacture
table_lines.comment: The date the measurement equipment was originally manufactured or re-manufactured (as opposed to refurbished).

table_lines.name: >>Date of Installation
table_lines.comment: The date the measurement equipment was installed in its current location. The measurement equipment may or may not have been used prior to installation in its current location.

table_lines.name: >>DateTime of Last Calibration
table_lines.comment: Date and time of the last calibration of the measurement equipment.

table_lines.name: Target Luminance Characteristics Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Target luminance characteristics to which the Display Subsystem can be calibrated.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Luminance Characteristics ID
table_lines.comment:
Number that identifies this Luminance Characteristics Item.
The value shall be unique within the Target Luminance Characteristics Sequence (0028,7008).

table_lines.name: >Display Function Type
table_lines.comment:
The type of Display Function used to define the target luminance curve.
See

table_lines.name: >Target Minimum Luminance
table_lines.comment: The minimum luminance value of the target luminance curve, in candelas per square meter (cd/m

table_lines.name: >Target Maximum Luminance
table_lines.comment: The maximum luminance value of the target luminance curve, in candelas per square meter (cd/m

table_lines.name: >Gamma Value
table_lines.comment:
The Gamma value for generating the target luminance curve.
Required if the value of Display Function Type (0028,7019) is GAMMA.

table_lines.name: >Number of Luminance Points
table_lines.comment:
The number of luminance points in the user defined target luminance curve.
Required if the value of Display Function Type (0028,7019) is USER_DEFINED.

table_lines.name: >Luminance Response Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Luminance Response Values for the user defined target luminance curve.
The number of Items shall match the value of Number of Luminance Points (0028,701B).
Required if the value of Display Function Type (0028,7019) is USER_DEFINED.

table_lines.name: >>DDL Value
table_lines.comment:
The integer Digital Driving Level (DDL) for this luminance value.
The DDL Value for the first Item in the Sequence shall be 0. The DDL Value of the last Item in the Sequence shall be the maximum DDL value. Two Items in the Sequence shall not have the same DDL value. The DDL Value of the Items in the Sequence shall increase monotonically.

table_lines.name: >>Luminance Value
table_lines.comment: Luminance in candelas per square meter (cd/m

table_lines.name: >Luminance Response Description
table_lines.comment: User defined text to describe the user defined target luminance curve.

table_lines.name: >CIExy White Point
table_lines.comment:
A single measured White Point recorded for the Display Subsystem.
The white point is recorded as a CIE xy chromaticity with two dimensionless floating point values where the first is the x value and the second is the y value.

table_lines.name: >Reflected Ambient Light
table_lines.comment: Reflected ambient light in candelas per square meter (cd/m

table_lines.name: >Ambient Light Value Source
table_lines.comment:
Source of the reflected ambient light value.
Required if Reflected Ambient Light (2010,0160) is present.

table_lines.name: QA Results Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Results of QA activities.
Exactly one Item shall be included for each Display Subsystem present in the Display System.

table_lines.name: >Display Subsystem ID
table_lines.comment: The Display Subsystem ID of the Item in the Display Subsystem Sequence (0028,7023) to which these results apply.

table_lines.name: >Display Subsystem QA Results Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Results of QA activities for the identified Display Subsystem.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Configuration ID
table_lines.comment:
The Configuration ID of the Item in the Display Subsystem Configuration Sequence (0028,700A) under which the QA was performed.
A given Configuration ID value shall not appear more than once in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Configuration QA Results Sequence
table_lines.comment: Results of QA activities for the identified Display Subsystem in the identified configuration.

table_lines.name: >>>Display Calibration Result Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The most recent calibration result.
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>>Luminance Characteristics ID
table_lines.comment: The Luminance Characteristics ID of the Item in the Target Luminance Characteristics Sequence (0028,7008) that represents the target values used during this calibration.

table_lines.name: >>>Visual Evaluation Result Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The most recent visual evaluation result.
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>Luminance Uniformity Result Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The most recent luminance uniformity result.
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>Luminance Result Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The most recent luminance result.
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Actual Human Performer Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Human performer(s) responsible for the results.

Coded identification of the human performer.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
