table_lines.name: >Human Performer's Name
table_lines.comment: Name of the human performer.

table_lines.name: >Human Performer's Organization
table_lines.comment: Organization to which the human performer is accountable for the results.

table_lines.name: Measurement Equipment Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Describes the measurement equipment (if any) used in deriving the results. This may describe standalone equipment or may re-iterate details of equipment built into the Display System.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Measurement Functions
table_lines.comment:
Measurement functions of the measurement equipment.
This multi-valued Attribute shall contain at most one of each enumerated value. When multiple values are present, the equipment is capable of performing multiple functions.

table_lines.name: >Measured Characteristics
table_lines.comment:
Characteristic(s) which are measured by the measurement equipment.
This multi-valued Attribute shall contain at most one of each enumerated value. When multiple values are present, the equipment is capable of measuring multiple characteristics.

table_lines.name: >Measurement Equipment Type
table_lines.comment:
Type of measurement equipment.
See

table_lines.name: >Manufacturer
table_lines.comment: Manufacturer of the measurement equipment.

table_lines.name: >Manufacturer's Model Name
table_lines.comment: Manufacturer's model name of the measurement equipment.

table_lines.name: >Device Serial Number
table_lines.comment: The measurement equipment serial number.

table_lines.name: >Date of Manufacture
table_lines.comment: The date the measurement equipment was originally manufactured or re-manufactured (as opposed to refurbished).

table_lines.name: >Date of Installation
table_lines.comment: The date the measurement equipment was installed in its current location. The measurement equipment may or may not have been used prior to installation in its current location.

table_lines.name: >DateTime of Last Calibration
table_lines.comment: Date and time of the last calibration of the measurement equipment.

table_lines.name: Visual Evaluation Test Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Test Results of a visual evaluation of the display subsystem output.
May include evaluation of multiple test pattern images, as long as all Items in this Sequence are generated in a single QA test session.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Test Result
table_lines.comment: Result of a test.

table_lines.name: >Test Result Comment
table_lines.comment:
User comment on the result or performance of the test.
Might include scoring values that are not intended to be machine readable.

table_lines.name: >Test Pattern Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Coded identification of the test pattern presented for visual evaluation.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Reference to the Image Instance containing the test pattern presented for visual evaluation.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Test Pattern Code Sequence (0028,702C) is absent in this Item. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >>Test Image Validation
table_lines.comment: Indication of whether the test image was validated as matching the characteristics of the display system (e.g., resolution and bit depth).

table_lines.name: Visual Evaluation Method Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Coded description of the methodology used during this visual evaluation.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Number of Luminance Points
table_lines.comment:
The number of luminance measurements recorded.
The number depends on the test pattern specified in the Measurement Pattern Code Sequence (0028,702D).

table_lines.name: Measurement Pattern Code Sequence
table_lines.comment: Definition of the locations on the display device at which luminance measurements were taken. One measurement is recorded for each location.

table_lines.name: DDL Value
table_lines.comment: The integer Digital Driving Level (DDL) at which the luminance values were measured.

table_lines.name: White Point Flag
table_lines.comment: Whether white point values were also recorded at each location.

table_lines.name: Luminance Response Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Recorded Luminance Response Values
The number of Items shall match the value of Number of Luminance Points (0028, 701B).
The Items shall be stored in major row order (from left to right then from top to bottom).

table_lines.name: >Luminance Value
table_lines.comment: Luminance in candelas per square meter (cd/m

table_lines.name: >CIExy White Point
table_lines.comment:
White Point at the measurement location,
The white point is recorded as a CIE xy chromaticity with two dimensionless floating point values where the first is the x value and the second is the y value.

table_lines.name: Reflected Ambient Light
table_lines.comment: Reflected ambient light in candelas per square meter (cd/m

table_lines.name: Ambient Light Value Source
table_lines.comment: Source of the ambient light value.

table_lines.name: Number of Luminance Points
table_lines.comment: The number of luminance measurements recorded.

table_lines.name: Luminance Response Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Measured Luminance Response Values
The number of Items shall match the value of Number of Luminance Points (0028,701B).

table_lines.name: >DDL Value
table_lines.comment:
The integer Digital Driving Level (DDL) at which this luminance value was measured.
The DDL Value for the first Item in the Sequence shall be 0. The DDL Value of the last Item in the Sequence shall be the maximum DDL value. Two Items in the Sequence shall not have the same DDL value. The DDL Value of the Items in the Sequence shall increase monotonically.

table_lines.name: >Luminance Value
table_lines.comment: Luminance in candelas per square meter (cd/m

table_lines.name: >CIExy White Point
table_lines.comment:
A single measured white point recorded for the display subsystem.
The white point is recorded as a CIE xy chromaticity with two dimensionless floating point values where the first is the x value and the second is the y value.

table_lines.name: Reflected Ambient Light
table_lines.comment: Reflected ambient light in candelas per square meter (cd/m

table_lines.name: Ambient Light Value Source
table_lines.comment: Source of the ambient light value.

table_lines.name: Assessment Label
table_lines.comment: A label that is used to identify this Assessment.

table_lines.name: Assessment Type Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Type of Assessment that was performed.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Assessment Set ID
table_lines.comment: Identifies the set of assessments to which this assessment result belongs.

table_lines.name: Assessment Requester Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The person or device that made the assessment request.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Assessed SOP Instance Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The SOP Instances that were assessed.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Comparison SOP Instance Sequence
table_lines.comment:
SOP Instance(s) used by the assessor to compare to the assessed SOP Instances.
Required if the assessor used comparison SOP Instances.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Assessment Summary
table_lines.comment:
Summary of the assessment result.
The relationship between the values of Observation Type (0082,0008) found and the Assessment Summary value is implementation dependent.

table_lines.name: Assessment Summary Description
table_lines.comment: Human-readable summary description of the assessment result.

table_lines.name: Pertinent Resources Sequence
table_lines.comment:
List of Resources that contain information considered pertinent for the assessment.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Retrieve URI
table_lines.comment: biblio_RFC_3986

table_lines.name: >Resource Description
table_lines.comment: Description or title of the resource.

table_lines.name: Number of Assessment Observations
table_lines.comment: Number of Observations made during the assessment.

table_lines.name: Assessment Observations Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Observations made during the assessment.
Required if Number of Assessment Observations (0082,0006) is not zero.
The number of Items included in the Sequence shall equal the value of Number of Assessment Observations (0082,0006).

table_lines.name: >Observation Significance
table_lines.comment: The significance of this observation regarding the quality or effectiveness of the assessed SOP Instance of this observation.

table_lines.name: >Observation Basis Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Basis on which the Observation was performed.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Observation Description
table_lines.comment: Human-readable description of the Observation.

table_lines.name: >Structured Constraint Observation Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Structured Constraint(s) that were used to make this observation and description of conformance or violation.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Assessed Attribute Value Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The value of the Attribute in the assessed SOP Instance.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Modality
table_lines.comment:
Type of device, process or method to which the protocols in this Series apply.
See

table_lines.comment:
Custodial organization for this Protocol Instance. Represents the organization that is currently in charge of maintaining this protocol Instance.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Institution Name
table_lines.comment: Name of Custodial Institution or Organization.

table_lines.name: >Institution Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Coded identifier of Custodial Institution or Organization.
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Responsible Group Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The department, unit or service that is responsible for the management of this Protocol.
See
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Protocol Name
table_lines.comment: Name for this Protocol.

table_lines.name: Potential Scheduled Protocol Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A list of Protocol Codes for which this Protocol may be considered a match.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Potential Requested Procedure Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A list of Procedure Codes for which this Protocol may be considered a match.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Potential Reasons for Procedure
table_lines.comment:
List of reasons deemed appropriate by the Protocol author for a procedure using this Protocol
Each reason shall be encoded in a separate value of this multi-value Attribute.

table_lines.name: Potential Reasons for Procedure Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
List of reasons deemed appropriate by the Protocol author for a procedure using this Protocol.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Potential Diagnostic Tasks
table_lines.comment:
List of diagnostic tasks deemed appropriate by the Protocol author for a procedure using this Protocol.
E.g., detect collections of blood, identify brain masses.

table_lines.name: Contraindications Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
List of reasons for which the authors of the Protocol deemed it contraindicated.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Predecessor Protocol Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Defined or Performed Procedure Protocol Instances from which this Defined Procedure Protocol was derived.
See
This Attribute is not present in Performed Procedure Protocol Instances since the Referenced Defined Protocol Sequence (0018,990C) is used instead.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Content Creator's Name
table_lines.comment: Name of the most recent person (such as a technologist or physician) to significantly modify the content of this SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: Content Creator's Identification Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identification of the most recent person to significantly modify the content of this SOP Instance.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Protocol Design Rationale
table_lines.comment: Explanation of the rationale behind the selected parameter values or changes to them.

table_lines.name: Protocol Planning Information
table_lines.comment:
Description of details and activities related to planning the execution of this Protocol.
See

table_lines.name: Instance Creation Date
table_lines.comment: Date the Protocol SOP Instance was created.

table_lines.name: Instance Creation Time
table_lines.comment: Time the Protocol SOP Instance was created.

table_lines.name: Referenced Performed Protocol Sequence
table_lines.comment:
References to Performed Protocol Instances describing related prior procedures for this patient.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Clinical Trial Sponsor Name
table_lines.comment:
The name of the clinical trial sponsor.
See

.

.

See

Name of the site responsible for submitting clinical trial data.
See

table_lines.name: Clinical Trial Protocol Ethics Committee Name
table_lines.comment:
Name of the Ethics Committee or Institutional Review Board (IRB) responsible for approval of the Clinical Trial.
Required if Clinical Trial Protocol Ethics Committee Approval Number (0012,0082) is present.

table_lines.name: Clinical Trial Protocol Ethics Committee Approval Number
table_lines.comment: Approval number issued by committee described in Clinical Trial Protocol Ethics Committee Name (0012,0081).

table_lines.name: Ethics Committee Approval Effectiveness Start Date
table_lines.comment: The date the approval identified in Clinical Trial Protocol Ethics Committee Approval Number (0012,0082) becomes effective.

table_lines.name: Ethics Committee Approval Effectiveness End Date
table_lines.comment: The date the approval identified in Clinical Trial Protocol Ethics Committee Approval Number (0012,0082) ceases to be effective.

table_lines.name: Patient Specification Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Constraints on the characteristics of patients to which the protocol is applicable.

table_lines.usage:
Only Attributes defined in the

table_lines.comment:
Modality of the equipment to which the protocol is applicable.

table_lines.comment:
Equipment models/versions.

table_lines.name: >Manufacturer
table_lines.comment: Manufacturer of the equipment.

table_lines.name: >Manufacturer's Related Model Group
table_lines.comment: Name of a group of related equipment models from the Manufacturer (0008,0070) to which the same protocol applies.

Manufacturer's model name of the equipment.

table_lines.name: >Software Versions

Manufacturer's designation of software version of the equipment.

table_lines.comment:
Accessories or options that further specify the model.

table_lines.name: >>Accessory Code
table_lines.comment:
Machine readable identifier for the accessory.
E.g., this may indicate accessory equipment such as cardiac gating equipment.

table_lines.name: >Device Serial Number
table_lines.comment: Serial number of a specific device for which the Protocol is intended.

table_lines.name: >Date of Manufacture
table_lines.comment: The date the equipment was originally manufactured or re-manufactured (as opposed to refurbished).

table_lines.name: >Date of Installation
table_lines.comment: The date the equipment was installed in its current location. The equipment may or may not have been used prior to installation in its current location.

table_lines.name: Instruction Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Instructions relating to preparation and performance of the Protocol.
See
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Instruction Index
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the order in which instruction Sequence Items are performed.
The value shall be an integer, increasing monotonically by 1, starting from 1.

table_lines.name: >Instruction Text
table_lines.comment: A short displayable string indicating what should be done.

table_lines.name: >Instruction Description
table_lines.comment: A detailed description explaining what should be done.

table_lines.name: >Instruction Performed Flag
table_lines.comment:
Whether or not this instruction was followed in the performed Protocol.
Required if the value of SOP Class UID (0008,0016) equals one of the following values:

table_lines.name: >Instruction Performed DateTime
table_lines.comment:
Date and time the instruction was performed.
Required if Instruction Performed Flag (0018,9918) is present with a value of YES.

table_lines.name: >Instruction Performance Comment
table_lines.comment: Comment about how the instruction was actually performed, about the outcome of performing the instruction or about why the instruction was not performed.

table_lines.name: Protocol Defined Patient Position
table_lines.comment:
Patient position relative to the equipment described by the procedure protocol.
See

table_lines.name: Patient Positioning Instruction Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Instructions for positioning and aligning the patient for the procedure. E.g., aligning an anatomical landmark with laser crosshairs.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.
The precise correlation between positioning and scan elements is to be described in the Instruction Text if necessary.

table_lines.name: >Instruction Index
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the order in which instruction Sequence Items are presented/performed.
The value shall be an integer, increasing monotonically by 1, starting from 1.

table_lines.name: >Instruction Text
table_lines.comment: A displayable string explaining what should be done.

table_lines.name: >Instruction Description
table_lines.comment: A detailed description explaining what should be done.

table_lines.name: >Instruction Performed Flag
table_lines.comment:
Whether or not this instruction was performed.
Required if the value of SOP Class UID (0008,0016) equals one of the following values:

table_lines.name: >Instruction Performed DateTime
table_lines.comment:
Date and time the instruction was performed.
Required if Instruction Performed Flag (0018,9918) is present with a value of YES.

table_lines.name: Positioning Method Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the method for positioning the patient.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.comment:
A coded location identifying the intended landmark used as the basis for positioning.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.comment: UID of the Frame of Reference of another data set to which the current procedure is intended to be roughly aligned.

table_lines.name: Target Position Reference Indicator

Position Reference Indicator for the Target Frame of Reference UID (0018,991E).
See

table_lines.comment:
Identifies the general anatomic region imaged by the Protocol.

table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items that modifies the anatomic region of interest of this Instance.

table_lines.comment:
Identifies the primary anatomic structure(s) of interest in this Protocol.

table_lines.comment:
Sequence of Items that modifies the primary anatomic structure of interest in this Instance.

table_lines.comment:
Specification of the acquisition parameters for acquisition protocol elements in an imaging procedure.
There shall be one Item in this Sequence for each Acquisition Protocol Element in the Protocol. See

table_lines.name: >Protocol Element Number
table_lines.comment: The Protocol Element Number of the Acquisition Protocol Element being specified in this Item.

Constraints on one or more acquisition parameters.

table_lines.name: >>Modifiable Constraint Flag
table_lines.comment: Required if the constraint may not be modified, may be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Acquisition Protocol Element Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Parameter values for each Protocol Element in the acquisition protocol. Each Item in the Sequence describes one Element. Elements are performed in the order of their Protocol Element Number (0018,9921).
See
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Acquisition Type
table_lines.comment:
Description of the method used during acquisition.
See

table_lines.name: >Tube Angle
table_lines.comment:
The constant angle at which the X-Ray source is located during acquisition. 0 degrees means that the source is located at the highest point of the gantry orbit. Degrees increase from 0 to positive 360 in a clockwise direction as viewed when facing the gantry where the table enters the gantry.
Required if Acquisition Type (0018,9302) is CONSTANT_ANGLE.

table_lines.name: >Constant Volume Flag
table_lines.comment: Identifies that the acquisition was performed by repetitively acquiring the same volume set over a period of time.

table_lines.name: >Fluoroscopy Flag
table_lines.comment: Identifies that near real-time display of a block of continuously acquired data was performed.

table_lines.name: >Revolution Time
table_lines.comment:
The time in seconds of a complete revolution of the source around the gantry orbit. This value is independent of the Reconstruction Angle (0018,9319) of the frame.
Required if Acquisition Type (0018,9302) is other than CONSTANT_ANGLE.

table_lines.name: >Single Collimation Width
table_lines.comment: The width of a single row of acquired data (in mm).

table_lines.name: >Total Collimation Width
table_lines.comment: The width of the total collimation (in mm) over the area of active X-Ray detection.

table_lines.name: >Table Height
table_lines.comment: The distance in mm from the top of the patient table to the center of rotation of the source (i.e., the data collection center or isocenter). The distance is positive when the table is below the data collection center.

table_lines.name: >Gantry/Detector Tilt
table_lines.comment: Nominal angle of tilt in degrees of the scanning gantry. Not intended for mathematical computations. Zero degrees means the gantry is not tilted, negative degrees are when the top of the gantry is tilted away from where the table enters the gantry.

table_lines.name: >Table Speed
table_lines.comment: The distance in mm that the table moves in one second during the gathering of data.

table_lines.name: >Table Feed per Rotation
table_lines.comment: Motion of the table (in mm) during a complete revolution of the source around the gantry orbit.

table_lines.name: >Spiral Pitch Factor
table_lines.comment: Ratio of the Table Feed per Rotation (0018,9310) to the Total Collimation Width (0018,9307).

table_lines.name: >CTDIvol
table_lines.comment: Required if Acquisition Type (0018,9302) is not CONSTANT_ANGLE. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >CTDI Phantom Type Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Required if CTDIvol (0018,9345) is present.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >CTDIvol Notification Trigger
table_lines.comment:
The threshold for the CTDIvol value, in mGy, at which a dose notification is triggered for this Acquisition Protocol Element.
See

table_lines.name: >DLP Notification Trigger
table_lines.comment:
The threshold for the DLP value, in mGy.cm, at which a dose notification is triggered for this Acquisition Protocol Element.
See

table_lines.name: >Acquisition Motion
table_lines.comment:
Motion of scan progression.
See
The value of NOT_IMPORTANT is not permitted in the Performed Procedure Protocol IOD.

table_lines.name: >Acquisition Start Location Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Anatomically oriented transverse location where this acquisition starts.
Only a single Item is permitted in the Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Acquisition End Location Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Anatomically oriented transverse location where this acquisition ends.
Only a single Item is permitted in the Sequence.

table_lines.name: >CT X-Ray Details Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Parameter values for each of the X-Ray beams in the Acquisition Protocol Element. Each Item in the Sequence describes one X-Ray beam.
See
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Beam Number
table_lines.comment: Identification number of the beam.

table_lines.name: >>KVP
table_lines.comment: Peak kilo voltage output of the X-Ray generator.

table_lines.name: >>Exposure Time in ms
table_lines.comment:
Duration of exposure for this Acquisition Protocol Element in milliseconds.
If Acquisition Type (0018,9302) equals SPIRAL the duration of exposure shall be weighted by the Spiral Pitch Factor (0018,9311).

table_lines.name: >>X-Ray Tube Current in mA
table_lines.comment: Nominal X-Ray tube current in milliamperes.

table_lines.name: >>Exposure in mAs
table_lines.comment: The exposure expressed in milliampere seconds, for example calculated from exposure time and X-Ray tube current.

table_lines.name: >>Auto KVP Selection Type
table_lines.comment: The type of automated selection of the kVp value.

table_lines.name: >>Auto KVP Upper Bound
table_lines.comment: Upper limit on the value of the auto-selected kVp.

table_lines.name: >>Auto KVP Lower Bound
table_lines.comment: Lower limit on the value of the auto-selected kVp.

table_lines.name: >>Exposure Modulation Type
table_lines.comment: A multi-valued label describing the type of current modulation used for the purpose of limiting the dose.

table_lines.name: >>Focal Spot(s)
table_lines.comment: Used nominal size of the focal spot in mm. The Attribute may only have one or two values, for devices with variable focal spot, small dimension followed by large dimension.

table_lines.name: >>Filter Type
table_lines.comment: Type of filter(s) inserted into the X-Ray beam.

table_lines.name: >>Cardiac Synchronization Technique
table_lines.comment:
Cardiac synchronization technique applied during acquisition or processing.
See

table_lines.name: >>Cardiac Signal Source
table_lines.comment:
Source of cardiac synchronization signal.
Required if Cardiac Synchronization Technique (0018,9037) equals other than NONE.

table_lines.name: >>Cardiac RR Interval Specified
table_lines.comment:
R-R interval in ms measured prior to or during the scan.
Required if Cardiac Synchronization Technique (0018,9037) equals other than NONE.

table_lines.name: >>Cardiac Beat Rejection Technique
table_lines.comment:
Cardiac arrhythmia rejection technique.
Required if Cardiac Synchronization Technique (0018,9037) equals PROSPECTIVE or RETROSPECTIVE.

table_lines.name: >>Low R-R Value
table_lines.comment:
R-R interval low limit for beat rejection, in ms.
Required if Cardiac Synchronization Technique (0018,9037) equals PROSPECTIVE or RETROSPECTIVE.

table_lines.name: >>High R-R Value
table_lines.comment:
R-R interval high limit for beat rejection, in ms.
Required if Cardiac Synchronization Technique (0018,9037) equals PROSPECTIVE or RETROSPECTIVE.

table_lines.name: >>Skip Beats
table_lines.comment: Number of beats prescribed to be skipped after each detected arrhythmia.

table_lines.name: >>Cardiac Framing Type
table_lines.comment:
Type of framing performed.
See
Required if type of framing is not time forward from trigger, may be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >>Respiratory Motion Compensation Technique
table_lines.comment:
Technique to reduce respiratory motion artifacts.
See

table_lines.name: >>Respiratory Signal Source
table_lines.comment:
Signal source from which respiratory motion is derived.
Required if Respiratory Motion Compensation Technique (0018,9170) equals other than NONE or BREATH_HOLD. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >>Respiratory Trigger Delay Threshold
table_lines.comment:
Respiratory trigger threshold in percent of the chest expansion for the frame relative to the last Respiratory-Peak.
See
Required if Respiratory Motion Compensation Technique (0018,9170) equals other than NONE, REALTIME or BREATH_HOLD. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >>Respiratory Trigger Type
table_lines.comment:
Characteristic of the respiratory signal used to the define the respiratory triggering.
Required if the value is not TIME. May be present otherwise.

Specification of the parameters for reconstruction of the acquired data of an imaging procedure.
There shall be one Item in this Sequence for each reconstruction protocol element in the Protocol. See
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Protocol Element Number
table_lines.comment: The Protocol Element Number of the Reconstruction Protocol Element being specified in this Item.

table_lines.name: >Parameters Specification Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Constraints on reconstruction parameters.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.usage:
For CT only Attributes defined in

For XA only Attributes defined in

The semantics of values of Constraint Violation Significance (0082,0036) in the Macro are assigned in

The same Attribute shall not appear in more than one Item in the Sequence with the same values for Selector Sequence Pointer (0072,0052) and Selector Sequence Pointer Items (0074,1057).

table_lines.name: >>Modifiable Constraint Flag
table_lines.comment: Required if the constraint may not be modified, may be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Reconstruction Protocol Element Sequence
table_lines.comment: One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Source Acquisition Protocol Element Number
table_lines.comment:
A value corresponding to the Protocol Element Number (0018,9921) of the Acquisition Protocol Element from this Protocol being reconstructed in this reconstruction protocol element.
This may be multi-valued if multiple acquisitions are combined in a single reconstruction protocol element.

table_lines.name: >Source Acquisition Beam Number
table_lines.comment: One or more values corresponding to the Beam Number (300A,00C0) in the Acquisition Protocol Element (specified in Source Acquisition Protocol Element Number (0018,9938) ) from which data was used in this reconstruction protocol element.

table_lines.name: >Referenced SOP Class UID
table_lines.comment:
Uniquely identifies the referenced SOP Class.
Required if the referenced acquisition protocol element is not in this Instance.
Shall have a value of 1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.200.2 (CT Performed Procedure Protocol Storage).

table_lines.name: >Referenced SOP Instance UID
table_lines.comment:
The UID of the Instance containing the acquisition protocol element referenced in Source Acquisition Protocol Element Number (0018,9938).
Required if the referenced acquisition protocol element is not in this Instance.

table_lines.name: >Reconstruction Start Location Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Anatomically oriented transverse location where this reconstruction starts.
Only a single Item is permitted in the Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Reconstruction End Location Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Anatomically oriented transverse location where this reconstruction ends.
Only a single Item is permitted in the Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Reconstruction Algorithm Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Algorithm used in this reconstruction protocol element.
Only a single Item is permitted in the Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Convolution Kernel
table_lines.comment:
A label describing the convolution kernel or algorithm used to reconstruct the data.
A single value shall be present.

table_lines.name: >Convolution Kernel Group
table_lines.comment: A label describing the group that the Convolution Kernel (0018,1210) belongs.

table_lines.name: >Reconstruction Diameter
table_lines.comment: Required if Reconstruction Field of View (0018,9317) is not present.

table_lines.name: >Reconstruction Field of View
table_lines.comment:
The field of view width (x-dimension) followed by height (y-dimension) as used for reconstruction in mm.
Required if Reconstruction Diameter (0018,1100) is not present.

table_lines.name: >Reconstruction Target Center Location Sequence
table_lines.comment: An anatomically based description of a point in the patient used as the reconstruction center target point.

table_lines.name: >Rows
table_lines.comment: Number of rows in the reconstructed image.

table_lines.name: >Columns
table_lines.comment: Number of columns in the reconstructed image.

table_lines.name: >Reconstruction Angle
table_lines.comment: Angle (in degrees) over which the data from which the frame was reconstructed was collected.

table_lines.name: >Image Filter
table_lines.comment: A label describing the filter applied to the reconstructed image after the original reconstruction has been completed.

table_lines.name: >Image Filter Description
table_lines.comment:
A description of the nature or effect of the Image Filter (0018,9320).
E.g., sharpening, noise removing, edge enhancing.

table_lines.name: >Derivation Code Sequence
table_lines.comment: Additional processing applied to the reconstructed image after image filter (if any).

table_lines.name: >Slice Thickness
table_lines.comment: Nominal reconstructed slice thickness, in mm.

table_lines.name: >Spacing Between Slices
table_lines.comment: Spacing between slices, in mm. The spacing is measured from the center-to-center of each slice.

table_lines.name: >Window Center
table_lines.comment: Preferred value for Window Center (0028,1050) in the Image Instances produced by this reconstruction protocol element.

table_lines.name: >Window Width
table_lines.comment: Preferred value for Window Width (0028,1051) in the Image Instances produced by this reconstruction protocol element.

table_lines.name: >Requested Series Description
table_lines.comment: Requested text to copy into the Series Description (0008,103E) of the images resulting from this reconstruction protocol element.

table_lines.name: >Requested Series Description Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A code that is intended to be copied into the Series Description Code Sequence (0008,103F) of instances resulting from this Acquisition Protocol Element.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Content Qualification
table_lines.comment:
Content Qualification Indicator of Instances resulting from this Reconstruction Protocol Element.
See

table_lines.name: Storage Protocol Element Specification Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Specification of the parameters for storage of imaging data.
There shall be one Item in this Sequence for each Storage Protocol Element. See
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Protocol Element Number
table_lines.comment: The Protocol Element Number of the Storage Protocol Element being specified in this Item.

table_lines.name: >Parameters Specification Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Constraints on storage parameters.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.usage:
Only Attributes defined in

The semantics of values of Constraint Violation Significance (0082,0036) in the Macro are assigned in

The same Attribute shall not appear in more than one Item in the Sequence with the same values for Selector Sequence Pointer (0072,0052) and Selector Sequence Pointer Items (0074,1057).

table_lines.name: >>Modifiable Constraint Flag
table_lines.comment: Required if the constraint may not be modified, may be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Storage Protocol Element Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Parameter values for each storage protocol element in the Protocol. The output Instances of the referenced Acquisition or Reconstruction Protocol Elements are stored to the location specified in the Output Information Sequence.
See
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
The performing system might not support the requested storage protocol or not be configured for the desired destination.

table_lines.name: >Source Acquisition Protocol Element Number
table_lines.comment:
A value corresponding to the Element Number (0018,9921) of the Acquisition Protocol Element for which data is stored.
This may be multi-valued if multiple acquisition protocol element data are being stored together.
Required if Source Reconstruction Protocol Element Number (0018,993A) is not present.

table_lines.name: >Source Reconstruction Protocol Element Number
table_lines.comment:
The Element Number (0018,9921) corresponding to the Reconstruction Protocol Element for which data is stored.
This may be multi-valued if multiple reconstruction protocol element data are being stored together.
Required if Source Acquisition Protocol Element Number (0018,9938) is not present.

table_lines.name: >Source Acquisition Beam Number
table_lines.comment:
The Beam Number (300A,00C0) in the Acquisition Protocol Element (specified in Source Acquisition Protocol Element Number (0018,9938) ) for which data is stored. Multiple values may be specified if data for multiple beams is being stored.
Required if:
SOP Class UID (0008,0016) has a value of 1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.200.2 (CT Performed Procedure Protocol Storage) or 1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.200.8 (XA Performed Procedure Protocol Storage), and Source Acquisition Protocol Element Number (0018,9938) is present and only some of the beams in the Acquisition Protocol Element are to be stored.

table_lines.name: >Referenced SOP Class UID
table_lines.comment:
Uniquely identifies the referenced SOP Class.
Required if the referenced acquisition or reconstruction protocol element is not in this Instance.

table_lines.name: >Referenced SOP Instance UID
table_lines.comment:
The UID of the Protocol Instance containing the element referenced in Source Reconstruction Protocol Element Number (0018,993A) or Source Acquisition Protocol Element Number (0018,9938).
Required if the referenced acquisition or reconstruction protocol element is not in this Instance.

table_lines.name: >Output Information Sequence
table_lines.comment:
References to acquired and reconstructed data objects stored as part of this storage protocol element.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Approval Subject Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Instances that are the subject of the Approval Sequence.
All Assertions in the Approval Sequence (0044,0100) apply to all Instances in this Sequence.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Approval Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Recorded approvals of the subject Instances.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.usage:
Assertion Code Sequence (0044,0101) B

The Approver is recorded in the Asserter Identification Sequence inside the

table_lines.name: >Institution Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Institution or organization for which use of the protocol is approved/disapproved or eligible/ineligible for reimbursement.
Required if Assertion Code Sequence (0044,0101) is

table_lines.name: >Clinical Trial Protocol ID
table_lines.comment:
Identifier of the clinical trial protocol for which use of the protocol is approved or disapproved.
Required if Assertion Code Sequence (0044,0101) is

table_lines.name: Modality
table_lines.comment:
Type of device, process or method to which the protocols in this Series apply.
See

table_lines.name: Acquisition Protocol Element Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Parameter values for each Protocol Element in the acquisition protocol. Each item in the sequence describes one Element. Elements are performed in the order of their Protocol Element Number (0018,9921).
See
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Radiation Setting
table_lines.comment: Identify the general level of X-Ray dose exposure.

table_lines.name: >Acquisition Mode
table_lines.comment: Manufacturer-defined name of the acquisition mode described by this Protocol Element.

table_lines.name: >Scan Options
table_lines.comment: Identifies the acquisition technique of this Protocol Element.

table_lines.name: >Dose Mode Name
table_lines.comment: Manufacturer-defined name of the dose level program (e.g. High, Medium, Low).

table_lines.name: >Acquired Subtraction Mask Flag
table_lines.comment: Identifies that the device acquired mask images for subtraction.

table_lines.name: >Fluoroscopy Persistence Flag
table_lines.comment:
Identifies that the device has persistently kept a block of continuously acquired fluoroscopy data. Applicable if the equipment supports local storage of fluoroscopy data.
See

table_lines.name: >Fluoroscopy Last Image Hold Persistence Flag
table_lines.comment:
Identifies that the device has persistently kept the last image of the acquired fluoroscopy data. Applicable if the equipment supports local storage of Fluoro Last Image Hold data.
See

table_lines.name: >Upper Limit Number Of Persistent Fluoroscopy Frames
table_lines.comment: Upper limit of the number of fluoroscopy frames to be persistently kept.

table_lines.name: > Contrast/Bolus Auto Injection Trigger Flag
table_lines.comment: Identifies that the contrast/bolus injection was automatically controlled.

table_lines.name: >Contrast/Bolus Injection Delay
table_lines.comment: Time delay in seconds of the injection of contrast/bolus with respect to the X-Ray start. Negative values mean that injection starts before X-Ray start.

table_lines.name: >Contrast/Bolus Ingredient Opaque
table_lines.comment: Whether the absorption of the contrast/bolus ingredient was greater than the absorption of water (tissue).

table_lines.name: >XA Acquisition Phase Details Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Parameter values for each of the phases. Each item in the sequence describes one phase.
One or more Items are permitted in this sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >>XA Acquisition Duration
table_lines.comment: The time in seconds used for the acquisition of this phase.

table_lines.name: >>XA Acquisition Frame Rate
table_lines.comment: The frame rate in frames per second used for this phase.

table_lines.name: >Planes in Acquisition
table_lines.comment:
The multiplicity of planes that could be used simultaneously during the acquisition.
See

table_lines.name: >XA Plane Details Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Parameter values for each of the planes (or X-Ray beams) operating simultaneously in the Acquisition Protocol Element. Each item in the sequence describes one plane.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Plane Identification
table_lines.comment: Identification of the plane to which the parameters of this sequence item applies.

table_lines.name: >>Beam Number
table_lines.comment:
Identification number of the beam.
The value shall be 1 if Plane Identification (0018,9457) equals MONOPLANE or PLANE A, and shall be 2 if Plane Identification (0018,9457) equals PLANE B.

table_lines.name: >>KVP
table_lines.comment: Peak kilo voltage output of the x-ray generator.

table_lines.name: >>X-Ray Tube Current in mA
table_lines.comment: Nominal X-ray tube current in milliamperes.

table_lines.name: >>Exposure Time in ms
table_lines.comment: Duration of exposure for this Acquisition Protocol Element in milliseconds.

table_lines.name: >>Exposure in mAs
table_lines.comment: The exposure expressed in milliampere seconds, for example calculated from Exposure Time and X-Ray Tube Current.

table_lines.name: >>Average Pulse Width
table_lines.comment: Average width of X-Ray pulse in msec.

table_lines.name: >>Focal Spot(s)
table_lines.comment: Used nominal size of the focal spot in mm. The Attribute may only have one or two values, for devices with variable focal spot, small dimension followed by large dimension.

table_lines.name: >>Acquisition Field Of View Label
table_lines.comment: Manufacturer-defined name of the Field of View label displayed on the acquisition console. Each label corresponds to a FOV dimension applied during the acquisition.

table_lines.name: >>Field of View Dimension(s) in Float
table_lines.comment:
Dimensions in mm of the Field of View, that is the image pixels stored in Pixel Data (7FE0,0010). If Field of View Shape (0018,1147) is:
RECTANGLE: row dimension followed by column.
ROUND: diameter.
HEXAGONAL: diameter of the circle circumscribing the hexagon.

table_lines.name: >>X-Ray Filter Details Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Parameter values for each of the filters inserted simultaneously into the X-Ray beam. Each item in the sequence describes one filter.
One or more Items shall be included in this sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>Filter Thickness Minimum
table_lines.comment: The minimum thickness in mm of the X-Ray absorbing material used in the filters. May be multi-valued, with values corresponding to the respective values in Filter Material (0018,7050).

table_lines.name: >>>Filter Thickness Maximum
table_lines.comment: The maximum thickness in mm of the X-Ray absorbing material used in the filters. May be multi-valued, with values corresponding to the respective values in Filter Material (0018,7050).

table_lines.name: >>>Filter Type
table_lines.comment: Type of filter(s) inserted into the X-Ray beam (e.g., wedges).

table_lines.name: >>>Filter Material
table_lines.comment: The X-Ray absorbing material used in the filter.

table_lines.name: >>Detector Binning
table_lines.comment: Number of active detectors used to generate a single pixel. Specified as number of row detectors per pixel then column.

table_lines.name: >>Bits Stored
table_lines.comment: Number of bits stored for each pixel sample in the acquired images.

table_lines.name: >>Rows
table_lines.comment: Number of rows in the acquired images.

table_lines.name: >>Columns
table_lines.comment: Number of columns in the acquired images.

table_lines.name: >>Primary Positioner Scan Start Angle
table_lines.comment:
Start position of the primary positioner in degrees.
Applicable only to protocol elements for rotational acquisitions, i.e., Scan Options (0018,0022) equals ROTA.

table_lines.name: >>Secondary Positioner Scan Start Angle
table_lines.comment:
Start position of the secondary positioner in degrees.
Applicable only to protocol elements for rotational acquisitions, i.e., Scan Options (0018,0022) equals ROTA.

table_lines.name: >>Primary Positioner Scan Arc
table_lines.comment:
Total amount of rotation of the primary positioner in degrees.
Applicable only to protocol elements for rotational acquisitions, i.e. Scan Options (0018,0022) equals ROTA.

table_lines.name: >>Secondary Positioner Scan Arc
table_lines.comment:
Total amount of rotation of the secondary positioner in degrees.
Applicable only to protocol elements for rotational acquisitions, i.e., Scan Options (0018,0022) equals ROTA.

table_lines.name: >>Primary Positioner Increment
table_lines.comment:
Constant increment of the primary positioner angle in degrees. Positive increment indicates an increasing value of the primary positioner angle.
Applicable only to protocol elements for rotational acquisitions, i.e., Scan Options (0018,0022) equals ROTA.

table_lines.name: >>Secondary Positioner Increment
table_lines.comment:
Constant increment of the secondary positioner angle in degrees. Positive increment indicates an increasing value of the secondary positioner angle.
Applicable only to protocol elements for rotational acquisitions, i.e., Scan Options (0018,0022) equals ROTA.

table_lines.name: >>Distance Source to Detector
table_lines.comment:
Distance from source to receptor plane perpendicular to the receptor plane in mm.
Applicable only to protocol elements for rotational acquisitions, i.e., Scan Options (0018,0022) equals ROTA.

table_lines.name: >Requested Series Description
table_lines.comment: Text that is intended to be copied into the Series Description (0008,103E) of the images resulting from this Acquisition Protocol Element.

table_lines.name: >Requested Series Description Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A code that is intended to be copied into the Series Description Code Sequence (0008,103F) of the images resulting from this Acquisition Protocol Element.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Content Qualification
table_lines.comment:
Content Qualification Indicator of instances resulting from this Acquisition Protocol Element.
See

table_lines.name: Reconstruction Protocol Element Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Parameter values for each reconstruction protocol element in the Protocol. Elements are performed in the order of their Protocol Element Number (0018,9921).
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Source Acquisition Protocol Element Number
table_lines.comment:
A value corresponding to the Protocol Element Number (0018,9921) of the Acquisition Protocol Element from this Protocol being reconstructed in this reconstruction protocol element.
This may be multivalued if multiple acquisitions are combined in a single reconstruction protocol element.

table_lines.name: >Source Acquisition Beam Number
table_lines.comment: One or more values corresponding to the Beam Number (300A,00C0) in the Acquisition Protocol Element (specified in Source Acquisition Protocol Element Number (0018,9938)) from which data was used in this reconstruction protocol element.

table_lines.name: >Referenced SOP Class UID
table_lines.comment:
Uniquely identifies the referenced SOP Class.
Required if the referenced acquisition protocol element is not in this instance.
Shall have a value of 1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.200.8 (XA Performed Procedure Protocol Storage).

table_lines.name: >Referenced SOP Instance UID
table_lines.comment:
The UID of the instance containing the acquisition protocol element referenced in Source Acquisition Protocol Element Number (0018,9938).
Required if the referenced acquisition protocol element is not in this instance.

table_lines.name: >Reconstruction Pipeline Type
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the type of pipeline of the reconstruction.
See

table_lines.name: >Window Center
table_lines.comment: Preferred value for Window Center (0028,1050) in the image instances produced by this reconstruction protocol element.

table_lines.name: >Window Width
table_lines.comment: Preferred value for Window Width (0028,1051) in the image instances produced by this reconstruction protocol element.

table_lines.name: >Image Filter Details Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Description of image filters applied to the reconstructed image. The filters are applied in the order of the sequence items.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Image Filter
table_lines.comment: A label identifying the filter applied to the reconstructed image.

table_lines.name: >>Image Filter Description
table_lines.comment:
A description of the nature or effect of the Image Filter (0018,9320).
E.g., sharpening, noise removing, edge enhancing, metal artifact reduction.

table_lines.name: >Applied Mask Subtraction Flag
table_lines.comment: Identifies that a subtraction mask was applied.

table_lines.name: >Mask Visibility Percentage
table_lines.comment:
The percentage of visibility of the mask frame during the subtraction.
A value of 0 corresponds to subtracted display, a value of 100 corresponds to un-subtracted display (native). See Section C.8.19.7.1.

table_lines.name: >Rows
table_lines.comment: Number of rows in the reconstructed image.

table_lines.name: >Columns
table_lines.comment: Number of columns in the reconstructed image.

table_lines.name: >Image Rotation
table_lines.comment: Rotation of the image clockwise in degrees, before the Image Horizontal Flip (0070,0041) is applied.

table_lines.name: >Image Horizontal Flip
table_lines.comment: Whether or not the image horizontal flip is applied after any Image Rotation has been applied such that the left side of the image becomes the right side.

table_lines.name: >Algorithm Type
table_lines.comment: Type of algorithm used to create the 3D reconstruction.

table_lines.name: >Convolution Kernel
table_lines.comment:
A label describing the convolution kernel or algorithm used to perform 3D reconstruction of the data.
A single value shall be present.

table_lines.name: >Number Of Slices
table_lines.comment: Number of slices in the 3D reconstructed image.

table_lines.name: >Slice Thickness
table_lines.comment: Nominal 3D reconstructed slice thickness, in mm.

table_lines.name: >Spacing Between Slices
table_lines.comment: Spacing between 3D reconstructed slices, in mm. The spacing is measured from the center-to-center of each slice.

table_lines.name: >Reconstruction Field of View
table_lines.comment: The field of view width (x-dimension) followed by height (y-dimension) as used for 3D reconstruction in mm.

table_lines.name: >Derivation Code Sequence
table_lines.comment: Additional processing applied to the reconstructed image after image filter (if any).

table_lines.name: >Requested Series Description
table_lines.comment: Text that is intended to be copied into the Series Description (0008,103E) of the images resulting from this Reconstruction Protocol Element.

table_lines.name: >Requested Series Description Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A code that is intended to be copied into the Series Description Code Sequence (0008,103F) of the images resulting from this Reconstruction Protocol Element.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Content Qualification
table_lines.comment:
Content Qualification Indicator of instances resulting from this Reconstruction Protocol Element.
See

table_lines.name: Measurement Units Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Units of distance for the coordinate system for the encapsulated 3D Manufacturing Model file.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Model Modification
table_lines.comment: Specifies whether a modification of the observed anatomy (other than mirroring) was used to create the model (e.g. simulating an expected surgical result). In the negative, the model follows the observed patient anatomy in the source data.

table_lines.name: Model Mirroring
table_lines.comment: Specifies whether mirroring of anatomy from the other side of the patient was used to create the model.

table_lines.name: Model Usage Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the use for which the manufactured object is intended.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Content Description
table_lines.comment: A description of the model.

table_lines.name: Icon Image Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A preview image representing the rendered model.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Derivation Algorithm Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Software algorithm that created the 3D model.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Model Group UID
table_lines.comment: Uniquely identifies a group to which the model belongs. Manufacturing models that share the same Model Group UID are considered distinct parts within the same assembly.

table_lines.name: Recommended Display CIELab Value
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the color recommended to be used for the model. This color applies both when digitally displaying the model and when selecting material for manufacturing.
This would typically be used to visually distinguish between models that are part of the same assembly and/or provide best analog to real world appearance.
The units are specified in PCS-Values, and the value is encoded as CIELab.
This value may be superseded by individual colors that have been specified inside the encapsulated model (when the encapsulated format allows this).
See

table_lines.name: Recommended Presentation Opacity
table_lines.comment:
Specifies the opacity recommended to be used for the model. This opacity applies both when digitally displaying the model and when selecting material for manufacturing.
A non-opaque value would typically be specified when either (a) another model grouped in the same assembly needs to be visible behind or inside this model, or (b) the model represents anatomy that is not fully opaque.
If not present, then it is assumed the model should be presented and manufactured as opaque.
See

table_lines.name: Fraction Pattern Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The pattern of delivery of fractions within and across days of the week in a machine-readable form.
Required if a fraction pattern has been defined.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Number of Fraction Pattern Digits Per Day
table_lines.comment:
The maximum number of fractions encodable within a day in a Fraction Pattern (3010,0087).
Required if Weekday Fraction Pattern Sequence (3010,0087) is present.
See

table_lines.name: >Repeat Fraction Cycle Length
table_lines.comment:
Number of weeks needed to describe fraction pattern.
Required if Weekday Fraction Pattern Sequence (3010,0087) is present.
See

table_lines.name: >Weekday Fraction Pattern Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of week-day based fraction patterns.
Each Item represents an alternative pattern.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >>Fraction Pattern
table_lines.comment:
String of 0's (no treatment) and 1's (treatment) describing the fraction pattern for the fractions defined by this set. Length of string is 7 x Number of Fraction Pattern Digits Per Day x Repeat Fraction Cycle Length. The first character of the string represents Monday.
See

table_lines.name: >>Intended Start Day of Week
table_lines.comment:
String of 0's (no treatment) and 1's (treatment) describing the intended start fraction for this set. Length of string is 7 x Number of Fraction Pattern Digits Per Day x Repeat Fraction Cycle Length. The first character of the string represents Monday.
See

table_lines.name: >Minimum Hours between Fractions
table_lines.comment:
Minimum number of hours between consecutive fractions.
Consecutive fractions are given in Number of Fraction Pattern Digits Per Day (300A,0079).

table_lines.name: >Intended Fraction Start Time
table_lines.comment: The intended time(s) of day when the first RT Treatment Fraction of the day should be started.

table_lines.name: RT Treatment Phase Index
table_lines.comment: Index of the RT Treatment Phase in the Sequence.

table_lines.name: RT Treatment Phase UID
table_lines.comment: A UID by which this RT Treatment Phase can be referenced.

table_lines.name: Intended Phase Start Date
table_lines.comment:
The date when this treatment phase is intended to start.
See

table_lines.name: Intended Phase End Date
table_lines.comment:
The date when this treatment phase is intended to be completed.
See

C.36.2.1.3-1.table_caption: RT Treatment Phase Interval Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: RT Treatment Phase Interval Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Intervals between treatment phases.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >Basis RT Treatment Phase Index
table_lines.comment:
The RT Treatment Phase which provides the basis for this interval.
This index corresponds to an Item in the Intended RT Treatment Phase Sequence (3010,004B).
See

table_lines.name: >Related RT Treatment Phase Index
table_lines.comment:
The RT Treatment Phase which is related to the phase identified by Basis RT Treatment Phase Index (3010,003E). Each RT Treatment Phase Index value shall appear in this Attribute in only one Item within this Sequence.
This index corresponds to an Item in the Intended RT Treatment Phase Sequence (3010,004B).
See

table_lines.name: >Temporal Relationship Interval Anchor
table_lines.comment:
The anchor point of the interval specified in this Item with respect to the phase referenced by the Basis RT Treatment Phase Index (3010,003E).
Required if a value is present in Minimum Number of Interval Days (3010,0050) or Maximum Number of Interval Days (3010,0051).

table_lines.name: >Minimum Number of Interval Days
table_lines.comment:
The minimum number of days that the start of the related phase should follow the basis phase referenced in Basis RT Treatment Phase Index (3010,003E).
Fractional values are allowed. Negative values are allowed if Temporal Relationship Interval Anchor (3010,004F) has a value of END.

table_lines.name: >Maximum Number of Interval Days
table_lines.comment:
The maximum number of days that the start of the related phase should follow the basis phase referenced Basis RT Treatment Phase Index (3010,003E).
Fractional values are allowed. Negative values are allowed if Temporal Relationship Interval Anchor (3010,004F) has a value of END.

table_lines.name: Dosimetric Objective UID
table_lines.comment:

table_lines.name: Absolute Dosimetric Objective Flag
table_lines.comment:
Whether the objective must be met by the resulting Radiotherapy treatment plan.
Detecting whether or not a Radiotherapy treatment plan has met this Dosimetric Objective and how this situation is handled is out of scope of the Standard.

table_lines.name: Dosimetric Objective Purpose
table_lines.comment: The purpose for which the objective is to be used.

table_lines.comment:
The description of the method used to calculate the effective dose.

table_lines.comment:
Manufacturer's Unique Identifier (UID) for the class of the device.

A class allows definition of a group of devices with a similar set of capabilities.

table_lines.name: Institution Name

table_lines.name: Institution Address

Patient support device definitions.

Distance in mm from the reference location as specified by RT Device Distance Reference Location Code Sequence (300A,0659) to the RT Accessory Device Slot.

table_lines.name: Referenced RT Accessory Holder Device Index

table_lines.comment:
Patient positions during treatment, being prescribed or recorded.

May be present otherwise.

table_lines.comment:
Index of this Item in this Sequence.
The value shall start at 1 and increase monotonically by 1.

C.36.2.2.5-1.table_caption: RT Control Point General Macro Attributes

table_lines.name: RT Control Point Index
table_lines.comment:
The index of the RT Control Point within the Sequence where this Macro is included.
RT Control Points shall be executed in the order of the RT Control Point Index.
The value shall start at 1 and increase monotonically by 1 within the Sequence where this Macro is included.

table_lines.name: Cumulative Meterset
table_lines.comment:
Meterset at the RT Control Point.
The units are specified by Radiation Dosimeter Unit Sequence (300A,0658).
For the Item with RT Control Point Index equal 1, the Cumulative Meterset shall be equal to 0.0.
Required if RT Radiation Physical and Geometric Content Detail Flag (300A,0638) equals FULL or IDENT_ONLY or RT Record Flag (300A,0639) equals YES and if the conditions in
May be present otherwise only if the conditions in
See

table_lines.name: Referenced Treatment Position Index
table_lines.comment:
The value of Treatment Position Index (300A,0606) from the Treatment Position Sequence (300A,063F) within this IOD that this RT Control Point refers to.
Required if Treatment Position Sequence (300A,063F) is present and the conditions in

table_lines.name: Recorded RT Control Point DateTime
table_lines.comment:
Date and time of the Recorded RT Control Point.
For all but the final Control Point this shall be the date and time when the delivery of radiation at this Control Point began. For the final Control Point this shall be the date and time when the previous control point ended.
Required if RT Record Flag (300A,0639) equals YES and if the SOP Class of the SOP Instance including this Module is not RT Radiation Salvage Record Storage ("1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.481.17").
May be present otherwise only if RT Record Flag (300A,0639) equals YES.

table_lines.name: Referenced Radiation RT Control Point Index
table_lines.comment:
The value of RT Control Point Index (300A,0600) of the RT Control Point in the RT Radiation SOP Instance referenced by Referenced RT Instance Sequence (300A,0631) in this Instance.
Required if RT Record Flag (300A,0639) equals YES and if the recorded RT Control Point Index corresponds to a planned RT Radiation Control Point Index.

table_lines.name: Delivery Rate

The unit of the delivery rate value.

table_lines.name: Beam Area Limit Sequence

Area within which the treatment beam must be contained, for example when using MLC tracking for a moving target.

Required if beam shall be limited.

table_lines.usage: The Outline is defined on the Beam Modifier Definition Plane.

table_lines.name: Number of Radiation Generation Modes
table_lines.comment:
Number of Radiation Generation Modes defined in the Radiation Generation Mode Sequence (300A,067B).
The Number shall be greater than zero.
Required if RT Radiation Physical and Geometric Content Detail Flag (300A,0638) equals FULL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Radiation Generation Mode Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Radiation Generation Modes defining the type of radiation and characteristics of the beam generated.
Radiation Generation Modes shall characterize different primary beam fluence.
The number of Items included in this Sequence shall equal the value of Number of Radiation Generation Modes(300A,0685).
Required if Number of Radiation Generation Modes (300A,0685) is present.

table_lines.name: >Radiation Generation Mode Index
table_lines.comment:
Index of this Item in this Sequence.
The value shall start at 1 and increase monotonically by 1.

table_lines.name: >Radiation Generation Mode Label
table_lines.comment:
User-defined label that identifies this Radiation Generation Mode.
See

table_lines.name: >Radiation Generation Mode Description
table_lines.comment: User-defined description of the Radiation Generation Mode.

table_lines.name: >Radiation Generation Mode Machine Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A vendor-specified machine-readable code that unambiguously identifies this Radiation Generation Mode.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if RT Radiation Physical and Geometric Content Detail Flag (300A,0638) equals FULL. May be present otherwise.
See

table_lines.name: >Radiation Type Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Type of radiation for this Radiation Generation Mode.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Energy Unit Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The unit of energy values specified in Nominal Energy (300A,0680), Minimum Nominal Energy (300A,0681), Maximum Nominal Energy (300A,0682).
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Nominal Energy
table_lines.comment:
The nominal beam energy in units as defined in the Energy Unit Code Sequence (300A,0684).
Required if Minimum Nominal Energy (300A,0681) and Maximum Nominal Energy (300A,0682) are not present.
See

table_lines.name: >Minimum Nominal Energy
table_lines.comment:
The minimum nominal beam energy in units as defined in the Energy Unit Code Sequence (300A,0684).
Required if Nominal Energy (300A,0680) is not present.
See

table_lines.name: >Maximum Nominal Energy
table_lines.comment:
The maximum nominal beam energy in units as defined in the Energy Unit Code Sequence (300A,0684).
Required if Nominal Energy (300A,0680) is not present.
See

table_lines.name: >Radiation Fluence Modifier Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identifies the type of fluence modifier of this Radiation Generation Mode.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Radiation Device Configuration and Commissioning Key Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Keys identifying the configuration and commissioning data used as input for treatment planning of this Instance.
Value Type (0040,A040) is constrained to value UIDREF.
See
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

Number of RT Beam Limiting Devices in the RT Beam Limiting Device Definition Sequence (300A,064D).

Beam limiting device (collimator), such as jaw or leaf (element) sets.

table_lines.comment:

table_lines.name: RT Beam Limiting Device Opening Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Beam limiting device (collimator) settings defining the opening for the current Control Point.
Required if Number of RT Beam Limiting Device Openings (300A,0657) is present and has a non-zero value and the conditions in
The number of Items included in this Sequence shall equal the value of Number of RT Beam Limiting Device Openings (300A,0657).

table_lines.name: Number of Wedges
table_lines.comment:
Number of Wedges defined in the Wedge Definition Sequence (300A,0651).

Treatment wedge definitions.
Required if Number of Wedges (300A,00D0) is present and has a non-zero value.
The number of Items included in this Sequence shall equal the value of Number of Wedges(300A,00D0).

table_lines.name: >Device Index
table_lines.comment:
Index of this Item in this Sequence.
The value shall start at 1 and increase monotonically by 1.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Defined Device Index
table_lines.comment:
Device Index value that links the device defined by this Sequence Item to the corresponding device in an RT Radiation Instance. The device identification of the two devices may or may not be the same.
The value is the index of a device in the Wedges Definition Sequence (300A,0651) within the single SOP Instance referenced by Referenced RT Instance Sequence (300A,0631).
Required if the Instance referenced in Referenced RT Instance Sequence (300A,0631) contains the device that corresponds to the device defined by this Sequence Item.

table_lines.comment:
Nominal wedge angle in degrees.

Effective wedge angle in degrees.
See

table_lines.name: >Beam Modifier Orientation Angle

The direction from thick edge to thin edge is along the positive y-axis of the Beam Modifier Definition Plane.
See

table_lines.name: Number of Wedge Positions
table_lines.comment:
Number of Wedge Positions defined in the Wedge Position Sequence (300A,0116).
Required if Number of Wedges (300A,00D0) is present and has a non-zero value.

table_lines.name: Wedge Position Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Position for each Wedge for the current Control Point.
Required if Number of Wedge Positions (300A,0655) is present and has a non-zero value and the conditions in
The number of Items included in this Sequence shall equal the value of Number of Wedge Positions (300A,0655).

table_lines.name: >Referenced Device Index
table_lines.comment: The value of Device Index (3010,0039) in Wedge Definition Sequence (300A,0651) for the Wedge being used.

table_lines.name: >Wedge Position
table_lines.comment: Position of Wedge at current Control Point.

table_lines.name: >Radiation Beam Wedge Thin Edge Distance
table_lines.comment:
Closest distance in mm from the central axis of the beam along the wedge angle direction to the thin edge as projected on the Beam Modifier Definition Plane defined by the RT Beam Modifier Definition Distance (300A,0688).
The value is negative if the thin edge is located on the positive y-axis, and is positive otherwise.
Required if Wedge Position (300A,0118) is PARTIAL.
See

table_lines.name: Number of Compensators
table_lines.comment:
Number of Compensators defined in the Compensator Definition Sequence (300A,0662).
Required if RT Radiation Physical and Geometric Content Detail Flag (300A,0638) equals FULL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Compensator Definition Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Treatment compensator definitions.
Required if Number of Compensators (300A,00E0) is present and has a non-zero value.
The number of Items included in this Sequence shall equal the value of Number of Compensators (300A,00E0).

table_lines.name: >Device Index
table_lines.comment:
Index of the Device in this Sequence.
The value shall start at 1 and increase monotonically by 1.

table_lines.comment:
Device Index value that links the device defined by this Sequence Item to the corresponding device in an RT Radiation Instance. The device identification of the two devices may or may not be the same.
The value is the index of a device in the Compensator Definition Sequence (300A,0662) within the single SOP Instance referenced by Referenced RT Instance Sequence (300A,0631).
Required if the Instance referenced in Referenced RT Instance Sequence (300A,0631) contains the device that corresponds to the device defined by this Sequence Item.
See

table_lines.name: >Compensator Base Plane Offset
table_lines.comment:
The distance in mm between the mounting plane and the base plane of the compensator.
The value shall be positive when the base plane is farther away from the reference location (as specified by RT Device Distance Reference Location Code Sequence (300A,0659) ) than the mounting plane.
Required if RT Radiation Physical and Geometric Content Detail Flag (300A,0638) equals FULL. May be present otherwise.
See

table_lines.name: >Compensator Map Orientation
table_lines.comment:
Side of the compensator base that the compensator surface shape faces.
Required if RT Radiation Physical and Geometric Content Detail Flag (300A,0638) equals FULL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Compensator Shape Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Description of the shape of the Compensator and the fabrication parameters.
Required if RT Radiation Physical and Geometric Content Detail Flag (300A,0638) equals FULL. May be present otherwise.
Only one Item shall be present.

table_lines.name: >>Compensator Divergence
table_lines.comment: Whether or not the compensator is shaped according to the beam geometrical divergence.

table_lines.name: >>Material ID
table_lines.comment: User-defined identifier for the material used to manufacture the Compensator.

table_lines.name: >>Compensator Proximal Thickness Map
table_lines.comment:
A data stream of triplets of x, y and thickness in mm representing a map of the coordinates in the Beam Modifier Definition Plane and thicknesses from the compensator base plane. The order of triplets is not significant.
Required if Compensator Map Orientation (300A,0663) is SOURCE_SIDE or DOUBLE_SIDED.
See

table_lines.name: >>Compensator Distal Thickness Map
table_lines.comment:
A data stream of triplets of x, y and thickness in mm representing a map of the coordinates in the Beam Modifier Definition Plane and thicknesses from the compensator base plane. The order of triplets is not significant.
Required if Compensator Map Orientation (300A,0663) is PATIENT_SIDE or DOUBLE_SIDED.
See

table_lines.name: >>Compensator Shape Fabrication Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The method of fabrication, such as shape of tools to be used, surface modeling technique.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Radiation Beam Compensator Milling Tool Diameter
table_lines.comment: The diameter in mm of the milling tool to be used to create the compensator. The diameter is expressed as the actual physical size and not a size projected on the Beam Modifier Definition Plane.

table_lines.name: Number of Blocks
table_lines.comment:
Number of Blocks defined in the Block Definition Sequence (300A,066A).
Required if RT Radiation Physical and Geometric Content Detail Flag (300A,0638) is FULL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: Block Definition Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Block definitions.
Required if Number of Blocks (300A,00F0) is present and has a non-zero value.
The number of Items included in this Sequence shall equal the value of Number of Blocks (300A,00F0).
Only one Item in this Sequence shall have

table_lines.comment:
Device Index value that links the device defined by this Sequence Item to the corresponding device in an RT Radiation Instance. The device identification of the two devices may or may not be the same.
The value is the index of a device in the Block Definition Sequence (300A,066A) within the single SOP Instance referenced by Referenced RT Instance Sequence (300A,0631).
Required if the Instance referenced in Referenced RT Instance Sequence (300A,0631) contains the device that corresponds to the device defined by this Sequence Item.
See

table_lines.name: >Material ID
table_lines.comment: User-defined identifier for material used to manufacture the Block.

table_lines.name: >Block Divergence
table_lines.comment:
Whether or not the block is shaped according to the beam geometrical divergence.
Required if RT Radiation Physical and Geometric Content Detail Flag (300A,0638) equals FULL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Block Orientation
table_lines.comment:
Specifies on which side of the block base the block extends.
Required if RT Radiation Physical and Geometric Content Detail Flag (300A,0638) equals FULL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Radiation Beam Block Thickness
table_lines.comment:
Physical thickness of block in mm parallel to the central radiation beam axis.
Required if Material ID (300A,00E1) has a value. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Block Edge Data Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Block Edge Data streams.
The polygons represented by the Block Edge Data (300A,066B) data streams in all Items in this Sequence shall be non-overlapping.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Block Edge Data
table_lines.comment:
A data stream of coordinate pairs in mm representing a polygon which comprise the block edge.
The polygon is implicitly closed from the last pair to the origin pair and all edges shall be non-intersecting except at the vertices. Any given coordinate pair shall only occur once in the data stream.
Coordinates are projected on the Beam Modifier Definition Plane.

table_lines.name: >Number of Block Slab Items
table_lines.comment:
Number of slabs composing the block if the block has been sliced parallel to the Beam Modifier Definition Plane. If the block has not been sliced the value shall be zero.
Required if RT Radiation Physical and Geometric Content Detail Flag (300A,0638) equals FULL. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Block Slab Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of slab(s) that comprise the block.
Required if Number of Block Slab Items (300A,0440) is present and has a value greater than 1.
The number of Items included in this Sequence shall equal the value of Number of Block Slab Items (300A,0440).

table_lines.name: >>Block Slab Number
table_lines.comment:
Identification number of the Block Slab.
The value shall start at 1, and increase monotonically by 1.
The number indicates the order of the slabs with respect to the source, where Number 1 corresponds to the slab nearest to the source.

table_lines.name: >>Radiation Beam Block Slab Thickness
table_lines.comment:
Physical thickness of block slab in mm in a direction parallel to the radiation beam axis.
The sum of Radiation Beam Block Slab Thickness (300A,066E) values in all Items of this Sequence must equal the Radiation Beam Block Thickness (300A,066D) of the block.

table_lines.name: >>Device Alternate Identifier
table_lines.comment: An identifier intended to be read by a device such as a bar code reader.

table_lines.name: >>Device Alternate Identifier Type
table_lines.comment:
Defines the type of Device Alternate Identifier.
Required if Device Alternate Identifier (3010,001B) has a value.

table_lines.name: >>Device Alternate Identifier Format
table_lines.comment:
Description of the format in which the Device Alternate Identifier (3010,001B) is issued.

table_lines.comment: Indicates whether the RT Accessory Holder has slots in which other RT Accessory Holders or beam modifying devices can be inserted.
