Slots being available in this Accessory Holder.

May be present if RT Accessory Holder Slot Existence Flag (300A,060F) has the value YES.

table_lines.comment: The ID of the slot where accessories are inserted.

table_lines.name: >>RT Accessory Holder Slot Distance
table_lines.comment: Distance in mm from the reference location as specified by RT Device Distance Reference Location Code Sequence (300A,0659) to the slot along the radiation beam axis.

table_lines.name: Number of General Accessories

Weight of importance to be applied to the Dosimetric Objective. A higher value means that this objective is more important. Values are only meaningful within the Items in this Sequence. The use of weight value in the process of optimization and treatment parameter definition is implementation-dependent.
Required if Absolute Dosimetric Objective Flag (3010,0073) is NO.

table_lines.comment:

table_lines.name: >>Conceptual Volume Optimization Precedence
table_lines.comment:
Value used to resolve usage of overlapping regions of Conceptual Volumes during dose optimization.
An overlapping region is part of the Conceptual Volume(s) with the lowest number. An overlapping region is not part of any other Conceptual Volume with a higher number.
Overlapping regions with equal precedence are part of all Conceptual Volumes with the same value.
Any number takes precedence over an empty value.

table_lines.name: >>Conceptual Volume Blocking Constraint
table_lines.comment:
Constraints on primary radiation passing through the current Conceptual Volume.
Primary Radiation is defined as modulated or shaped radiation, as opposed to scattered radiation or transmission radiation.

table_lines.name: >>Conceptual Volume Category Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:

Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Conceptual Volume Type Code Sequence

table_lines.comment: Value of RT Prescription Index (3010,003C) in the RT Prescription Sequence (3010,006B) specifying the prescription to which the current prescription is related.

table_lines.name: >>Fraction-Based Relationship Interval Anchor
table_lines.comment: The anchor point of this RT Prescription Sequence Item with respect to the prescription referenced by Referenced RT Prescription Index (3010,0041).

table_lines.name: >>Number of Interval Fractions
table_lines.comment:
The interval expressed in number of fractions. The Fraction-Based Relationship Interval Anchor (3010,0083) establishes the anchor point to which the interval is tied.
A value of 0 means that the current prescription is intended to start simultaneously with the anchor of the related prescription.
If Fraction-Based Relationship Interval Anchor (3010,0083) equals START, the value shall be 0 or positive. This is the number of fractions after the first fraction of the delivery of the referenced prescription that the delivery of the current prescription is intended to start.
If Fraction-Based Relationship Interval Anchor (3010,0083) equals END, the value shall be negative or 0. This is the number of fractions prior to the last fraction of the delivery of the referenced prescription that the delivery of the current prescription is intended to start.

table_lines.comment:

table_lines.comment: DateTime when Treatment Tolerance Violation occurred.

table_lines.name: >Treatment Tolerance Violation Category
table_lines.comment: The category of tolerance violation which was exceeded.

table_lines.comment:

table_lines.comment:
Cause of treatment tolerance violation.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Treatment Tolerance Violation Attribute Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The Attribute whose value exceeded the tolerance.
Required if the violation corresponds to an Attribute in the current SOP Instance.
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Treatment Tolerance Violation Identification
table_lines.comment:
An identification of the parameter(s) which exceeded the tolerance, intended for structured processing.
Required if Treatment Tolerance Violation Attribute Sequence (300A,0733) is not present or has zero Items. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Treatment Tolerance Violation Description
table_lines.comment:
User-defined description of the treatment tolerance violation.
This information is intended for display to human readers. Shall not be used for structured processing.
Required if Treatment Tolerance Violation Attribute Sequence (300A,0733) is not present or has zero Items. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >Override Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Overrides of this treatment tolerance violation, including the authorization by a qualified person to continue treatment delivery.
Zero or one Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Operator Identification Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Identification of the operator who authorized the override.
One or more Items shall be present.

table_lines.usage: The Observer Type (0040,A084) shall be PSN.

table_lines.name: >>Override DateTime
table_lines.comment: Date and Time when the user authorized the override.

table_lines.name: >>Override Reason
table_lines.comment:
User-defined reason of the override.
May contain notes, e.g. on the justification why the treatment was delivered in the presence of an interlock or unexpected machine condition.

table_lines.name: >>Alternate Value Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The alternate value for the parameter as accepted by the user when the override was entered. The actual value applied during treatment may be different.
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Confirmation Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Records confirmations (sign-offs) by treatment session operators of details that may not be verified electronically (e.g. the presence of devices).
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Interlock Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Interlocks that occurred prior, during or after the delivery of radiation covered by this SOP Instance.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Additional Parameter Recording Instance Sequence
table_lines.comment:
SOP Instances that contain additional recording of treatment parameters.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.
See

table_lines.name: >Creator-Version UID
table_lines.comment:
Unique identification of the equipment and version of the software that has created the referenced Instance that contains the additional parameters.
The UID allows one to avoid attempting to interpret the additional parameters with an unknown format.
Required if the Referenced SOP Class UID (0008,1150) is Raw Data Storage ("1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.66"). May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: RT Radiation Task Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Subset of RT Radiations to be delivered and/or to have quality assurance procedures applied.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.
All RT Radiation SOP Instances in the referenced RT Radiation Set shall either be in this Sequence or the Omitted Radiation Sequence (300A,0787). Correspondingly the sum of the number of Items in this Sequence and the number of Items in the Omitted Radiation Sequence (300A,0787) shall be the number of RT Radiation SOP Instances in the referenced RT Radiation Set.
If a complete fraction (no continuation of a previously interrupted treatment) is to be delivered, the number of Items in the Sequence shall be the number of RT Radiation SOP Instances in the referenced RT Radiation Set. The Omitted Radiation Sequence (300A,0787) will not be present in this case.

table_lines.name: >Referenced RT Radiation Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Reference to a single RT Radiation SOP Instance containing the parameters to be used for the delivery of the RT Radiation.
The reference shall contain an RT Radiation SOP Instance that has been referenced in the RT Radiation Set SOP Instance in the Referenced RT Radiation Set Sequence (300A,0702).
Only a single Item shall be included in this sequence.

table_lines.name: >RT Delivery Start Patient Position Sequence
table_lines.comment:

The content of this Sequence shall take precedence over the treatment positions specified in the referenced RT Radiation.
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Treatment Delivery Continuation Flag
table_lines.comment: Whether the task defines a continuation of a previously interrupted treatment delivery of the referenced RT Radiation.

table_lines.name: >Continuation Start Meterset
table_lines.comment:
Meterset within the RT Radiation referenced in the Referenced RT Radiation Sequence (300A,0630) at which treatment delivery starts.
The Meterset is expressed in units specified by Radiation Dosimeter Unit Sequence (300A,0658) in the referenced RT Radiation SOP Instance.
Required if Treatment Delivery Continuation Flag (300A,0708) is YES.

table_lines.name: >Continuation End Meterset
table_lines.comment:
Meterset within the RT Radiation referenced in the Referenced RT Radiation Sequence (300A,0630) at which treatment delivery ends.
The Meterset is expressed in units specified by Radiation Dosimeter Unit Sequence (300A,0658) in the referenced RT Radiation SOP Instance.
Required if Treatment Delivery Continuation Flag (300A,0708) is YES and the Continuation End Meterset (0074,0121) is not equal to the Meterset of the last RT Control Point in the referenced RT Radiation SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: >Radiation Order Index
table_lines.comment:
Index defining the order in which the RT Radiations are to be delivered.
The value shall start at 1, and increase monotonically by 1.

table_lines.name: >Referenced RT Treatment Preparation Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Reference to a RT Treatment Preparation SOP Instance that applies to this delivery.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Omitted Radiation Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Subset of RT Radiations that are not to be delivered.
The delivery system shall not deliver any RT Radiations referenced in this Sequence.
Required if one or more RT Radiation SOP Instances contained in the referenced RT Radiation Set are not to be delivered.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Referenced RT Radiation Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The RT Radiation SOP Instance that is not to be delivered.
The reference shall contain an RT Radiation SOP Instance that has been referenced in the RT Radiation Set SOP Instance in the Referenced RT Radiation Set Sequence (300A,0702).
Only a single Item shall be included in this sequence.

table_lines.name: >Reason for Omission Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Reason the RT Radiation is not to be delivered.

table_lines.name: Stop Cumulative Meterset

table_lines.comment:

table_lines.comment:

table_lines.comment:

table_lines.name: >>RT Beam Modifier Definition Distance
table_lines.comment:
Absolute distance in mm along the z-axis of the Base Beam Modifier Coordinate System from the reference location specified by RT Device Distance Reference Location Code Sequence (300A,0659) to the Beam Modifier Definition Plane.

Groups of Annotations sharing common characteristics, such as graphic type, properties or measurements.

table_lines.comment: Identification number of the Annotation Group. Uniquely identifies a Annotation Group within this SOP Instance. Shall start at a value of 1, and increase monotonically by 1.

table_lines.name: >Annotation Group UID
table_lines.comment: Unique identifier of the Annotation Group.

table_lines.usage:
May not be necessary if the anatomy is implicit in the Annotation Property Type Code Sequence (006A,000A).

More than one Item in Anatomic Region Sequence (0008,2218) may be used when a region of interest spans multiple anatomical locations and there is not a single pre-coordinated code describing the combination of locations. There is no requirement that the multiple locations be contiguous.

table_lines.name: >Annotation Property Category Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence defining the general category of the property the Annotation Group represents.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Annotation Property Type Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence defining the specific property the Annotation Group represents.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Annotation Property Type Modifier Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence defining the modifier of the property type of this Annotation Group.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Number of Annotations
table_lines.comment:
The number of Annotations in this Annotation Group.
Each point, polyline or polygon, ellipse or rectangle is counted as one Annotation.

table_lines.name: >Annotation Applies to All Optical Paths
table_lines.comment: Whether the Annotations in this Annotation Group apply to all the optical paths within the corresponding images.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Optical Path Identifier
table_lines.comment:
Identifies one or more optical paths to which this Annotation applies.
Refers to the same value in Optical Path Identifier (0048,0106) within the Optical Path Sequence (0048,0105) in the images to which this Annotation applies.
More than one value may be present if the Annotations apply to more than one (but not all) Optical Paths.
Required if Annotation Applies to All Optical Paths (006A,000D) is NO.

table_lines.name: >Annotation Applies to All Z Planes
table_lines.comment:
Whether the Annotations in this Annotation Group apply to the full thickness of the tissue on the slide. I.e., they are applicable regardless of the focal plane, in the case that images were acquired with multiple focal planes (Z-stacks).
Required if Annotation Coordinate Type (006A,0001) is 3D.

table_lines.name: >Common Z Coordinate Value
table_lines.comment:
More than one value may be present if the Annotations apply to more than one (but not all) Z planes.
Required if Annotation Coordinate Type (006A,0001) is 3D, and all points in Point Coordinates Data (0066,0016) or Double Point Coordinates Data (0066,0022) are in the same Z plane(s).
See

table_lines.name: >Point Coordinates Data
table_lines.comment:
The coordinates of one or more points that define the Annotations (whether single points or polygons), encoded in (X, Y) or (X, Y, Z) order.
Required if Double Point Coordinates Data (0066,0022) is not present.
For each point, two coordinates (X, Y) shall be encoded if Common Z Coordinate Value (006A,0010) is present, otherwise three coordinates (X, Y, Z) shall be encoded.
See

table_lines.name: >Double Point Coordinates Data
table_lines.comment:
The coordinates of one or more points that define the Annotations (whether single points or polygons), encoded in (X, Y) or (X, Y, Z) order.
Required if Point Coordinates Data (0066,0016) is not present.
For each point, two coordinates (X, Y) shall be encoded if Common Z Coordinate Value (006A,0010) is present, otherwise three coordinates (X, Y, Z) shall be encoded.
See

table_lines.name: >Long Primitive Point Index List
table_lines.comment: Required if Graphic Type (0070,0023) is POLYLINE or POLYGON.

table_lines.name: >Recommended Display CIELab Value
table_lines.comment:
Default triplet value in which it is recommended that the Annotation Group be rendered. The units are specified in PCS-Values, and the value is encoded as CIELab.
See

table_lines.name: >Measurements Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Measurements for some or all Annotations in the Annotation Group. Each Item describes one type of measurement.
See
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Concept Name Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Defines the type of measurement stored in this Item.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Measurement Units Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Units of measurement for the value in this Item.
Only a single Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Measurement Values Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The measurement values for the Annotation Group.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>Floating Point Values
table_lines.comment:
Measurement values for Annotations stored in this Annotation Group.
If Annotation Index List (006A,0011) is present, measurement values are stored for a subset of Annotations, and the number of values shall match the number and order of indices in Annotation Index List (006A,0011).
If Annotation Index List (006A,0011) is absent, measurement values are stored for every Annotation in Long Primitive Point Index List (0066,0040), if present, and the number of values shall match the number and order of Annotations in Long Primitive Point Index List (0066,0040) .
If Annotation Index List (006A,0011) and Long Primitive Point Index List (0066,0040) are absent, measurement values are stored for every Annotation stored in Point Coordinates Data (0066,0016) or Double Point Coordinates Data (0066,0022), and the number of values shall match thevalue of Number of Annotations (006A,000C).
See

table_lines.name: >>>Annotation Index List
table_lines.comment:
List of indices referencing Annotations identified in Long Primitive Point Index List (0066,0040) or successive points stored in Point Coordinates Data (0066,0016) or Double Point Coordinates Data (0066,0022) for which measurement values shall be stored.
Required if Measurement Values stored in Floating Point Values (0066,0125) are associated with only a subset of Annotations.
See

table_lines.name: >>Reason for Removal Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Reason the Series was removed from operational use.
Required if Removed from Operational Use (0008,0405) value is Y.
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.usage: Defined Context Group DCID 7031 Reason for Removal from Operational Use.

table_lines.name: >>Series Number
table_lines.comment: A number that identifies this Series.

table_lines.name: >>Series Description
table_lines.comment: Description of the Series.

table_lines.name: >>Series Date
table_lines.comment: Date the Series started.

table_lines.name: >>Series Time
table_lines.comment: Time the Series started.

table_lines.name: >>Laterality
table_lines.comment: Laterality of (paired) body part examined.

table_lines.name: >>Request Attributes Sequence
table_lines.comment: One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.usage: Recording of prior Attribute values and provenance of metadata changes at the Series level. See

table_lines.name: >>File Set Access Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Non-DICOM protocol methods to access the set of stored SOP Instances comprising this Series.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>Container File Type
table_lines.comment: Required if File Access URI (0008,0409) is present.

table_lines.name: >>Storage Media File-set ID
table_lines.comment: A human readable Identifier that identifies the Storage Media on which the Series resides.

table_lines.name: >>Inventoried Instances Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Records of SOP Instances whose Study, Series and Instance Attribute values match the Scope of Inventory.
See
Required if Inventory Level (0008,0403) has value INSTANCE.
Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>Specific Character Set
table_lines.comment:
Character Set that expands or replaces the Basic Graphic Set for this Item.
Required if an extended or replacement character set, other than those specified or implied for the Series level Attributes, is used in the Instance level Attributes. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >>>SOP Class UID
table_lines.comment: SOP Class UID of the inventoried SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: >>>SOP Instance UID
table_lines.comment: SOP Instance UID of the inventoried SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: >>>Instance Number
table_lines.comment: A number that identifies the inventoried SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: >>>Related General SOP Class UID
table_lines.comment: Uniquely identifies a Related General SOP Class for the SOP Class of the inventoried Instance.

table_lines.name: >>>Content Date
table_lines.comment: The date that creation of the content of the inventoried SOP Instance started.

table_lines.name: >>>Content Time
table_lines.comment: The time that creation of the content of the inventoried SOP Instance started.

table_lines.name: >>>Timezone Offset From UTC
table_lines.comment:
Offset from UTC to the timezone for all DA and TM Attributes present in the inventoried Instance, and for all DT Attributes present in the inventoried Instance that do not contain an explicitly encoded timezone offset.
See

table_lines.name: >>>Rows
table_lines.comment: Number of pixel matrix rows in the inventoried Image SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: >>>Columns
table_lines.comment: Number of pixel matrix columns in the inventoried Image SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: >>>Number of Frames
table_lines.comment: Number of frames in the inventoried Image SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: >>>Bits Allocated
table_lines.comment: Number of bits allocated for each pixel sample in the inventoried Image SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: >>>Observation DateTime
table_lines.comment: The date and time at which the root Content Item of the inventoried Document SOP Instance was completed.

table_lines.name: >>>Concept Name Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
A coded description of the content or type of the inventoried SOP Instance.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>Content Template Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Attributes of the Template that describes the content structure and constraints for the inventoried Document SOP Instance.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>>Template Identifier
table_lines.comment: Identifier of the Template as defined by the Mapping Resource (0008.0105).

table_lines.name: >>>>Mapping Resource
table_lines.comment: Resource that defines the Template.

table_lines.name: >>>Referenced Request Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Requested Procedures that were fulfilled (completely or partially) by the inventoried Document SOP Instance.
One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>Specimen Description Sequence
table_lines.comment: One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>>Specimen Identifier
table_lines.comment: A departmental information system identifier for the Specimen.

table_lines.name: >>>>Specimen UID
table_lines.comment: Unique Identifier for Specimen.

table_lines.name: >>>Content Label
table_lines.comment: A label that is used to identify the inventoried SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: >>>Content Description
table_lines.comment: A description of the content of the inventoried SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: >>>Presentation Creation Date
table_lines.comment: Date on which the inventoried Presentation State SOP Instance was created.

table_lines.name: >>>Presentation Creation Time
table_lines.comment: Time at which the inventoried Presentation State SOP Instance was created.

table_lines.name: >>>Content Creator's Name
table_lines.comment: Name of operator who created the content of the inventoried SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: >>>Removed from Operational Use
table_lines.comment: Required if this SOP Instance is not to be used for operational purposes, and Removed from Operational Use (0008,0405) Attribute at Study or Series level does not have the value Y. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: >>>Reason for Removal Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Reason the SOP Instance was removed from operational use.
Required if Removed from Operational Use (0008,0405) value is Y.
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.usage: Recording of prior Attribute values and provenance of metadata changes at the Instance level. See

table_lines.name: >>>File Access Sequence
table_lines.comment: One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>Storage Media File-set ID
table_lines.comment: A human readable Identifier that identifies the Storage Media on which the Instance resides.

table_lines.name: >>>Alternate Representation Sequence
table_lines.comment: One or more Items are permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>>>Series Instance UID
table_lines.comment:
Unique identifier of the Series of the alternate representation.
Required if the alternate representation is in a different Series than the inventoried SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: >>>>SOP Class UID
table_lines.comment: SOP Class UID of the alternate representation SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: >>>>SOP Instance UID
table_lines.comment: SOP Instance UID of the alternate representation SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: >>>>Purpose of Reference Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
The nature of the alternate encoding.
One Item shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Scope of Inventory Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.
An empty Sequence, or a Sequence with a single empty Item, indicates Universal Match to all Studies in the Repository.

table_lines.name: >Extended Matching Mechanisms
table_lines.comment: Required if extended matching mechanisms were applied.

table_lines.name: >Specific Character Set
table_lines.comment: Required if Attributes within the Sequence Item use an expanded or replacement character set.

table_lines.name: >Timezone Offset from UTC
table_lines.comment: Required if Extended Matching Mechanisms (0008,040F) includes value TIMEZONE_ADJUST.

table_lines.name: >Query/Retrieve Level
table_lines.comment: Required if Extended Matching Mechanisms (0008,040F) includes value RELATIONAL.

table_lines.name: >Range Matching Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Exactly two Items shall be included in this Sequence.
Required if Range Matching is applied to any Key Attribute.

table_lines.name: >>Any DA, DT, or TM Attributes
table_lines.comment:
Key Attribute values for matching.
Multiple Attributes may be present.

table_lines.name: >List of UID Matching Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Required if List of UID Matching is applied to any Key Attribute.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Any UI Key Attribute
table_lines.comment: Key Attribute value for matching.

table_lines.name: >Empty Value Matching Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Key Attributes for Empty Value Matching.
See
Required if Extended Matching Mechanisms (0008,040F) includes value EMPTY_VALUE and Empty Value Matching is applied to any Key Attribute.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Any Attributes
table_lines.comment:
Key Attributes with zero-length values.
Multiple Attributes may be present.

table_lines.name: >General Matching Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Required if Single Value, Multiple Value, or Wild Card matching is applied to any Key Attribute.
Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >>Any Attributes
table_lines.comment:
Key Attribute values for matching.
Multiple Attributes may be present.

table_lines.comment: Required if File Access URI (0008,0409) is present.

table_lines.name: Filename in Container
table_lines.comment: Required if Container File Type (0008,040A) is ZIP, TAR, or TARGZIP.

table_lines.name: File Offset in Container
table_lines.comment: Required if Container File Type (0008,040A) is BLOB. May be present otherwise.

table_lines.name: File Length in Container

table_lines.name: Stored Instance Transfer Syntax UID
table_lines.comment:
Transfer Syntax of the SOP Instance encoded in DICOM File Format. Equal to Transfer Syntax UID (0002,0010) in File Meta Information header of the stored Instance.
Required if File Access URI (0008,0409) is present.

table_lines.name: Lossy Image Compression Ratio
table_lines.comment:
Describes the approximate lossy compression ratio(s) that have been applied to this image.
See

table_lines.name: MAC Algorithm
table_lines.comment: Required if MAC (0400,0404) is present.

table_lines.comment: SOP Class UID of the Inventory SOP Instance included by reference.

table_lines.name: Referenced SOP Instance UID
table_lines.comment: SOP Instance UID of the Inventory SOP Instance included by reference.

table_lines.name: Inventory Access End Points Sequence
table_lines.comment: Only a single Item is permitted in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Incorporated Inventory Instance Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Required if the referenced Inventory SOP Instance itself includes Inventory SOP Instances by reference.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.usage: Recursive inclusion to describe a tree of referenced Inventory SOP Instances.

table_lines.comment: AE Title end point from which SOP Instances may be retrieved using a C-MOVE or C-GET based SOP Class (see

table_lines.comment: Base URI end point of the origin server from which SOP Instances may be retrieved using a DICOM web-based service (see

table_lines.comment: chapter_P

table_lines.usage: Key Attribute values for the Studies to be included in the Inventory.

table_lines.name: Transaction UID
table_lines.comment: Unique identifier of a transaction initiating the production of an Inventory.

table_lines.name: Transaction Status
table_lines.comment: Processing status for this transaction. (See

table_lines.name: Transaction Status Comment
table_lines.comment: Explanation or further detail of Transaction Status (0008,0417).

table_lines.name: Inventory Purpose
table_lines.comment: Purpose for which the Inventory is to be created.

table_lines.name: Inventory Level
table_lines.comment: Information Entity level for records to be included in Inventory.

table_lines.name: Referenced SOP Class UID
table_lines.comment: SOP Class UID of the produced Inventory SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: Retrieve AE Title
table_lines.comment: AE Title from which the Inventory SOP Instance may be retrieved through Inventory MOVE or Inventory GET SOP Classes (see

table_lines.name: Retrieve URL
table_lines.comment: Base URI of the origin server from which the Inventory SOP Instance may be retrieved through the Non-Patient Instance Service (see

table_lines.name: Total Number of Study Records
table_lines.comment: Number of Studies found and processed into Inventory SOP Instances (as of time of message) that match Scope of Inventory.

table_lines.name: Requested Status Interval
table_lines.comment: Requested interval, in minutes, between Inventory Status notifications. Value shall be greater than 0.

table_lines.name: Retain Instances
table_lines.comment: Whether produced Inventory SOP Instances should be retained when Inventory production is canceled.

table_lines.name: File-set ID
table_lines.comment: User or implementation specific Identifier (up to 16 characters). For definition, see

table_lines.name: File-set Descriptor File ID
table_lines.comment: ID of a File (in the same File-set) used for user comments related to the File-set (e.g., a README file). The Specific Character set used may be specified in the Specific Character Set of the File-set Descriptor File (0004,1142).

table_lines.name: Specific Character Set of File-set Descriptor File
Offset of the First Directory Record of the Root Directory Entity
table_lines.comment: Offset of the first byte (of the Item Data Element) of the first Directory Record of the Root Directory Entity. This Offset is a number of bytes starting with the first byte of the File Meta Information. When the Root Directory Entity contains no Directory Record, this offset shall be set to 00000000H.

table_lines.name: Offset of the Last Directory Record of the Root Directory Entity
table_lines.comment: Offset of the first byte (of the Item Data Element) of the last Directory Record of the Root Directory Entity. This Offset is a number of bytes starting with the first byte of the File Meta Information. When the Root Directory Entity contains no Directory Record, this offset shall be set to 00000000H.

table_lines.name: File-set Consistency Flag
table_lines.comment: The value FFFFH shall never be present.

table_lines.name: Directory Record Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence of zero or more Items where each Item contains a Directory Record by including the Directory Elements from (0004,1400) to (0004,1511) and Record selection Keys as defined below (marked with a >).
A zero length Value indicates that no Directory Records are contained in the Root Directory Entity.

table_lines.name: >Offset of the Next Directory Record
table_lines.comment:
Offset of the first byte (of the Item Data Element) of the next Directory Record of the same Directory Entity. This Offset is an unsigned integer representing a number of bytes starting with the first byte of the File Meta-information. A zero offset shall be used to mean that there is no other Directory Record in this Directory Entity.
This Offset may be used to keep an inactive Record (0004,1410) chained with the next Directory Record of the same Directory Entity.

table_lines.name: >Record In-use Flag
table_lines.comment:
The value 0000H shall never be present.
Other Values are reserved and shall not be set by File-set Creators, but if present shall be interpreted as FFFFH by File-set Readers or Updaters.

table_lines.name: >Offset of Referenced Lower-Level Directory Entity
table_lines.comment:
Offset of the first byte (of the Item Data Element) of the first Directory Record of the Referenced Lower Level Directory Entity. This Offset is a number of bytes starting with the first byte of the File Meta Information.
When no lower-level Directory Entity (containing at least one Directory Record) is referenced, this Attribute shall have a Value of 00000000H.

table_lines.name: >Directory Record Type
table_lines.comment: sect_F.4

table_lines.name: >Private Record UID
table_lines.comment: sect_F.5

table_lines.name: >Referenced File ID
table_lines.comment: All referenced Files shall be with the File-set to which the Directory belongs. Any File within the File-set (to which the Directory belongs) shall be referenced by at most one Directory Record. When the Directory Record does not reference any SOP Instance this Attribute shall not be present.

table_lines.name: >Referenced SOP Class UID in File
table_lines.comment:
Unique ID for the SOP Class of the Instance stored in the referenced File.
Required if the Directory Record references a SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: >Referenced SOP Instance UID in File
table_lines.comment:
Unique Identifier for the SOP Instance stored in the referenced file.
Required if the Directory Record references a SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Transfer Syntax UID in File
table_lines.comment:
Unique Identifier for the Transfer Syntax used to encode the Instance stored in the referenced file.
Required if the Directory Record references a SOP Instance.

table_lines.name: >Referenced Related General SOP Class UID in File
table_lines.comment:
Unique ID for the Related General SOP Class(es) related to the SOP Class of the Instance stored in the referenced file.
Required if the Directory Record references a SOP Instance that encodes the Related General SOP Class UID (0008,001A).

table_lines.name: Specific Character Set
table_lines.comment: Required if an extended or replacement character set is used in one of the keys.

table_lines.comment:
Sequence that defines the type of imaging Studies to which this Hanging Protocol applies.
One or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Procedure Code Sequence
table_lines.comment: Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: >Reason for Requested Procedure Code Sequence
table_lines.comment: Zero or more Items shall be included in this Sequence.

table_lines.name: Hanging Protocol User Identification Code Sequence
table_lines.comment:
Sequence that provides a coded identifier for the person, group, or site for which this Hanging Protocol was defined.
Zero or one Item shall be included in this Sequence.
